title: hunt's chili spaghetti
directions: Prep: 5 minutes. Cook: 20 minutes. Serves 4.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan. Then mix cornflakes and margarine and spread over the top of the potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes after removing from oven.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook and drain cabbage; place in a casserole dish with cheese, bell peppers, onion and pimento.
Spread out; pour mushroom soup on top.
Sprinkle herb dressing on top.
Dot with butter.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: tired mama cake
directions: Place cherries and pineapple in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over the filling.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Slice butter and lay on top of nuts and cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 400 degrees for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 2 deep dish or 3 small pies.

title: lemon lush
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, margarine and nuts. Press into a 10 x 7-inch pan and bake for 15 minutes. Set aside and let cool.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Combine all except Monterey Jack and Cheddar cheese in mixer (can be done by hand).
Layer in casserole dish, 1/2 of mixture, 1/2 Cheddar and 1/2 Monterey Jack.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: old fashioned fruit cake
directions: Combine molasses, buttermilk, baking powder, soda and enough flour to make it thick enough to roll thin.
Cut out around a small pie plate and fry.
Cook dried apples and add sugar to sweeten, also cinnamon and allspice.

title: aunt gen's cucumber salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Tie pickling spice in cheese or put in tea ball.
Add along with rest of ingredients. Cover and marinate at least 2 hours.
Keep marinade; add more cucumbers later.

title: cherry jubilee pie(a wonderful cheesecake pie with cherries on the bottom.)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Put mix into shell and bake 15 minutes. Beat the cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla until soft and creamy.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Spoon cheese mixture on top.
Bake 30 minutes and cool.
Then spread with sour cream and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Refrigerate.

title: guacamole
directions: Cut avocados in half; remove seed and peel.
In a medium bowl, mash avocados with a fork until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Serve with vegetables or tortilla chips. Makes about 1 1/4 cups.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients in bottom of pan until smooth. Mix sugars and cocoa in bowl.
Sprinkle over cake batter.
Pour water over top of mixture and bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: *Sour cream and baking soda are mixed together.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Put in 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Stir together the peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt.
Microwave for 3 minutes.
Stir.
Microwave for 2 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla; microwave 2 minutes and 15 seconds.
Add soda and put on buttered pan.
Break up when cool.

title: chicken and mushrooms
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Wash and pat dry.
Season with salt and pepper.
In skillet, heat butter (substitute margarine for low cholesterol), garlic and 2/3 of the oil.
Brown chicken on both sides (about 10 minutes).
Lower heat, add herbs and continue cooking 25 minutes.

title: cola date loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Heat cola to boiling in a saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in dates, mixing well.
Stir in brown sugar and oil.
Set aside to cool.

title: t v snacks
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large pan.
Mix all other ingredients well.
Pour over dry ingredients; mix real well.
Bake in slow oven (200°) for 1 hour, stirring about every 10 minutes.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend oleo and sugars together.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Set aside.
Blend together flour, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix together, then stir in oatmeal.
Drop by spoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 7 to 8 minutes at 375°.

title: carrot and nut cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Frost with:

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream sugar, brown sugar, shortening and peanut butter together.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla together; beat well.
Stir together salt, baking soda and flour; then add all to peanut butter mixture.
Mix very well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in additional granulated sugar.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar, water and butter in saucepan. Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add beaten egg yolks. Cook for 4 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Stir in lemon juice and lemon rind.
Let stand until cooled completely.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites in mixer bowl until soft peaks form.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar gradually, beating until stiff peaks form.
Spread over top of pie, sealing to edge.
Bake at 400° until browned.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: geneva's mary jane cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Make small balls from mixture and roll balls in coconut.

title: polk county (florida) potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until just past crunch. Boil eggs with potatoes.
Drain and rinse.
Mix all together; sprinkle paprika on top.
Chill, but can eat warm.
Great!

title: waldorf salad
directions: Variation:
Instead of celery, add cubed pineapple

title: jazz-ma-tazz stuffed spuds
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in skillet over medium heat. Cook green pepper, onion and celery 5 minutes.
Add seasonings, meats and potatoes.
Remove from heat. Stir in 1 cup each cheese. Mound mixture into potato shells.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Top with extra cheese.
Serves 4.

title: baked rice and onion
directions: Mix, cover and bake 30 minutes at 425°.
Quick, good and goes with whatever.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each. Add vanilla and vinegar; fold in the flour, then add syrup and nuts. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost.

title: chocolate spiders
directions: Place chocolate morsels in top of double boiler.
Bring water to a boil. Reduce heat to low and cook until morsels melt.
Add noodles and nuts, mixing well. Drop by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet. Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: egg, cheese and olive casserole
directions: Butter an 8 x 13-inch baking pan.
Alternate layers of bread, cheeses and ripe olives.
Beat eggs and combine with dry mustard and milk.
Pour over bread/cheese layers.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Garnish with green stuffed olives.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lasagna
directions: Pour oil into a skillet.
Brown the onions and ground beef for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add garlic, salt, pepper, oregano, parsley, tomatoes, tomato puree and tomato paste.
Cover with lid.
Simmer 45 minutes.

title: elfin chip cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth. Add sugar gradually. Beat in sour cream and vanilla and then mix in Cool Whip. Stir in chips and pour into crust.
Chill for 6 hours.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Sprinkle cucumbers with salt.
Let stand 30 minutes, drain. Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over cucumbers and chill.
Can also add sliced onion to cucumbers.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Add onions and peppers.
Continue to cook until onion is transparent.
Stir in tomatoes, rice, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Pour in greased 2-quart casserole. Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove.
Cover the last 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: shoe peg salad
directions: Drain canned vegetables well.
Chop onion, green pepper and pimentos; add to canned vegetables. Mix remaining ingredients and add to vegetables.
Let set overnight or several hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake 45 minutes in unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake 5 minutes at 425° to set pie shell, then reduce heat to 325° and bake until filling cracks around the edges of crust.

title: piping hot biscuits
directions: Roll dough half as thick as you like your biscuits.
Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar, salt and cream of tartar. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk all at once.
Stir with a fork just until moistened, knead gently 10 times on lightly floured surface.
Roll or pat dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 16.

title: floating tacos
directions: Cook hamburger and onion. Drain.
Return to large saucepan. Add seasonings, tomato sauce, rice and water.
Cook over medium heat for 1 hour. Add water as it cooks, if needed.
Spoon over corn chips and garnish with your favorite toppings (tomato, lettuce, cheese, taco sauce, etc.).

title: french-cheese bread
directions: Cut bread in diagonal slices.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Spread mix on both sides of slices and put bread back together on a piece of foil.
Wrap bread in foil securely and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Cover potatoes with vegetable oil and wine vinegar; place in refrigerator until cool.
Add pimento pepper, bell pepper, onion, dill pickle, cabbage, carrots, ripe olives, salt and pepper.
Toss with 1 cup mayonnaise and 1 tablespoon mustard.
Mix and serve.

title: vinaigrette for tomatoes
directions: Mix well. Cut tomatoes in wedges. Makes enough for 8 tomatoes.

title: pie filling squares
directions: Pack in a 9 x 12 pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: seasoned salt
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: pea soup
directions: Combine; simmer uncovered 3 to 4 hours.

title: bacon cheese brunch
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cut bacon slices into fourths.
Cook until crisp; drain.
Mix apples and sugar.
Spread in baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour over top. Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: zesty chicken and rice
directions: Put rice and dressing mix in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish. Pour broth over the top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in pan.
When broccoli is done, drain excess water.
Add butter, soup and Cheez Whiz to broccoli.
Cook on low heat until cheese melts.
Add rice to all ingredients in casserole dish and stir.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook in oven at 250° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: jane's corn pudding no. 2
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: raspberry spread
directions: Mix ingredients together in bowl.
Ready for spreading.

title: double fudge mallow cake
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add cocoa and sugar.
Mix well. Beat eggs slightly in mixing bowl, then add cocoa mixture to eggs, beating until frothy at high speed.
Add flour, salt and vanilla, mixing well.
Fold in nuts.

title: chicken pasta
directions: In a large pot, cook pasta according to package directions, drain.
Add approximately 2 tbsp. olive oil and chopped basil leaves to pasta and toss.
Set aside.

title: crabmeat appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on English muffin halves.
Bake at 350° until bubbly on top.
Cut each half of muffin into 4 pieces and serve hot.

title: crispy chicken
directions: Blend honey and French dressing.
Dip chicken in dressing and then in crumbs.
Coat well.
Place in foil-lined flat pan.
Do not crowd.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until tender.
May be used hot or thoroughly chill to use for picnic.

title: italian zucchini pie(1980 pillsbury grand prize winner)
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook zucchini and onion in the margarine until tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in parsley, salt, pepper, garlic powder, basil and oregano.
In a large bowl, beat eggs and cheese.
Stir in vegetable mixture.

title: burnt sugar pie
directions: Using an iron skillet, brown one cup of the sugar to a dark brown syrup (watch carefully).
Sift remaining sugar, flour and salt.
Add milk gradually.
Add this mixture to syrup.
Stir and cook until thickened.
Add a small amount of hot mixture into beaten egg yolks; stir, then add yolks to sugar mixture and continue cooking and stirring another 2 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla; blend.
Pour into baked 9-inch pie crust.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix 2 eggs, 1 stick butter and butter cake mix and spread in pan.
Then mix 2 eggs, 1 stick butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar; spread on top of other layer.
Bake for 1 hour or until middle sinks in oven at 350°.

title: mildred evans' pound cake
directions: Cream butter until fluffy.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flavoring.
Combine sifted cake flour and salt in another bowl and gradually add small amounts to the butter mixture.
Alternate with the milk until all is mixed.
Pour into a greased and floured 4 x 16-inch loaf pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool 5 to 6 minutes and remove from the pan to cooling rack.

title: baked herbed chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: punch
directions: Mix pineapple juice and lemonade.
Chill until serving time. At that time, add chilled club soda or 7-Up.
Dip pineapple sherbet and place on top of punch in bowl at serving time.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, celery, green pepper, onion, pimento and salt in large bowl.
Let stand 1 hour; drain well.
Meanwhile, mix sugar, vinegar and seeds in saucepan.
Heat to boil.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Let cool.
Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate covered until cold.
Store in glass jars in the refrigerator up to 2 months.
Serve as hot dog topping with sandwiches or on a relish tray.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: Tear bread into a large mixing bowl.
Add milk and egg.
Add meat and seasonings; mix thoroughly.

title: fruit filled thumbprint cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl combine all ingredients except egg whites, nuts and preserves.
Beat at low speed, scraping bowl often, until well mixed (2 to 3 minutes). Shape rounded teaspoon of dough into 1-inch balls.
In a small bowl, beat egg whites with a fork until foamy.
Dip each ball into egg whites; roll in chopped nuts.
Place 1-inch apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Make a depression in center of each cookie with back of spoon.
Bake 8 minutes; remove from oven.
Fill centers with preserves.
Continue baking 6 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: angel food ice cream cake
directions: Line a tray with heavy wax paper.
Slice the angel food cake in thirds horizontally. Slice the ice cream in thirds horizontally.
Place a layer of cake, a layer of ice cream, cake, ice cream, cake and ice cream. Cover and store in freezer.
Slice and serve when ready.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage until tender, drain and set aside until cool. Then chop fine.
Mix together beaten egg, butter, milk, salt and paprika.
Stir into cabbage and put into buttered casserole dish. Sprinkle bread crumbs over top and bake until brown.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Wash and drain vegetables.
Break broccoli and cauliflower (fine).
Chop onion.
Add pimento.
Mix mayonnaise, oil, sugar and vinegar together in a jar.
Combine dressing with vegetables; toss to coat.
Refrigerate overnight or a few hours.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix the dry ingredients, then make a hole and put in egg, milk and the apples.
Drop by spoonful in hot lard and fry like doughnuts.
Cover with powdered sugar glaze.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons juice.
Add 3 tablespoons flour to the sugar.
Stir in juice and mix well.
Fold in pineapple and cheese; mix well.

title: tex-mex tortillas
directions: Stir-fry tortillas in oil for 2 minutes.
Add onions, tomato sauce, salt and water.
Top with cheese and simmer until water is absorbed and cheese is melted.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Place flour in a 10-inch cast-iron skillet.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until dark brown, stirring every 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and set aside.
Combine chicken and water in a large Dutch oven; cook 20 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken and broth from Dutch oven and reserve.

Combine onion, green pepper, celery, garlic and 1/3 cup chicken broth in Dutch oven. Cook over medium heat 10 to 12 minutes or until vegetables are tender, add browned flour and 1 cup chicken broth; stir until blended.
Gradually stir in remaining broth; add green onions and next 7 ingredients.
Remove chicken from bones and chop into bite-size pieces.
Add to Dutch oven.
Cover and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaves.
Serve gumbo with rice. Yield:
10 servings (228 calories per 1 cup serving with 1/3 cup rice.)

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a bowl.
Mix lightly.
Shape into balls.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add meatballs and cook until lightly browned.
Drain on absorbent paper.

title: blueberry pineapple cream
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Toast corn flakes in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan for 8 to 10 minutes.
Combine butter and sugar.
Pour over cereal; stir until evenly coated.
Reserve 3 tablespoons for top.
Press remaining mixture into bottom of pan.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven until set.

title: apple 'n' honey glaze(glaze for ham)
directions: In a small bowl combine all ingredients.
Spoon 3/4 cup sauce over ham surface during the last 30 minutes of baking.
Heat remaining sauce and serve with ham.
Makes enough glaze for a 4 pound half ham.
Double for whole ham.

title: dutch oven sheepherder's bread
directions: Combine hot water, butter, salt and sugar (or honey).
Stir until butter is melted.
With temperature of about 110° stir in yeast.
Cover and let stand until real bubbly.
Start mixing flour, eggs, gluten and dough enhancer until you have a stiff mix.
Put dough on a floured board or table and knead, using as little flour as possible to keep it from sticking.
About 15 or 20 minutes and it should be well kneaded.
Place in greased bowl and cover.
Put in a warm place and let it rise, about 1 to 2 hours.
Punch it down and knead for another ten minutes.
Place back in pan and let rise again.

title: chocolate turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour 1/2 of mix into pan.
Bake 15 minutes in preheated oven at 350°.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix up sour cream, whipped cream and margarine in a large bowl.
Then, in a medium bowl, mix milk and vanilla pudding.
Put the pudding in the bowl.
Chop up the cookies in a blender.
Then in a large bowl, put chopped cookies on the bottom of the bowl. Then pour a layer of the pudding.
Then do it over and over until you run out.

title: five bean bake
directions: Cook bacon until light brown.
Add onions and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Add brown sugar, vinegar and seasonings.
Cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Combine with beans; bake for 2 hours at 325°.

title: scalloped tomato casserole
directions: Layer half each of tomatoes, onion, cracker crumbs, sugar and salt in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Repeat with remaining half.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, combine eggs, sugar, butter, vinegar and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into pie shell.
Bake until firm, about 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool on rack. Serve garnished with chopped nuts, whipped cream or Cool Whip if desired.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Place Eagle Brand milk, water and salt into top of double boiler and mix.
Add chocolate.
Cook over boiling water, stirring often, until thick (about 10 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Cool and spread on cake.

title: mabel's apple coffee cake
directions: Cream together sugar, margarine and egg; mix well.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add 1/2 cup cold coffee and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix all together.
Then add apples.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup brown sugar and nuts over top.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Stir yeast and 2 tablespoons sugar in warm water.
Let set 15 minutes.
Heat milk and 1/2 cup oleo in saucepan.
Measure sugar and salt in large mixing bowl.
Pour in milk mixture.
Stir until dissolved.
When lukewarm, add eggs and yeast mixture.
Add 2 1/2 cups flour; stir.
Add remaining flour and mix well.
Turn out on floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic for 5 minutes. Place in greased bowl; let rise until double in bulk, about 2 hours.
Punch down and let dough rest for 30 minutes.
Roll dough out on floured board.
Spread other 1/2 cup oleo over the dough. Mix cinnamon and sugar (1/4 cup and 3/4 cup).
Sprinkle over the oleo; roll and slice.
You may leave some for doughnuts.
Let rolls rise until double, about 2 hours.

title: fresh green bean soup
directions: String and cut up beans.
Cook cut beans and diced potatoes in 5 cups of salted water for 15 minutes.
In a frying pan brown flour in the fat; add black pepper and paprika.
Add 1/4 cup cold water and stir until smooth.
Add sour cream.
Add this mixture to the cooked beans and potatoes.
Bring to a boil and simmer for a few minutes.

title: caryn's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Chill dough in freezer for about 1 hour.

title: cream cheese scones
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and sugar.
Mix until well blended.
Add raisins, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Mix well.
Set aside.
Combine dry ingredients; blend.
Cut in oleo until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk; mix until moistened.
Divide dough in half.
On a lightly floured surface; roll out each half to a 12 x 9-inch rectangle.
Spread one half with cream cheese mixture.
Top with second half of dough.
Cut into twelve 3-inch squares; cut each square in half diagonally.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Drizzle with honey.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add eggs alternately with sour cream and flour, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.

title: rocky road-peanut butter squares
directions: Note:
Instead of Triples cereal, you may use Rice Krispies.

title: texas fudge(an appetizer)
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread Jack on the bottom.
Cover with green chilies, then cover with Cheddar.
Pour beaten eggs over all.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand before serving. Cut into squares.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix everything in order and mix well.
Bake at 350° until tested done.

title: cool whip cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Mix pineapple and pudding mix.
Fold in the Cool Whip; frost cake.
Store in refrigerator.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in water until tender, then strain water out of rice. You should have about 1 cup of rice. Mix sugar, vanilla, butter and flour together. Add eggs and mix well. Add milk and raisins to sugar mixture. Stir in rice. Pour mixture into shallow baking dish and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until set.

title: chicken casserole(serves 2 to 3)
directions: Saute almonds in butter or margarine until golden brown; set aside.
Blend soup, celery, mayonnaise and onion.
Fold in chicken and rice.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes until bubbly.
Sprinkle almonds on top for last 5 minutes.

title: fettuccine with cherry tomatoes, goat cheese and herbs
directions: Cook fettuccine until al dente.
While pasta is cooking, heat oil and garlic in small saucepan over low heat just until mixture is hot and remove from heat.
Drain fettuccine well and in a bowl, toss oil mixture, parsley, mint, tomato, goat cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 2.

title: cheese balls
directions: Cream softened cream cheese.
Add onion tops, Accent, Worcestershire sauce and 1 package chopped chipped beef.
Roll into balls.
Roll balls into chopped chipped beef.
Wrap in foil.
Store in refrigerator for 4 days.
Serve on crackers.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cut all fruits and mix thoroughly.
Add milk.
Bake in 2 pans 2 1/2 hours at 200°.
May be baked in one tube pan for 4 hours at 200°.
Line pan with brown paper and grease.
Leave in pan overnight.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Put all in blender.
Blend well.
Texture must be like most salad dressings.
Makes 1 pint.

title: stove top stuffing mix and chicken casserole
directions: Make stuffing as directed on box.
Press into an 11 x 13-inch pan or roasting dish.
Cut chicken into small pieces.
Put over top of stuffing and then add two cans of cream of chicken soup on top of chicken.
Do not dilute.
Bake about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: holiday green pea dip(serves 24)
directions: In medium bowl, mash cheese with a fork or beat with electric mixer at low speed until smooth.
Beat in milk, then sour cream, dry green pea soup mix, onion soup mix, crushed garlic and Worcestershire sauce until mixture is smooth.
Refrigerate until 30 minutes before serving.
Serve with crackers and raw vegetables.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix together sour cream and baking soda.
Add other ingredients.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: personalized fortune cookies
directions: Write fortunes on small slips of paper.

title: patty tuna sandwiches
directions: Blend; wonderful for party tea sandwiches.

title: peanut-fudge bites
directions: Combine peanut butter morsels, sweetened condensed milk and butter in a 2-quart glass bowl.
Microwave at High 1 1/2 minutes, or until morsels melt.
Stir well.
Pour mixture on a cookie sheet lined with wax paper.
Spread into a 13 x 11-inch rectangle. Smooth surface with a rolling pin.
Chill 45 minutes, or until firm.
Turn mixture onto a cutting board.
Remove wax paper.
Cut into desired shapes with 1-inch and 1 1/2-inch cookie cutters.

title: hamburgers
directions: Makes 8 patties.
I also add salt, pepper and garlic salt to each patty before frying.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Make the cake mix according to directions.
Bake in sheet pan. As soon as cake is out of oven, punch holes 1 inch apart with ice pick.
Spoon sweetened condensed milk over the cake with holes and let soak in.
Cool completely.

title: marbled chocolate chip cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat together sugars, butter and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs; combine flour, soda and salt.
Gradually beat into butter mixture until well blended.

Scoop 1/3 of dough into separate bowl. Mix in cocoa until well blended; stir in chocolate chips and stir vanilla chips into remaining white dough. Return chocolate dough to white dough, with wooden spoon and stir the two doughs just until marbled.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: queso dip
directions: Chop cheese block into small pieces and melt in a pot.
Add picante sauce and cilantro.
Let cool for about 5 minutes.
Serve with chips.

title: plain icing
directions: Cook
sugar, corn syrup and water for 20 minutes (248°) or until
firm
ball forms when tried in cold water.
Let cool for 5 to 10 minutes, then pour slowly over the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add
vanilla
and
beat until it holds its shape. Spread the
layers
and
sides,
sprinkling
the top with dry coconut.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Bring pie filling, water and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in jello until dissolved and cool.
Add 7-Up.
Chill until firm.

title: stroganoff
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients and drain.
Add onion soup, salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Cook 10 minutes.
Turn heat off and add sour cream.
Mix with buttered egg noodles.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Tear bread into small pieces.
Add all ingredients.
Cover and put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake in preheated oven (350°) 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fig cake
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, salt and spices into large bowl. Beat eggs, oil, sugar, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Fold in figs and nuts.
Pour into greased 12-cup Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Slice Twinkies and line a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix milk and cheese. Pour over desired topping.
Add Cool Whip and 2 cans of any fruit on top:
cherries, strawberries, etc.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat a small amount of oil in a large, heavy skillet.
Add corn bread batter.
Bake at 450° for about 25 minutes, or until golden brown.
(I add water to make a real soft batter and have the skillet real hot when batter is added.)
This is especially good with black-eyed peas.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat with mixer and pour into freezer canister.
Layer salt and ice around canister.
Ready in 25 to 30 minutes.
Can put into individual canisters and freeze.

title: easy vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve with raw veggies.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Slice bananas over crust. Mix cool whip, cream cheese, and sugar with mixer until smooth. Pour over bananas. Cover with blueberry pie filling. Let cool and then serve.

title: pecan sandies(makes 4 dozen)
directions: Cream softened margarine and cream cheese.
Add egg and flavoring.
Beat well.
Add dry cake mix, then add chopped pecans. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 12 minutes or until browned and done.

title: "slush" bourbon punch
directions: Boil the 2 cups of water and tea bags for 3 minutes; remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir together and freeze 12 to 24 hours.
Remove from freezer approximately 1 hour prior to serving.
Serve as slushy.
Enjoy!

title: brandy slush
directions: Steep tea in hot water for 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags and add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Freeze.
Serve with white soda or 50/50.

title: seasoned crackers
directions: Heat the oil. Add dill, garlic salt and salad dressing package; mix well.
Place crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour oil mixture over crackers and mix until well coated.

title: baked pineapple casserole
directions: Beat eggs. Add bread, sugar and marshmallows.
Add pineapple and melted butter.
Place in greased baking dish and pour milk over top. Bake, uncovered, 35 to 40 minutes or until set and brown in a 350° oven. Serve hot with meal.

title: cherry crunch cake
directions: Spread cherry pie filling over the bottom of an oblong greased baking dish.
Spread a can of crushed pineapple over cherry filling.
Pour dry cake mix over mixture.
Sprinkle nuts over top. Melt butter or margarine and pour over top.
Cover all the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: lemon-lime punch
directions: Heat 1 cup pineapple juice and dissolve lime Jell-O, stirring often.
Bring just to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add 2 cups pineapple juice and the frozen lemonade.
Allow to melt.
Mix and add the Seven-Up and mix again.
Add ice and serve.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, mix and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: cracked glass cake
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine and press in bottom and sides of pan (spring-form).
Mix each flavor of gelatin with 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Let set completely. Cut into
cubes.
Mix hot pineapple juice with unflavored gelatin and 1/4 cup cold water; add to whipped cream.
Gently fold in gelatin squares until completely mixed and pour into shell; refrigerate until firm.

title: chi chi's chile con queso
directions: Melt cheese and half and half in double boiler (may add more half and half until desired consistency).
Boil peppers until soft.
Add to melted cheese.
Add garlic powder, green chilies and jalapenos.
Stir until mixed well.
Put in crock-pot to keep warm. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.

title: elephant soup
directions: Cut elephant into bite size pieces.
Wash cloves.
Bring water to a boil.
Add chunks and cloves to water.
Let boil for 24 hours.
Turn heat down and simmer for an additional 72 hours. Salt and pepper to taste.
This will serve approximately 1,800 people.
If more guests are expected, the rabbits may be added. Do this only if necessary. . . .
most people do not like "hare" in their soup.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Saute onion and butter; mix all ingredients.
Top with cornflakes.
Drizzle 1 stick margarine.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Pour 3/4 cup boiling water over mixture.
Add Milnot and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: cheese potato and onion pie(english version)
directions: Peel, cook and mash potatoes and onions.
When ready, layer potatoes, onions and cheese in glass or regular pan (9 x 11-inch), ending with mashed potatoes on top sprinkled with cheese.
Cooking time is 25 to 30 minutes.
Tastes wonderful.
Serve by itself or with hot dogs, hamburgers, etc.

title: swedish spritz cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar a little at a time.
Mix together all ingredients.
Put 3/4 of dough mixture in a cookie press.
Press out onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with colored sugar and bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Watch to make sure they don't burn!

title: apple dump cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl.
Stir gently until mixed.
Bake at 325° in an ungreased pan for 1 hour.
Serve plain or with a cream cheese frosting.

title: chips of chocolate peanut butter cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, peanut butter and oleo.
Blend at low speed until crumbly; reserve 1 cup.
Add remaining crumb mixture in a bowl; blend at low speed until moistened.
Beat for 3 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour batter into greased bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with 1 cup reserved crumbs, then sprinkle the chocolate pieces over batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cheese salmon bake
directions: Start heating oven to 375°.
Grease 1 quart casserole.
In saucepan, melt butter and add flour, stirring until blended smooth.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly to avoid lumps. Cook, stirring until smooth and thickened.
To salmon add uncooked noodles, cheese, salt, pepper and sauce.
Combine thoroughly. Pour into casserole.
Bake 30 minutes or until set.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheesy meatball patties
directions: Combine 1/4 cup Prego, beef, bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Shape into 4 patties 1/2-inch thick.
Cook in hot oil until brown. Add remainder of the Prego. Cover.
Over heat, cook 10 minutes. Top patties with Mozzarella cheese.
Serve with spaghetti.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Prepare apples and pecans.
Set aside.
Beat oil, sugar and eggs until creamy.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Slowly add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Fold in apples, pecans and flavorings.
Line bottom of a 10-inch tube pan with wax paper.
Grease pan well and dust with flour.
Spoon batter into pan and bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: heavenly brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Mix remaining ingredients, including nuts.
Pour into 8-inch square greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients for crust.
Pat into a 13 x 9-inch dish.

title: slushy punch
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine water and sugar.
Bring to boiling, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Boil syrup gently, uncovered, for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix and put in hollowed out bread of choice.
Line bread with lettuce before putting dip in.
Use dipped out bread which has been toasted, chips of your choice or veggies for dipping.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage, drain.
Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles and place on an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan or 12-inch round cake pan with points toward center.
Press over bottom and up sides to form a crust.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes and top with Cheddar cheese.
In a bowl, beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, corn syrup, butter and vanilla; stir until blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into frozen pie crust.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven on a preheated baking sheet, 50 to 55 minutes, or until knife inserted halfway between center and edges comes out clean.
Cool on rack. Serves 8.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla and mix well but lightly.
Combine the flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to zucchini-egg mixture.
Stir until well blended; add nuts and pour into two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool on a rack. Makes 2 loaves.

title: two-flavor fudge
directions: Combine sugars, milk and butter in saucepan.
Bring to full boil over moderate heat, stirring frequently; then boil for additional 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and add Marshmallow Creme and morsels.
Stir until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Blend in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased pan.
Chill until firm.
Makes about 1 1/2 pounds.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix
softened
margarine,
powdered
sugar,
water
and vanilla
well.
Add
sifted flour and nuts; mix well.
Mixture will
be
dry and crumbly.	Mix with hands and roll into small finger size rolls.	Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 45 minutes.
Roll in sifted powdered sugar and cool.

title: old-fashioned applesauce cake
directions: In saucepan, bring applesauce, shortening and raisins to bubbling hot stage.
Stir together sugar, flour, salt, cloves, cinnamon, allspice, nutmeg and nuts (may be added).
Add 2 rounded teaspoonfuls soda to hot mixture and stir.
Pour over floured mixture and fold in.
Bake in a 325° oven in a 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 smaller bread pans until done (approximately 45 to 60 minutes).

title: old fashioned cream pie
directions: Combine and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool. Bake a pie shell and cool.
Sprinkle cinnamon in the bottom of the pie shell.
Pour in filling and sprinkle cinnamon on top.

title: chicken drummettes
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients for sauce.
Marinate drummettes overnight, turning every few hours in sauce.
Bake at 400° about 30 minutes, then put under broiler for about 5 to 8 minutes, until crusty.
Serve as a finger food.

title: milnot cheese cake
directions: Chill Milnot overnight.
Dissolve Jell-O in one cup hot water. Cream the cream cheese and sugar together.
Whip Milnot until very stiff.
Mix all this together.

title: clam casino casserole
directions: Mix altogether and bake at 350° until bubbly (45 minutes to 1 hour).
Use as a hot dip or to fill clam shells.

title: ranch bread
directions: Beat oil, sugar and eggs.
Add bananas.
Mix together remaining dry ingredients.
Mix liquid and dry ingredients together.
Blend in cherries, chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured pans or pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: ethel's holiday salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Whip when set and fold in the cream cheese, salad dressing, celery and nuts. Spoon into a mold and let set until firm.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Put half of potatoes into a blender with the other 5 ingredients. Blend on high. As blender is running, add remaining potatoes. Blend until soupy.

title: easy apple cobbler
directions: Line bottom of 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish with apples. Combine margarine, sour milk, vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir until smooth.
Pour evenly over apples and spread. Combine the brown and white sugar with the 1/2 cup water and the spices.
Pour over the batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until top is lightly brown and apples are done.

title: banana bread(this recipe makes two loaves.)
directions: Mix sugar, oil eggs and bananas in large bowl.

title: six cup salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: tedee's pork chops
directions: Spread mustard on one side of pork chops.
Flour both sides of chops. Brown in skillet. Add soup and potatoes.
Add enough water to cover chops and potatoes (about 2 cans). Simmer for 1 hour.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Cook brown sugar and 1/4 cup butter and syrup until butter is melted.
Place in the bottom of a buttered 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Sprinkle bottom with chopped nuts, if desired.
Mix warm milk and yeast and let set until yeast begins to bubble.
Add sugar, melted butter, salt, eggs and flour and mix until not sticky.
Place in an oiled bowl (covered) to rise until double in size.
Smash down and roll out half of the dough.
Brush with about 2 to 3 tablespoons butter on each half.
Sprinkle with the 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon mixture.
Roll up and slice in 1 to 2-inch pieces.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Place in pan on top of brown sugar mixture.
Allow to rise again, then bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Run a knife along the sides of the pan and dump out of the pan so the sticky topping on the bottom is on the top.

title: kentucky fried chicken slaw
directions: Chop cabbage and add carrot.
Mix other ingredients together and add to cabbage.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Stir and serve.

title: broccoli salad
directions: After bacon is fried, cut up the onion and fry the onion in the bacon grease just until the glazed stage.
Mix together the 2 tablespoons bacon grease, vinegar, sugar and mayonnaise.
Add all ingredients together (broccoli, onion and the mayonnaise mixture) and refrigerate.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Melt in microwave.
Pour over large package miniature marshmallows and pecans.

title: mushroom rice
directions: Melt margarine
and add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil; reduce heat, cover
and
cook over low heat until rice is done.

title: tuna rice bake
directions: Break tuna in chunks; combine with half the soup, rice, milk, egg yolks, lemon juice, pimento and onions.
Fold in egg whites. Turn into greased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until set.
Cut in 6 squares.
Serve with Parsley Sauce.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all these together well; then stir in 1/2 cup coconut. Place in 2 well-greased pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar, peanut butter, cream cheese and Cool Whip until smooth.
Pour into crust.
Chill until set.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sugar together and set aside.
Layer first 5 ingredients in 9 x 13 inch casserole in order given.
Next, spread mayonnaise mixture over it as if icing a cake.
Finally, sprinkle the cheese and bacon over top.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 24 hours or overnight.

title: meat loaf pie
directions: Combine meat, potatoes, catsup, onion, salt, pepper and egg. Mix well.
Press meat mixture into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Drain off excess fat. Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Arrange triangles over partially baked meat crust.
Return meat pie to oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake 5 minutes longer. Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, melt 1/3 cup margarine; add onion, carrots, celery and parsley.
Cook, stirring occasionally, 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Blend in flour, salt, pepper and mustard.
Gradually stir in chicken broth and cream, keeping smooth.
Cook until mixture comes to a boil.
Stir in chicken and rice.
Turn into ungreased casserole.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: bible school ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients, folding in Cool Whip.
Freeze in an ice cream churn.
Resembles a Wendy's Frosty.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese and peanut butter.
Finally add Cool Whip.
Mix well and fill a cooked crust.
Freeze several hours. Keeps well in freezer.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture, blending well.
Add the chocolate chips.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Put a candy kiss in the middle of each cookie. Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 10 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen cookies.

title: ricotta cheese pie
directions: Beat all ingredients with mixer.
Pour into 2 deep-dish pie shells.
Bake
at 400° for 10 minutes; reduce to 350° and bake for 35 to 45 more minutes.

title: party chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half (8 pieces); place in buttered casserole.
Cover each piece of chicken with slice of Swiss cheese.
Dilute can of soup with wine; pour over chicken. Sprinkle stuffing mix over chicken.
Drizzle melted butter over stuffing mix.
Bake, uncovered, 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Can be easily doubled.
(A great party dish!)

title: baked corn
directions: Combine corn, sugar, salt, butter and eggs.
Stir until well blended.
Heat milk but do not boil.
Add milk to corn mixture and stir until blended.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until pudding is firm like a custard.
The tip of a knife inserted near the center will come out clean when the pudding is done.

title: upside-down cake
directions: Place brown sugar and butter or margarine in a large iron skillet.
Cook over low heat until it caramelizes.
Remove from heat.
Lay on sliced pineapple with a maraschino cherry in center of each slice.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cut cherries in fourths and pineapple in small pieces.
Mix flour with fruits, nuts and vanilla.
Mix eggs, butter and sugar. Pour over fruit mixture.
Mix well.
Grease and flour tube pan. Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: graham cracker bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk and mix.
Mixture will be "soupy".
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes one large loaf or two small.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Set aside 1/4 of grated cheese.
Mix sour cream, soup, green onions, chilies, olives and remaining cheese.
Soften tortillas, spoon sour cream mixture onto tortilla and roll.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with leftover mixture, remaining cheese and add more chopped olives.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: south of the border stew
directions: Brown meats in lard or butter.
Add garlic and onions and cook until onions are limp.
Combine browned meats and remaining ingredients in a slow cooker.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours. Serve with warm tortillas.

title: pie crust
directions: Put flour and salt in a bowl.
Cut in Crisco with a pastry blender until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle water over mixture.
Quickly make a ball with mixture.
(Do not add more water.)
Use a pastry cloth and cover for rolling pin, lightly floured, and roll out 2 crusts.
(You may refrigerate dough and use later.)

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add food color, which has vinegar mixed in it.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients. Add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350°, about 30 minutes.

title: mexican pie
directions: Brown beef and onion; add salt, pepper and garlic salt. Sprinkle flour over meat; mix lightly.
Add tomato sauce, water and chili powder.
Layer corn chips, beef, beans and cheese in large baking dish until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until hot and cheese is melted.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix and bake biscuits as directed.
You need 10 to 12 large biscuits.
Butter an 11 x 14-inch bake pan.
Split biscuits and line pan with halves.
Add 1/2 the cheese and all the ham.
Put the remaining cheese on top.

title: orange carrot cake
directions: Blend all frosting ingredients; beat until smooth.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Bring water, sugar and pie cherries to boiling point.
Add jello and allow to cool for a short time.
Add pineapple and Coca-Cola.
Chill until firm.
Top with Cool Whip as desired. Makes a nice, bright addition to turkey or holiday.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Fry ground beef and cut up Italian sausage into pieces and fry until cooked.
Add to sauce.
Cover and simmer for at least 1 1/2 hours.
Add seasonings.
I season to taste.

title: mom's light lemony cheesecake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with water.
Let set until it starts to thicken.
Beat cream cheese and sugar together.
Add this to Jell-O.
Beat and set aside.
Beat Milnot and vanilla.
This will start to thicken, then add lemon and cream cheese mixture.
Beat well.
Pour over vanilla wafer crust.

title: brenda hollar's breakfast cinnamon rolls
directions: Dip frozen rolls that have been separated in melted butter, then roll in sugar mixture.
Layer in greased Bundt pan.
Pour remaining butter over rolls, then top with sugar mixture.
Cover with a towel and leave out overnight to rise.
Bake next day at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove carefully by inverting Bundt pan onto cookie sheet.
Watch for splashing butter!

title: grandma's pork roast
directions: Cut slits in roast. Put onion wedges in slits. Salt and pepper entire roast.
Cover roast with mustard and coat with flour. Place in baking pan and add water around it. Bake at 350° until done. Baste often with water to form crust.

title: chicken smetane
directions: Mix sour cream, lemon juice and seasonings together in bowl big enough to dip chicken in.
Coat chicken using all mixture. Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: cornmeal rolls
directions: Combine cornmeal, sugar, salt and milk in medium saucepan and cook until thick, the consistency of cooked cereal. Cool to lukewarm. Add yeast that has been dissolved in lukewarm water, then eggs. Beat thoroughly. Gradually add flour to firm soft dough. Knead well on a floured surface. Place in a greased bowl. Cover and let rise until doubled, about 1 hour. Punch down. On a lightly floured surface, roll dough out to a 1-inch thickness. Cut with a biscuit cutter. Brush rolls with melted butter; then coat with corn meal. Place on a greased cookie sheet. Cover and let rise until doubled. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Dough will also keep in the refrigerator for several days. Yields about 18 rolls.

title: penne pasta and mushrooms
directions: Melt butter in skillet. Add mushrooms, garlic, salt and pepper. Saut until tender. Add wine and cook 1 minute. Mix oil in with the pasta and coat well. Add mushrooms and mix well. Season with salt and pepper. Serve hot with lots of Parmesan cheese.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until tender and drain well.
Add all ingredients, except oleo.
Beat until fluffy.
Add oleo.
Spoon into greased casserole.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May be made several days ahead and kept in refrigerator.
Bake when ready to serve.

title: tuna loaf
directions: Combine tuna with soup.
Soak crumbs in milk and add to tuna mixture, pimento, parsley, seasoning and eggs.
Mix thoroughly. Place in greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt in large bowl of mixer; mix until well blended.
Add oil, then eggs, one at a time.
Then add nuts, carrots and vanilla; mixing well.
Grease a Bundt pan thoroughly.
Pour in mixture and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour or until cake springs back when touched lightly.
Cool in pan.
Remove and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Mix eggs, Parmesan cheese and butter.
Stir into spaghetti.
Pour all into baking dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Top with spaghetti sauce.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: italian tomato soup stew
directions: Brown sausages.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients (except pasta).
Cook over low heat for 30 minutes.
Add cooked pasta and serve.
Grated cheese may be added individually.
Makes approximately 10 servings.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl combine all ingredients.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole dish. Bake, covered, for 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: baked chicken
directions: Combine soups and water.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a glass 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: hot shrimp spread or souffle dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 1 or 1 1/2-quart baking dish or ovenproof bowl.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add oil and eggs.
Beat at low speed until well mixed.
Add apples and nuts; mix again.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot bacon dressing for spinach salad
directions: Wash, trim and dry fresh spinach. Saute bacon in a large skillet until crisp.
Drain on paper towel, crumble and reserve. Saute onion in bacon drippings until soft.

Stir in vinegars, salt, pepper and sugar. Blend cornstarch and 2 tablespoons of the broth in a small cup. Add remaining broth to skillet. Stir in cornstarch mixture. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Pour over spinach, tossing well. Sprinkle with bacon.

title: tuna cashew casserole
directions: In 1 1/2-quart greased casserole, combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup chow mein noodles.
Sprinkle reserved noodles over top.
Bake, uncovered, in gas range oven at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: pecan butter balls
directions: Mix; roll in balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly and roll in powdered sugar.
Enjoy.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, baking powder and salt in a large bowl.
Combine milk, eggs, pumpkin, butter and raisins. Stir this into the flour mixture.
Grease muffin tins (24).
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix dry jello, sugar and pineapple.
Heat to near boiling point and remove from stove.
Stir in cream cheese.
Add water, Cool Whip and chopped nuts.
Mix well and pour into large Pyrex dish.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Prepare chicken of your choice. Season with salt and pepper. Roll in flour, then dip into an egg beaten with 2 tablespoons water. Roll in Italian bread crumbs and fry in oil until golden brown. Remove and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: casserole of vegetables
directions: Cook carrots and onion in small amount of water until just tender, about 8 minutes.
Cook spinach as directed on package. Drain vegetables.
Make cheese sauce (like a white sauce).
Place 1/2 the spinach in ungreased 1-quart casserole dish.
Cover with 1/2 carrot and onions.
Top with 1/2 the cheese sauce.
Repeat the layers.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden.
Very colorful and good.

title: crab rolls(makes 60)
directions: Melt cheese and 1/2 of butter in top of a double boiler. Cool.
Add crabmeat, stirring until mixture is spreadable.
(The butter and cheese separate.)
Roll each slice of bread with a rolling pin to flatten.
Spread crab mixture on one side of bread and roll up.
Melt remaining butter.
Dip rolls into butter.
Roll in sesame seed.
Place seam side down in shallow baking pan. Cover pan and freeze.
To serve, thaw slightly.
Cut each roll into thirds.
Broil until golden brown, turning once.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Cube potatoes.
Cook until tender.
Boil, drain and cool. Combine all ingredients (1/2 of bacon).
Mix well.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining bacon.
Bake in oven, uncovered, until top turns light brown.
Bake at 350°. Serves 10 to 12.

title: classic tex-mex cornbread supreme
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 9-inch square pan.
In large bowl, combine corn meal mix, sour cream and milk; blend well.
Add all remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour batter into greased pan. Bake for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni until tender; drain.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients (except one 8 ounce block of medium Cheddar).
Add enough milk to be creamy.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining 8 ounces shredded cheese on top.
Bake until bubbly at 350°.

title: easy two egg cake
directions: Mix sugar, Karo, eggs and water in top of double boiler.
Mix well.
Place over boiling water, cooking and beating until done and forms stiff peak.
Remove from heat.
Add flavorings and mix well.
Frost your cake and top with coconut.

title: herbed pretzels or oyster crackers
directions: Mix together the oil, lemon pepper, garlic powder, dill weed and dressing mix.
Break the pretzels into small pieces and put them into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Top with the liquid mixture. Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, saute onion and minced garlic in chicken broth.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Add 14 ounces chicken broth and whole tomatoes with juice.
Add picante sauce and cumin, simmering, covered, until spaghetti is cooked and most of the liquid is absorbed.
Add chicken and spoon into casserole dish sprayed with nonfat spray.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until cheese is melted. Yield: 6 to 8 servings

title: sherry-soy marinade
directions: Mix liquid and seasoning together.
Marinate tenderloin in marinade overnight in shallow glass dish.
Turn occasionally. Bake at 350° with cover of foil for 45 minutes per pound.

title: all man beef sandwich
directions: Put oleo in cast-iron skillet on medium heat.
Place 2 all beef hot dogs into oleo and heat to golden brown.
Put hot dogs into warm bun with fresh onion and mustard.

title: fresh peach cake
directions: Cook until thick and cool the peaches, water, sugar and cornstarch.

title: chocolate chip squares
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Stir in flour and vanilla.
Press mixture evenly into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate morsels and pecans. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares. Yields 2 dozen.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks; mix thoroughly. Beat egg white with first mixture; add cinnamon, then milk.
Bake in pie crust at 350° until firm, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: middle east chickpea dip
directions: Drain chickpeas reserving liquid.
In a blender, combine all ingredients; blend until smooth.
Add about 1 tablespoon of the reserved liquid.
Blend until desired consistency.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups.

title: 1000 island dressing
directions: Chop eggs. Add remainder of ingredients. Chill. Stores very well.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done; stir often. Rinse in cold ice water. Add salad dressing, chopped onion, cucumber, carrot, sugar and salt; mix well. Keep in refrigerator.

title: ham-kraut balls
directions: Prepare Horseradish Sauce (recipe follows).
Mix remaining ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place balls on greased rack in broiler pan.
Bake in 375°
oven 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve hot.
Place sauce nearby.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Take cooked and drained hamburger and spread into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread onion over hamburger.
Layer soup over onion and hamburger.
Put Tater Tots over layers and pour milk over all. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: egg substitute(for cholesterol restricted diets)
directions: Combine ingredients in a blender; whirl.
This is the equivalent of 1 egg.

title: chicken and spinach tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti to desired doneness as directed on package. Meanwhile, in large saucepan, melt margarine over medium heat. Add onion and garlic.
Cook 2-3 minutes or until tender.
Stir in flour, salt, oregano, basil and pepper.
Cook until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Gradually add milk.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Add 1/2 c. cheese, chicken, spinach and carrot.
Cook 2-3 minutes or until spinach is tender, stirring constantly.
Drain spaghetti.
Serve chicken mixture over spaghetti.
Sprinkle with 1 Tbsp. cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: curry vegetable dip
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 6-8 hours.
Use with raw vegetables - celery, carrots, zucchini, turnips, cauliflower, broccoli.

title: almond bark snack
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Pour melted almond bark over it and mix.
Dip out by tablespoons onto wax paper and cool.

title: zucchini bread(makes 1 loaf)
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl until foamy.
Beat in sugar, zucchini, oil and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour batter into a greased and floured pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake about 1 hour in oven at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes in pan, then put on wire rack to finish cooling.

title: chicken in its own gravy
directions: Coat chicken pieces with 1/4 cup flour.
Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in hot oven (425°) for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken; bake 15 to 20 minutes longer, or until tender.
Drain off fat.
Reduce temperature to slow (325°). Combine cheese, soup, milk, water and pepper.
Stir in frozen onions and mushrooms and liquid; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with foil; continue baking 15 to 20 minutes.

title: three bean bake
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in bacon drippings in large skillet.
Add bacon, baked beans, lima beans, kidney beans, chili sauce, brown sugar, vinegar, dry mustard and pepper; mix well. Pour into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yield:
8 servings.

title: dee's moms pound cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.

title: cream of chicken
directions: To make white sauce, melt butter over low heat, cool, add milk gradually.
Put back on burner to cook until thick and add seasoning and chicken.
Serve on toast.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix hamburger, egg, salt, pepper, rice and tomato juice. Stuff in peppers and cover with tomato soup.
Bake at 350°.

title: cottage cheese fruit salad
directions: Mix together cottage cheese and Cool Whip; add orange jello (dry).
Add pineapple and mandarin oranges; mix.
Place in mold or bowl; chill overnight.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Serves 8.

title: fast and easy cobblers
directions: Melt 1 cube butter in cake pan. Pour dough (batter) on top of melted butter. Then add fruit and 1/2 cup sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Use any kind of fruit.

title: corn and rice stuffed tomatoes
directions: Slice tops off tomatoes; scoop out pulp and reserve.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and oregano into shells.
In a skillet, cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add mushrooms and saute.
Add corn, rice, tomato pulp, salt and pepper.
Heat.
Add 1/4 cup grated cheese and stuff shells.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup cheese.
Put 1/2-inch water in a rectangular baking dish; place tomatoes in water and bake 25 minutes in a preheated 375° oven.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add next 3 ingredients and mix until blended. Sift dry ingredients.
Add to first mixture and blend.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake in greased tube pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed snapper fillets
directions: Mix all ingredients together and mound on the flesh side of the snapper fillet. Place on greased sheet pan, skin side down. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until fillet is flaky and stuffing has browned.

title: bake-me-not peanut bars
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine all ingredients except sugar and water.
Blend well at low speed; set aside.
In 1 1/2 quart saucepan, cook sugar and water to hard-ball stage (250°) or until syrup forms hard ball when dropped into very cold water.
Pour slowly over butter-flour mixture.
Stir until thickened and well blended.
Pour into buttered 11 x 7-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1 tablespoon of sugar and 1/4 teaspoon of cinnamon.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Mix 1 tablespoon of sugar and 1/4 teaspoon of cinnamon; sprinkle over the batter.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: michelle's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger; drain and dump everything together.
Ready when warm and celery is soft.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cool and cut into bite-size pieces. Line 9 x 11-inch glass baking dish with chicken.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Pour margarine over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes (until bubbly).
Serves 6 to 8.

title: oyster stew
directions: Melt butter in skillet then add oysters.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Combine oysters with other ingredients in large saucepan.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, for 20 minutes. Reheat before serving.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a skillet; bring to a boil, then add green beans and turkey.
Stir all together and pour in a pie pan.
Put one layer of cranberry sauce over the top of pie; add shredded cheese.
Put a pie crust over the top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chili gumbo
directions: Boil 1-quart water with salt and pepper to taste. Add the chopped onion.
Cook onion 5 minutes.
Add macaroni and tomatoes. Cook 15 minutes, then add chili with chili powder and garlic salt. Cut cheese in cubes and add to mixture.
Cook slowly until dissolved.

title: goulash burgers
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion and cook until brown.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer over low heat for 30 minutes. Serve on warm buns.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place each chicken breast half on a sheet of waxed paper; flatten to 1/4-inch thickness using a meat mallet or rolling pin. Place one slice of ham and one slice of cheese in the center of each chicken piece.
Sprinkle evenly with parsley and pepper. Roll up lengthwise and secure with wooden pick.
Dip each chicken breast in egg; coat well with breadcrumbs.
Melt butter in a heavy skillet; brown chicken on all sides.
Remove chicken to a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, reserving drippings in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients to reserved drippings and stir well.
Pour sauce over chicken; bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: teriyaki steak
directions: Place seasoned round steak in baking dish.
Pour onions over steak.
Pour teriyaki sauce, sprinkling on pieces of meat as you pour.
Add water into baking dish, not on meat.
Place in oven at 350° for about 45 minutes, turning occasionally.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F.

Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Combine sour cream and baking soda in a small bowl; set aside. Using an electric mixer, cream margarine and sugar in a large bowl. Beat in eggs, bananas and sour cream mixture. Sift in flour, baking powder, and walnuts, combine well. Spoon mixture into prepared pan. Bake 1 hour, or until toothpick inserted into center of loaf comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes in pan. Turn loaf out on to rack and cool completely.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve as dip with fresh fruits.
Yields 2 to 3 cups.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and cover.
Let stand overnight. Add the remaining ingredients the next day.
Whip the cream and add to the mixture.

title: baked beans
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces.
Brown bacon.
Add garlic and onions.
Before bacon is crisp, add remaining ingredients (except for beans).
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add beans.
Bake, covered, in oven at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: pizza crust
directions: Butter a pie pan well and add the crumbs of 12 vanilla wafers. Press well into place.
Arrange whole vanilla wafers around outer edge.
Fill with favorite pudding or fruit filling.

title: make-ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes.
Mash with cream cheese, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Put into buttered casserole dish.
Top with pats of butter.
(Can be stored up to 2 days before baking.)
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening (softened).
Add beaten eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add buttermilk and flour alternately.
Beat well. Add vanilla.
Roll out and cut with a cookie cutter.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Mix together.
Sift all dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Add 1 cup chopped unpeeled apples and 1/4 cup chopped nuts.
Spray bread pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil at 245° sugar, Karo and water.
Add raw peanuts and cook to 290°.
Add butter and cook to 310°.
Add and stir salt, soda and vanilla.
Quickly pour out onto greased surface such as marble slab.
Pull to help thin out.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in large saucepan.
Over low heat, bring to a boil.
Boil for exactly 1 minute, no more or no less.
Remove from heat.
Add salt, vanilla and peanut butter; mix until peanut butter is well blended.
Add oats; mix well.
Put spoonfuls onto wax paper as soon as possible.

title: parmesan chicken(for microwave)
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Put margarine in small bowl. Microwave on High for 30 seconds.
In a separate bowl, mix together the bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Salt and pepper chicken and roll in melted margarine.
Then roll in bread crumb mixture.

title: honeyed cranberry pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet and season. Add wine and honey. Cover and cook 1 hour.
Add cranberries the last 15 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix well, chill and serve.
For best results use Silver Floss sauerkraut.

title: pound cake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well and drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly brown around the edges.
These are excellent with homemade ice cream. Yields 1 to 1 1/2 dozen.

title: hot potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Over the top, spread 2 cups crushed corn flakes.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Cook and stir cubed pork in frying pan with oil.
Drain meat. Saute onions and garlic.
Drain off oil.
Stir in pork, 3 cups water, paprika, bouillon, caraway seed, salt, pepper and marjoram. Heat until boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer with a cover for 1 hour.
Stir in sauerkraut; heat to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer with cover until pork is tender.

title: apple crisp
directions: Start oven to 375°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Pour apples into prepared dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
If tart apples are used, add a sprinkling of brown sugar.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add melted butter or oleo.
Mix until like coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over apples.
Bake 30 minutes or until apples are done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: Separate Oreos and crush in food processor.
(Try to scrape out some of the white filling so you are mainly processing the cookies.)
Divide cookie crumbs into three parts.

title: cherry supreme pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add milk and lemon juice; mix well.
Pour in crust and chill.
Before serving, spread pie filling on top.
Slice and serve.

title: seafood sauce
directions: Mix in small pot.
Heat until simmers.
Butter can be added for smoother taste.
Good with boiled shrimp.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: zucchini nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In medium mixing bowl, combine eggs, oil, vanilla and zucchini; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until moistened.
Use paper baking cups in muffin tin or grease muffin cups.
Fill cups 2/3 full.
Bake for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: cranberry swirl coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar with electric mixer.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg at medium speed.
Mix dry ingredients, sour cream and flavoring; mix well.
Grease an 8 or 9-inch tube pan.
Put a layer of batter on bottom of pan. Swirl some cranberry sauce over batter; sprinkle with a few nuts. Add remaining batter to cover cranberries and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until done.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes, then turn on a rack to cool.
Can substitute other fruits, including pineapple.

title: cole slaw
directions: Wash and chunk cabbage.
Place loosely in blender and cover with water.
Blend only a few seconds until motor of blender changes speed.
Drain and repeat with remaining cabbage until all is shredded.
Drain well.
Mix sugar, salad dressing and a dash of salt and pepper.
Mix well with cabbage.
Drained cabbage may be stored in plastic container, covered and refrigerated for later use.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put hash browns.
Heat soup, butter, sour cream and cheese on medium heat until butter and cheese melts.
Mix onions.
Pour over hash browns.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: honey nutters
directions: Combine peanut butter, honey and milk in bowl; stir until blended. Add graham cracker crumbs to peanut butter; mix with hands until well blended. Roll into balls and roll in coconut or wheat germ. Yield: 80.

title: basic layer cake
directions: Sift flour with
baking
powder and salt.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one
at
a
time, beating well after each addition.
Alternately add	small amounts of flour mixture and milk.
Blend well after
each addition.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 3 layer pans in 350°	oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Put together with desired icing.

title: dill sour cream dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill several hours. Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: buttermilk breakfast cake
directions: Make crumbs of flour, sugar, salt and shortening; take out 1/2 cup for topping.
Add baking powder, baking soda and buttermilk to remaining mixture.
Add milk to crumb mixture and beat.
Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) pans.
Fill pans evenly.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup crumbs on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tofu stroganoff
directions: Wrap tofu in several layers of cheesecloth or paper towels. Press lightly to remove excess moisture.
Remove cheesecloth.
Cut tofu into 1/2-inch cubes.
Set aside.
Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Add oil.
Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add tofu.
Saute 4 minutes.
Remove from skillet and set aside.

title: meal in a dish
directions: Place steak in a long casserole dish.
Season; dot with butter and add Worcestershire sauce.
In layers, add sliced potatoes, onion, carrots, bell pepper and mushrooms.
Cover casserole with foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Remove the foil and cook 10 to 15 minutes longer, or until browned.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 13 baking dish with Pam. Combine all ingredients and pour into baking dish. Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven. (Bell pepper, chopped onion, mushrooms or tomatoes may be added.
Also crumbled bacon may be substituted for the sausage.)

title: beef oriental stir-fry
directions: Cut sirloin across grain into strips.
Stir-fry vegetables one at a time in 2 tablespoons of oil in skillet over medium heat until tender.
Place each vegetable in second skillet.
When cooked, add ginger and pepper.
Stir in mixture of cornstarch and broth.
Cook until thick.
Add oil.
Stir-fry sirloin, seasoned with soy sauce.
Mix sirloin with vegetables.
Serve over rice. Serve with soy sauce.

title: princess bars
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix graham cracker crumbs and press down with a fork.
Sprinkle the remaining ingredients in order.
Bake for 22 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: quick corn light bread
directions: Put the buttermilk in a bowl.
Sift in the plain meal, sugar, flour, salt and soda.
Add melted shortening.
Pour in hot greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift flour, sugar and soda.
Add shortening; mix well. Dissolve the yeast in warm water.
Add buttermilk to yeast and add liquid to flour mix.
After mixing thoroughly, roll out and cut. Bake at 450° until golden brown.
May be stored up to 1 week in refrigerator.

title: tuna lasagne
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook lasagne for 10 to 11 minutes according to package directions.
In large skillet, saute onions in oleo; blend in cream cheese.
Remove from heat; stir in cottage cheese, egg, basil, salt and pepper.
Set aside.

title: centerpiece cake or dirt cake
directions: You will need an 8-inch plastic flowerpot, silk flowers to decorate, gummy worms to decorate (if desired) and a garden trowel to serve cake.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Place bread in bottom of a casserole dish; cover with sausage.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Pour over sausage; then top with cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: baked pudding
directions: Crumb Mixture:
Crumble graham crackers; mix with brown sugar and butter.

title: charles' lemon pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt once.
Add a little flour to mixture and, on low speed, mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately ending with flour (important).
Add flavorings.
Bake in tube or Bundt pan, greased and floured well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: grandma revel's chicken
directions: Soak dried mushrooms in warm water; squeeze dry and cut into pieces.
Cook tomatoes, garlic and mushrooms until reduced to a thick paste.
Cut up chicken; remove excess fat (or skin entirely) and pat dry.
In heavy saucepan, brown chicken pieces lightly and pour off oil.
Return chicken to pan.
Add tomatoes, chicken broth, parsley, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, cover and reduce heat to a simmer.
Cook approximately 1 hour.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat nutmeg, cinnamon, sugar, salt, eggs and oil together. Add the pumpkin, water, soda and flour.
Fill 3 (1 pound) coffee cans halfway.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, salt and pepper; drain.
After draining ground beef, add remaining ingredients with exception of cheeses.
In a baking pan spread tomato and hamburger mix in a layer in bottom.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, a layer of lasagna noodles, sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and repeat.
Be sure to save some sauce for the top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook at 350° until brown.

title: baked potato skins
directions: Bake potatoes for approximately 20 minutes (depending on size) in a 350° oven.
