Cut lengthwise and scoop our potato pulp, leaving approximately 1/4-inch.
Brush with vegetable oil; add salt and pepper.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 475° for about 10 minutes or until crisp.

title: mrs. ottie's pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs; add flour; add salt and extract; cook for 45 minutes at 325°.
Turn heat down to 300° and cook for 25 minutes in a greased stem pan.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain the beans.
Combine with the green pepper.
Combine the sugar, vinegar and salad oil. Mix and pour over vegetables.
Add the salt and pepper, if desired.
Toss and chill overnight.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Beat egg with vinegar in a measuring cup.
Add water to make 1
cup.
Blend
in
lard, salt, baking powder and flour. Roll
out dough
and line pie pans.
Makes enough for 2 fruit pies.

title: tasty pecans
directions: Mix thoroughly the cider vinegar and honey.
Pour 1 tablespoon of mixture over pecans and coat well.
Pour pecans in shallow pan and bake at 300° until liquid mixture is dry, approximately 10 minutes.
Add butter or margarine and stir until melted.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Continue baking for 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Cool and store in refrigerator to become crisp.

title: herbed croutons
directions: In large skillet, melt butter.
Stir in garlic, Tabasco, tarragon and mint.
Add bread crumbs; toss lightly to coat cubes on all sides.
Stir until lightly browned.
Store in airtight container for up to 1 week.
Yields 3 cups.
Use in soups and salads.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: In large frying pan, cook ground beef and onion.
Drain grease.
Mix in spaghetti sauce, tomato paste and spices.
Cook until blended, just a few minutes.
In a 9 x 12-inch baking pan, lay out 2 tortilla shells.
Top with 1/4 of the meat mixture.
Top that with 1/4 of the cheese.
Repeat 3 times more until all ingredients are used, ending with a layer of cheese.
Bake at 350° until warm through and cheese melts.
Then let set 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 8.

title: chili-cheese dip
directions: Heat all together and serve with nacho chips.

title: pecan diamonds
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch baking dish with foil and then butter the foil.

title: steamed plum chicken
directions: Combine sesame seed, cornstarch, soy sauce and plum jam; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Coat chicken pieces with sauce; place in aluminum foil.
Spoon remaining sauce over chicken.
Wrap and steam 30 minutes or until tender.
Serve with rice.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Sugar Twin or Equal can be used in place of powdered sugar.

title: brown bread
directions: Mix rye meal, Indian meal and salt.
Stir molasses into sweet milk.
Stir soda into sour milk and add to molasses mixture.
Stir milk mixtures into dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered brown bread mold; cover.
Set on wooden rack in kettle of hot water, having enough water to come partway up on mold, but not enough to float it.
Cover kettle; bring to boil gently and steam for 3 hours.
To serve, place brown bread on plate and slice with a piece of string.
Place string all the way around for desired thickness, cross ends and pull to slice.

title: glaze for fruit salad
directions: Take 1 cup pineapple juice (add juice from oranges enough to make one cup), mix with pudding; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and becomes somewhat clear. Add to fruit and refrigerate.

title: bread pudding
directions: Bake at 350°.
It is done when a thin knife stuck in comes out clean.
May add raisins, if desired.

title: cheese ball
directions: Put cheese in large bowl for about 10 minutes to soften, then pour Worcestershire sauce on cheese and add garlic salt.
Mix with hands.
Form a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans or parsley flakes.
Store in refrigerator.
This will keep about a week.

title: graham cracker goodies
directions: Place crackers on large cookie sheet; set aside.
Bring butter and sugar to a boil and cook for 2 minutes.
Add nuts; mix well. Pour over crackers.
Bake for 5 minutes at 400°.
Let cool.
Break apart and serve.

title: parmesan crab meat dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together crab meat, 1 cup of Parmesan cheese, onion, garlic, cream cheese and mayonnaise with salt and pepper to taste.
Place in greased casserole dish; top with remaining 1/3 cup of Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake until hot and bubbly (about 20 to 25 minutes).
Freezes well, both before and after baking.
Serve with crackers.

title: homemade sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and allow to cool.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Allow yeast to work for about 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir 2 cups of flour and yeast into oatmeal.
Allow to rise, uncovered, until it doubles in bulk.
Punch down and blend in oil, salt, molasses and remaining flour to make stiff dough.
Knead about 10 minutes.

title: catalina salad
directions: Mix together all except avocado and Fritos. Add these just before ready to serve.

title: no-bake cheesecake
directions: In a small bowl, stir together Knox and sugar. Add boiling water and stir until completely dissolved.
In a large bowl, beat cream cheese and vanilla until fluffy. Gradually beat in gelatine mixture until smooth.
Pour in graham cracker crust and refrigerate.
Top with any desired fruit (drained fruit). Refrigerate about 3 hours.

title: taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease baking dish.
Cook and stir beef and onion until brown; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Spread in pan.
Beat milk, eggs and Bisquick until smooth.
Pour over meat mixture and bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Layer mushrooms, olives and chilies.
Spread over crust.
Top with tomato slices and cheese. Bake 8 to 10 minutes more.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serve with sour cream and salsa if desired.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and flour.
Stir with fork until it reaches the crumb stage.
Add cheese.
Line a lightly greased casserole dish with the apples.
Put flour mixture over the apples.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato with pineapple
directions: Boil potatoes with skin on.
When cool, peel and cut into pieces 1 1/4 inches thick.
Mix honey with hot water.
Just cover the bottom of a baking dish with the mixture.
Add the sweet potatoes and sliced pineapple.
Pour the remaining honey mixture over them and bake for 10 minutes in 400° oven.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix milk, oleo, sugar, coconut and pecans in a bowl until well blended.
Shape into balls and place in refrigerator to harden. When balls are cold, melt the chocolate and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip each ball in the mixture and return to refrigerator. (You may find a toothpick works well for dipping.)
Suitable for freezing.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Boil zucchini until slightly tender; drain.
Cool.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Saute carrot and onion in 4 tablespoons of margarine.
Add to the zucchini.
Melt remaining margarine and mix with 1 1/2 cups of croutons.
Add to the zucchini mixture.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over mixture.
Top with remaining croutons.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spring salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in a large bowl.
Place in the fridge for at least 2 hours.
Serve chilled.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Melt shortening in a large saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat; let cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg; beat well. Sift dry ingredients; add to first mixture.
Mix well and chill. Form in 1-inch balls, then roll in granulated sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake!

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine first flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and allspice.
Combine pumpkin and milk until blended. Cream shortening and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add egg and beat until fluffy.
Add flour mixture alternately with pumpkin mixture.
Beat well after each addition.
Combine blueberries and flour.
Gently stir into batter.
Fill 18 paper lined
muffin pans 3/4 full.
Sprinkle Streusel over top of muffin. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: bea's favorite tuna casserole
directions: Layer all ingredients, starting and ending with macaroni. Cook in preheated 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Top with broken slices of cheese for 5 to 10 more minutes.
Let set out of oven for 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: nutty goodies (cookie)
directions: Line cookie sheet with crackers; boil margarine and sugar in small pan for 2 minutes.
Spoon this over crackers until all covered.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake for 7 to 8 minutes at 350° until bubbly.
Remove from pan when taken from oven.

title: creamy carrot casserole
directions: In a saucepan, cook carrots just until tender, but still crisp; drain, reserving 1/2 cup cooking liquid. Place carrots in two 1 1/2-quart or one 3-quart lightly greased baking dish.

title: simple peach cobbler
directions: Lay peaches and juice in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix on top. Dot with margarine and nuts on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Pour into a greased 2-quart shallow casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes supreme
directions: In greased 11 x 7 x1 1/2-inch baking dish or 2-quart casserole, alternate layers of potatoes, green pepper and onion. Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 20 to 30 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: deep dish taco squares
directions: Cook beef and drain.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, cheese and onion; reserve.
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms. Pat in pan, pressing dough 1/2-inch up sides.
Layer beef, tomatoes and green pepper in pan.
Spoon sour cream mixture over top.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Bake until edges of the dough are light brown.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in greased pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: ultimate chocolate cake
directions: Melt the chocolate; allow to cool.
Prepare 2 (9-inch) layer cake pans by lightly spraying with cooking spray.
Place a circle of waxed paper in the bottom of each pan and lightly spray again over the waxed paper.

title: crunchy peanut butter drops
directions: In a large saucepan over medium heat, cook and stir corn syrup and sugar for 7 to 8 minutes or until sugar is dissolved (do not boil). Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and mix well. Fold in cornflakes. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper coated with nonstick cooking spray. Let stand for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until set. Store in a waxed paper lined airtight container.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients and stir well.
Pour over cereal and stir until coated.
Pour sugar over cereal and shake in a Ziploc bag until coated.
Might have to add more powdered sugar.

title: country cornbread(for turkey dressing)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs and milk.
Put shortening in a 10-inch iron skillet and place in oven. When shortening is very hot, coat sides of skillet.
Stir remaining shortening into mixture.
Place in skillet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion and garlic in margarine until tender.
Stir in 1/4 cup olives, chilies, sour cream and soup.
Mix well.
Reserve 3/4 cup sauce; set aside.

title: pear bread
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar and eggs.
Combine all dry ingredients.
Mix into the creamed butter mixture.
Add yogurt; stir in pears and vanilla.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and salt.
Add eggs and bananas.
Mix soda in water and add to mixture.
Sift flour with baking powder and add vanilla and nuts.

title: spaghetti casserole(servings:  10)
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Add onion, garlic, celery, parsley and olive oil to meat and cook until onion and celery are soft.
Add tomatoes, puree and paprika.
Cook until well blended and thick and season with salt and pepper.
Add sliced green olives, if desired.
Boil linguini in salted water; drain.
In a casserole dish, mix noodles, spaghetti sauce and Parmesan cheese. Bake, covered, in 350° oven until warm, 30 minutes.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and press in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Blend together the cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 3 eggs. Pour on top of the first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Let cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice and mix with other ingredients.
Place in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: basic beef stew
directions: In a large Dutch oven, brown stew meat in oil. Add next 7 items and enough water to cover and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Add carrots and tomatoes. Simmer for 15 minutes. Add sliced celery and potatoes. Simmer until potatoes are tender. Thicken with cornstarch if desired. Remove bay leaves and serve.

title: zucchini stew
directions: Put all ingredients in a large 4-quart cooking pot. Cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Cut chicken in quarters and cook on grill over low fire for approximately 1 hour, basting chicken with salt water until it is done.
Mix mayonnaise, mustard, margarine and Worcestershire sauce.
Baste chicken and brown.

title: poncho's hot dip
directions: Put onion, tomatoes and pepper in blender for a few seconds just to chop pepper.
Put on stove and add seasonings.
Bring almost to a boil, being careful not to boil.
Add Wesson oil. Serve hot on tacos or cold with tortillas or corn chips.

title: fast cream of broccoli soup
directions: Mix all together and cook over low heat for about 45 minutes to 60 minutes until hot and flavor is blended.

title: caramel icing for black walnut cake
directions: Brown and make into caramel first by putting 1/4 cup sugar into iron skillet.
Heat until sugar browns, stirring constantly. Add 1/4 cup of water to make syrup. Add to other ingredients. Boil briskly for 4 minutes, stirring constantly and cooking to soft ball stage.
Cool in ice water, beating constantly.
Add vanilla and nuts. Spread between layers on sides and top of cake.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown beef and onion; pour off grease. Blend pizza sauce, garlic powder and oregano.
Put mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella.
In a small bowl, mix egg, milk, oil, salt and flour; pour over meat and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: tortellini a la veg-all
directions: Cook pasta according to directions, drain.
Melt butter in skillet.
Stir in onion, red pepper and garlic, cook until tender, about 2 minutes.
Add canned veggies and heat.
Add pasta and cheese.

title: grandma's casserole with a modern twist
directions: Microwave potatoes until almost done; meanwhile dice onion, green pepper, chop cabbage, slice sausage and dice tomatoes. Spray nonstick skillet, add 2 tablespoons of olive or salad oil, onion and green pepper.
Saute until onion is soft.
Dice potatoes.
Add to skillet.
Fry as for homefries, stirring to brown.
Add sausage, tomatoes, cabbage and wine. Season to taste with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Cook until cabbage is tender-crisp, stirring frequently.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will also need 1 new 8-inch flowerpot, completely clean and artificial flowers for decoration.

title: bacon cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and Ranch Style dressing.
Chill.
Form ball when hardened and roll in bacon chips.
Serve with crackers.

title: sesame cheese burst biscuits
directions: Half each biscuit and fill with 1 cube cheddar cheese.
Press seams back together.
Place each cheese filled biscuit in a well greased baking dish.
Drizzle with melted butter and sprinkle with sesame seeds.
Bake according to package directions.
Serve hot.

title: peach blueberry pie
directions: Combine sugars, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Spread blueberries on bottom of unbaked pie shell; sprinkle with half the sugar and flour mixture and half the lemon juice.
Top with sliced peaches; sprinkle with remaining sugar, flour and lemon juice.
Dot with butter.
Cover with lattice top; brush with milk and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes, until brown and bubbly.

title: chocolate pies
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and cocoa in a saucepan.
Add well beaten egg yolks and milk.
Cook and stir until mixture is thick. Add vanilla.
Pour in baked pie crusts.
Top with beaten egg whites and sugar.
Brown in oven.
Makes 2 pies.

title: hurry up dessert
directions: Use a 9 x 9 x 1-inch square pan.
Pour pie filling and spread on bottom. Sprinkle cake mix (raw) over the fruit.
Cover completely. Cover with nuts.
Place butter pieces on top. Do not mix, leave it layered. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60
minutes. Best served warm. Top with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: In saucepan, heat water and juice.
Add cornstarch mixture and bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove and let cool slightly.
Add strawberries.
Pour into Grape Nuts crust and chill for 2 hours.

title: ice cream pudding cake
directions: Mix butter and crushed cookies.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°, then cool about 10 minutes.
Mix together pudding, milk and ice cream and spread on crust.
Let stand in freezer overnight.

title: pasta fagioli
directions: Simmer onion and garlic in oil.
Add tomato puree or paste, parsley, fresh basil and celery leaves.
Cook 1/2 hour on low heat.
Cook toletti or tiny shells.
When done, drain into another pot.
Leave as much water as you like.
Add beans.
Add sauce.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix beans and dry taco mix together and spread over plate.
Mix avocado, lemon juice and sour cream together and spread over bean mixture on plate.
Sprinkle onions, olives and chilies over beans and avocado.
Sprinkle both cheeses and tomato over top.

title: split pea soup
directions: You will need a 5-quart pot.

title: hot slaw
directions: Slice cabbage as for slaw.
Cook with bacon fat, sugar, salt and pepper until tender in a little water. Sprinkle with the flour.
Add the cream and bring to a boil. Add a little vinegar to suit your taste. Good when served with corn oysters (fritters).

title: finger paints
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients over low heat.
Add the liquid soap and food coloring.
Use freezer wrap for painting.

title: spinach madelaine
directions: Mix mushroom soup with onions and spices.
Heat until onions are cooked.
Add grated cheese.
Drain spinach and mix with mushroom mixture.
Place in a casserole dish and cover with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Bake in the oven at 400° and bake until crackers brown and mixture bubbles.

title: ginger beef
directions: Cook beef until brown; drain.
Add gravy, ginger, salt and pepper to beef.
Simmer for 10 minutes or until meat is tender. Place into serving bowl.
Garnish with green onions on top.
Serve with white rice.

title: dr. bird cake
directions: Place all dry ingredients in bowl; mix well, then make a well in center.
Break in eggs; add oil, vanilla, bananas and last, add pineapple with juice.
Stir ingredients in a folding fashion; do not beat.
Just mix well.
Pour into greased tube pan; bake at 300° to 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix well and chill overnight.

title: bran flax muffins
directions: Mix first eight ingredients together.
Stir in the next four. Combine the last three ingredients and stir all together just until moistened.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15-20 minutes.
Makes 15 muffins.

title: scrumptious candy bar cookies
directions: In a heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan, melt the unwrapped caramels in 1/3 cup light cream, over low heat, stirring occasionally. When the caramels are melted, stir the mixture until smooth.
Set caramel cream mixture aside.

title: sweet-and-sour pork(frank's favorite)
directions: Trim all visible fat from pork loin and cut meat into thin strips.
Heat oil in a skillet and brown the meat strips.
Remove the meat and set aside.
Drain pineapple and combine pineapple juice with water, vinegar, brown sugar, cornstarch and soy sauce. Shake in a glass jar until well mixed.

title: barbecue sauce(good on pork or chicken)
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer 1 hour, stirring often.
This makes a thick sauce.

title: crisp baked chicken
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Roll chicken in butter, then in fine cracker crumbs.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Do not cover chicken with foil or lid and do not layer chicken.

title: easy spanish rice
directions: Brown hamburger. Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.

title: school day chowder
directions: In large saucepan, combine hot dogs, celery, carrots, green peppers, onion and butter.
Cook and stir over medium heat until vegetables are tender.
Stir in flour and pepper until blended. Gradually add milk.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Yield: 5 servings.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Place candy bar pieces in medium microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on High 1 minute or until chocolate is smooth when stirred. Cool slightly. Fold Cool Whip whipped topping into melted chocolate; spoon into crust. Cover; refrigerate 6 hours or until firm.

title: cereal cookies
directions: Mix together well.
Bake at 350° for 10-15 minutes.

title: chicken stew
directions: Cook chicken and remove bones.
Save broth.
Cook slow when all is mixed together.
Mix 2 tablespoons flour in 1 cup water. Add to stew to thicken.
(Use about 2 cups broth.
Add more if necessary.)

title: homemade summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Form into 2 rolls and wrap in foil. Refrigerate 24 hours. With a fork, poke holes in foil on bottom of each roll. Place rolls on rack over pan to catch any liquid that drips during baking. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cookie factory chocolate chip cookies
directions: Bake on ungreased cookie sheets.
Make golf ball size cookies and place 2 inches apart on sheets.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes. Makes 10 dozen cookies.

title: more casserole
directions: Brown meat until crumbly; add onion, peppers and celery. Simmer for several minutes.
Add cooked noodles, tomato sauce, corn, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Spoon into baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: foolproof baking powder biscuits
directions: In a bowl, mix the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Stir in milk; knead lightly.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface.
With hands, pat to 1/2-inch thick rectangle or roll with lightly floured rolling pin.
Cut into 16 squares.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes, or until browned.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of 8-inch glass pie plate, followed by chili and then grated cheese on top.
Heat at 350° for approximately 15 minutes.
If you prefer, you may put in microwave and leave in just until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine egg yolks, lime juice and milk.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust and add meringue.
Bake until meringue is brown.

title: olive rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a casserole dish.
Place in 350° oven and bake, covered, about 1 1/4 hours or until "done." One may want to stir after 30 minutes and 1 hour.

title: sunflower white cake(one bowl)
directions: Stir flour, sugar and shortening and beat vigorously 200 strokes or 2 minutes in mixer, scraping bowl frequently.
Add unbeaten egg whites and continue beating 2 more minutes, scraping bowl frequently.
Batter will be thin.
Bake in two 8-inch greased and floured pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: russian beets
directions: Mix all ingredients, except beets.
Mix the sauce well and add it to the beets.
Heat the beets with sauce slowly, stirring to coat.
Makes 6 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cream the butter and flour.
Add the milk and bean liquid. Warm, then add the Velveeta cheese, chopped up; melt this.
Pour over the green beans in a greased casserole.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: mocha pound cake
directions: Mix shortening, flour, sugar, instant coffee, salt, cream of tartar and soda.
Add water and vanilla.
Mix until flour is moistened.
Then beat vigorously 2 minutes.
Add eggs and melted chocolate.
Beat 1 minute longer.
Pour into paper lined 9 1/2
x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 65 to 70 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then remove.
Cool completely, then add confectioners sugar over top.

title: pumpkin surprise
directions: Mix first five ingredients well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread dry cake mix over pumpkin mix.
Melt butter and pour over cake mix.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oreo death
directions: Crush Oreos and place in bottom of a 9
1/2 x 11-inch pan. Melt chocolate and butter over low heat, stirring often.
Spread softened ice cream over Oreos.
Pour chocolate mixture over ice cream.
Spread Cool Whip over ice cream.
Add chocolate chips as desired.
Store in freezer.

title: pumpkin delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle a yellow cake mix over the top.
Melt 1 cup butter and pour over the cake mix.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix the squash, onions and salt; let stand overnight.
Drain well.
Add the peppers, mustard seed, celery seed, turmeric, sugar and vinegar.
Boil until clear, about 1/2 hour.
Seal in hot sterile jars.

title: turnip green soup
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Good served with fried corn bread patties.

title: chicken salad
directions: Remove chicken from broth.
Skin and chop chicken fine.
Add celery, sweet pickles, pecans, hard-boiled eggs, mayonnaise and curry powder depending upon amount of salad.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: spicy corn bread
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder, salt and red pepper. Beat together eggs, milk and oil. Add to flour mixture and stir just until batter is smooth. Stir in corn, pimiento and cheese. Pour batter into a greased 10-inch cast-iron skillet or a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake in a 425° oven 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 8 or 9 servings.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in dish.
Set dish in water and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: *Pierce potatoes in several places.
Place on baking sheet. Put in oven and bake 1 1/2 hours until potatoes are tender.

title: congealed coca cola cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve orange gelatin in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce and mix well.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour mixture into mold that has been sprayed with Pam.
Chill.
When mixture begins to thicken, stir to distribute nuts evenly.
Chill until firm. Serves 8.

title: meat loaf in a mug
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put into microwave-safe mug or custard cup.
Make several small holes in center, all the way to the bottom.
Microwave for 3 minutes on High or until done. Drain any fat.
Let stand 3 minutes.

title: spanish tuna
directions: Combine Spanish rice and tuna in a saucepan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Heat until piping hot.
Stir often.
Serves 4. If you need more, add either another can of tuna or another can of Spanish rice.

title: frozen watermelon virgin margaritas
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender and puree until smooth. Divide among 4 glasses. Garnish with lime wedges. Serves 4. 1 point per serving.

title: countryside chicken bake
directions: Place rice in
greased
12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cover with combined
vegetables and
seasonings.
Combine
soup
and salad dressing; mix well. Gradually add water to soup mixture; mixing well.
Pour half the soup mixture over vegetables.
Top with chicken and
remaining
soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender and rice is cooked.

title: cinnamon jello delight
directions: Mix together jello, liquid, candies and sugar.
Heat until dissolved.
Add cold water and let partially set.
Add pineapple, apple and celery; let set completely.
Spread with mixture of cream cheese, powdered sugar, nuts and Miracle Whip or mayonnaise.

title: morning glory muffins(yield: 25 muffins)
directions: 1. Into large bowl sift together the flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add vanilla and egg. Beat until fluffy.
Add carrots (cool).
Mix flour, salt and baking powder together and sift.
Add to creamy mixture.
Add raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet, 2 to 3-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: arabian cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; beat in eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour milk.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Lightly grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread stuffing on bottom.
Pepper breasts, wrap a slice of cheese around each breast and lay chicken in pan.
Dilute soup and spoon around the chicken. Sprinkle additional crumbs over the top.
Bake 1 hour at 325° to 350°.

title: the best lasagna
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven cook meat and onion until browned well. Drain if necessary and add tomatoes, paste and spices.
Heat to boiling, stirring to break up tomatoes.
Reduce heat to simmer; cover and cook 2 hours until thick, stirring occasionally. Discard bay leaves.
Skim off any fat.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Mix margarine, flour and nuts.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: chocolate chip cream cheese cookies
directions: Line 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan with foil.
Slice cookie dough and press in pan, covering complete bottom.
Bake according to package directions.
Blend next four items until smooth.
Remove "cookie" from oven and let cool slightly.
Pour liquid on top of "cookie".
Sprinkle with cinnamon if desired.
Bake until set. Remove from oven.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add the oleo and cut in until the consistency of corn meal.
Pour milk into the mixture slowly and add the egg.
Stir to stiffen dough.
Knead 5 times.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into biscuits and bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Brush each with melted butter before baking.
The dough can also be rolled thin, covered with sugar, cinnamon, raisins and butter.
Roll up and slice into rolls.

title: vic's favorite salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Salsa gets much hotter the longer it sets so be careful with amount of jalapeno juice added.
Keeps well, refrigerated in an airtight container.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream(serves 4)
directions: Arrange chicken in shallow pan; cover with mushrooms.
Stir other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Dust with paprika. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Boil sweet potatoes. Skin and mash with butter, sugars and salt. Add juice and rind of lemon. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each. Add vanilla, half and half, and orange juice.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Combine sugar, cream of tartar and cinnamon with 1/4 cup water in saucepan.
Cook to soft ball stage or 238° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and pecans. Continue stirring until pecans are coated.
Pour onto waxed paper; separate pecans with fork while still warm.

title: sensational shrimp dip(preparation time:  5 minutes)
directions: Mix together ingredients until well blended; chill.
Serve with chips and vegetable dippers.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Cook cake, using directions on box.
Bring pineapple and sugar to boil.
Poke holes in cake and pour pineapple over cake.
Cool cake and follow with pudding mix.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: oriental rice
directions: Cook approximately 2 cups rice.
Put in casserole dish.
Add mushrooms, pimentos, green peas and onions.
Put in oven long enough for vegetables to warm only, not cook.

title: chicken and tomatoes
directions: Cut
chicken
in 1-inch pieces.
Dredge it with mixture of 1 tablespoon soy sauce, sherry and 1 tablespoon cornstarch. Heat pan.
Add
oil.
Saute
dredged chicken until tender. Add onions and
fry
a
few
seconds.
Drain
chicken
and
onion. Preheat pan
and add 2 tablespoons of the drained oil, remaining
1 tablespoon cornstarch, remaining 1 1/2 tablespoons soy sauce, salt, sugar and soup stock.
Boil a few seconds. To the boiling sauce,
add chicken, onions and tomatoes.
Heat thoroughly and serve
hot.
May be made in advance to the point of adding the chicken, onions and tomatoes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in pot.
Place on stove.
Add milk and stir constantly until it starts to boil.
Pour into baked pie shell and allow to cool for about 1 hour.
Top with whipped topping and garnish with strawberries.

title: chocolate peanut buddy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, beat butter and peanut butter until smooth.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Gradually beat in flour and salt.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips.
Spread into ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes until edge is brown.
Immediately sprinkle the rest of chocolate chips over cookie layer.
Let stand 5 minutes until chocolate chips are shiny and soft.
Spread chocolate chips evenly over top.
Cool.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch bars.
Yields 48 bars.

title: western chili casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet, add onions and celery; cook until tender.
Remove excess fat from skillet.
Add beans, salt and chili powder.
Place layer of chips in bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Alternate layers of chips, cheese and meat mix. Reserve 1/2 cup chips and 1/4 cup cheese for garnish.
Sprinkle center with reserved cheese.
Place chips around edge.
Top with olives.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: mainland-style laulau
directions: Cut pork into bite size pieces or strips and lay in baking pan (13 x 8 x 2-inch).
Salt with Hawaiian salt.
Drain juice from spinach and reserve.
Place spinach over pork, being sure to cover all pieces.
Bake, uncovered, for 2 hours at 275° to 300°. Do not stir or mix during cooking time; however, it may be necessary to baste with spinach juice.
Yields 3 or 4 servings.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Pour in graham cracker crust.
Cook for 8 minutes in 375° oven.
Let cool.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, sugar, oil, eggs, undrained pineapple and vanilla.
Mix only by hand.
Add bananas and nuts and mix again.
Bake in tube or Bundt pan that has been greased and floured, in 350° oven 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Let stand 1 hour before removing to serving plate.
May be iced with powdered sugar icing.
This moist cake improves with age.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order given, adding one ingredient at a time.
Mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 24 dozen.

title: chili(serves 1)
directions: Brown ground round and green onions.
Dissolve tomato soup in water; add to mixture along with chili powder and bean sprouts. Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Bake at 375° for 35 or 40 minutes or until done.

title: bonbon temptation pie
directions: Cover bottom of 9-inch chocolate cookie crust with bonbons. Mix pudding with milk.
Fold in whipped topping, food coloring and peppermint extract.
Spoon over bonbons and freeze 5 hours. Decorate with melted chocolate, whipped topping and more bonbons. Enjoy!

title: cornbread
directions: Beat together oil and egg in bowl until blended. Add cornmeal and buttermilk. Stir. Batter will be thin. Pour into greased hot pan. Bake at 400 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Choose any combination of fruits.
Mix your choice of fruit and nuts, draining all juices.
Add the dry pudding mixture and mix thoroughly.

title: fatoosh(toasted bread salad)
directions: Toast bread and break into small pieces.
Sprinkle with water to moisten the toast somewhat and mix.
Crush garlic with salt in large bowl.
Put bread on top of mashed garlic.
Cut cucumbers in small chunks, peppers, tomatoes and lettuce in small pieces.
Mince parsley with stems and scallions.
Put all these vegetables over the bread.
Add mint, lemon juice, olive oil and salt to taste. Mix well with hands.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Mix
lemon
Jell-O
(small) and 2 cups hot tomato juice; after Jell-O is
dissolved add remaining ingredients.
Cool to soupy stage
and
add
celery, olives, green pepper and onion. Mix together and mold.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Crush crackers and place in mixing bowl. Pour melted margarine over crackers.
Place 1/2 cracker mixture in a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Reserve other 1/2 for top.
Boil chicken. Save cup broth.
Remove chicken from bone.
Set aside.
Mix 1 cup broth, both cans of soup and sour cream.
Add chicken and stir. Pour chicken mixture over crumbs.
If using cheese, sprinkle over chicken mixture.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: sugared peanuts
directions: In iron skillet on stove top add all ingredients.
Stir over medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes until peanuts become sticky.
Be careful not to burn the sugar.
Too high heat will burn them. Continue to stir until nuts become coated with crusty shell. Remove immediately to cookie sheet and roast in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Enjoy!

title: asparagus mushroom casserole
directions: Place asparagus in glass loaf dish.
Place sliced eggs in layer over asparagus.
Sprinkle chopped pimiento on top.
Pour soup over mixture and top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: gelatin ribbon loaf
directions: Place lime and raspberry flavor gelatin in separate bowls; add 3/4 cup applesauce to each flavor and stir until thoroughly blended.
Place 2 double crackers, end to end, on a platter; spread with 1/4 cup lime gelatin mixture.
Top with a layer of crackers and spread with 1/4 cup raspberry gelatin mixture. Repeat layers, ending with crackers.
Prepare whipped topping mix as directed on package, omitting the vanilla and adding confectioners sugar and almond extract before beating.
Spread over top and sides of loaf.
Chill at least 30 minutes.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: mexican potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in salt water until tender.
Cut Velveeta cheese into cubes; combine with Ro-Tel tomatoes in top of double boiler. Melt cheese over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Brown meat over medium heat; season to taste.
Combine all ingredients and serve.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, margarine, and milk to a boil, boiling hard for 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and Marshmallow Cream.
Beat until candy begins to harden.
Pour into a buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender to make paste-like substance.
Add 2 (12-ounce) cans of shrimp or use fresh shrimp. Blend well.
Chill overnight or for several days.
Serve with crackers or on toast.

title: marmalade beets
directions: Melt marmalade, lemon juice, butter and beet liquid in saucepan over low heat.
Add seasonings.
Blend.
Add beets, cover and simmer 5 minutes.

title: fruit muffin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat eggs, oil and milk together. Add flour, sugar and baking powder. Fold in your favorite fruit.
Pour into greased muffin tins. Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: caramelized onions
directions: Put all in frying pan and saute 30 minutes.

title: mckinley pie
directions: Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake slowly at 350° until firm.

title: rabbit smothered in onions
directions: Season rabbit with salt and paprika.
Coat with flour and saute in butter until brown.
Cover rabbit thickly with onion slices and sprinkle with salt.
Pour in sour cream.
Cover skillet and simmer for 1 hour or bake at 325° until tender.

title: italian beef
directions: Dip beef into egg, then into crumbs, cheese and seasoning mixture.
Fry in 1/2-inch olive oil for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will also need 6-inch flower pot, 1 spade and 1 bunch artificial flowers.

title: almond chocolate pretzels
directions: Melt almond bark or chocolate in microwave on Defrost or 1/2 power or in a double boiler.
Dip pretzels by fork and place on wax paper.
May decorate with colored sugar, silver balls, etc. or drizzle on melted caramels, nuts, etc.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat eggs well until frothy. Add all ingredients in order given. Mix well. Bake in buttered 2-quart casserole for 1 hour at 350°.

title: kahlua
directions: Boil water (1 1/2 cups) and sugar 2 to 3 minutes; add vanilla. Combine coffee with 1/2 cup water and add to mixture.
Pour into 1/2 gallon jug or bottle; add vodka and glycerine.
Stir gently; cap and let stand 3 days before using.

title: grilled sesame chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken to make marinade.
Place chicken in Ziploc bag with marinade for 4 to 8 hours.
Turn chicken to coat evenly several times.
Keep in refrigerator.
Cook on grill 15 to 20 minutes.

title: "gack"(gooey, stretchy, fun stuff!)
directions: Mix glue with food coloring.
Use as much glue as "gack" you want; set aside.
In another container, mix water and Borax until Borax is dissolved.
Add some water/Borax mixture to glue (about 1/4 cup to start).
Mix as well as possible and pour off excess water.
Keep adding water/Borax mixture to glue mixture until "gack" is desired consistency.
Store in airtight container.
Not for human consumption.

title: low-fat apple crisp
directions: *Select margarine that has no more than 2 grams of saturated fat per tablespoon.

title: good for you muffins
directions: Mix all cereal in large bowl.
Pour on boiling water and stir to moisten.
Add oil and 1/2 of buttermilk.
Stir until smooth. Add eggs and sugar; stir.
Add 1/2 of flour, salt and soda.
Stir again.
Add other 1/2 of buttermilk and flour.
Add dates, nuts or whatever (chopped).
My recipe says bake 20 minutes at 400°; I have better luck baking 19 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Makes about 24 muffins.

title: squash relish
directions: Grind all vegetables together and cover with ice water with 1/2 cup salt added.
Let this stand 1 hour.
Drain, then rinse well, then drain and set aside.

title: magic biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into 6 greased muffin tins.
Bake in a 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: roy and joe's shrimp fried rice
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Boil shrimp in a large pan until pink.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
After removing from heat, add 1/2 tablespoon of Tabasco sauce and lemon (shred).
Let shrimp cool, then peel.

title: jello salad
directions: Bring the applesauce to a boil.
Do not boil!
Sprinkle the jello.
Stir until dissolved. Add the ginger ale.
Pour in mold and refrigerate.
May add the pineapple, if desired.

title: chiffon pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water, mandarin syrup and mandarin peel.
Chill until thickened but not completely set.
Line bottom of pie shell with well drained mandarin sections, reserving 3 sections for top of pie.
Blend Jell-O mixture and 3 cups of whipped topping and spoon into pie shell. Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping, fresh mint and mandarin sections.
Serves 8.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time (important).
Beat with mixer until fluffy. Add flour gradually until blended.
Add vanilla.
Pour into well-greased 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan. Section squares with knife. Spoon cherry filling into center of each square.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar when completely cool.

title: midget cheese cakes
directions: Place 1 vanilla wafer in each midget foil cupcake liner.
Fill each to top with cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Top with cherry or blueberry pie filling. Makes 32 cakes.

title: party punch
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan.
Cook until syrupy.
Add Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Add lemon and pineapple juice plus 1 gallon of water and almond extract.
Pour over ice; add ginger ale.

title: tuna salad
directions: Place all ingredients together and mix well.
Place on bread for a sandwich.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In saucepan, heat spaghetti sauce and water.
Combine Ricotta, Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Pour 3/4 cup sauce in baking dish; arrange 3 lasagne noodles on sauce (pasta will expand while cooking).
Pour 1/2 cup sauce over pasta; spread with half cheese mixture.
Cover with 1/2 cup sauce.
Repeat layers.
Top with pasta and remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan.
Cover with foil and bake 60 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: firecracker brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan.
In bowl, stir together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; with spoon, beat well.
Stir together flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt. Gradually add to egg mixture, beating until well blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread batter evenly into prepared pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool completely in pan or wire rack.
Cut into bars.
Makes about 16 brownies.

title: honey bun cake
directions: *Buttermilk:
One cup sweet milk mixed with 1 teaspoon vinegar or lemon juice added to it; let stand 5 minutes.

title: confetti custard
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and almonds.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
During last 5 minutes, sprinkle with almonds and continue to bake.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Add margarine.
Combine raisins, nuts and coconut.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in vinegar.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
Garnish with whipped cream.
Yields 8 servings.

title: buffet potatoes
directions: Blend together both cans of soup, the French onion dip and the evaporated milk with mixer. By hand, mix in thawed hash browns thoroughly. Put in 9 x 12-inch baking pan. Top with shredded Cheddar. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy casserole
directions: Brown hamburger or sausage with onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Drain.
Cook noodles.
Drain.
Mix soup with water until creamy.
Layer in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan:
hamburger or sausage, noodles and soup.
Top with cheese slices.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Heat milk to almost a boil. Let cool down some.
Add oil and lukewarm milk to dry mixture to make dough.
Put in a warm place and let it rise double.
Sift softly; spread on a floured wax paper to about 1-inch thick and sprinkle with melted butter and cinnamon sugar mixture.
Roll into a long roll and cut into 1/2 to 3/4-inch pieces.
Place in pan and let rise again in warm place.
Top with melted butter (and more cinnamon-sugar mix, if desired) and bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: make ahead canapes
directions: In medium bowl, stir together soup, cheese and ham, garlic and parsley, until mixed well.
Spread mixture on bread and place on baking sheets.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Freeze until firm.
Wrap in foil or place frozen canapes in freezer bags for longer storage.
Return to freezer.
Remove from freezer; preheat oven to 375°.
Cut bread into small squares.
Bake frozen canapes 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 80.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Mix together chicken, mayonnaise, onion and celery.
Set aside. Also, mix together 2 eggs, broth, butter and cornbread stuffing.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix and bake at 425° for 30 minutes or 20 minutes for muffins.

title: fudge
directions: Stir and boil for 10 minutes.
Add 1 jar marshmallow cream and 3 small packages of chocolate chips.
Stir until dissolved.
Add 2 cups pecans.
Pour into buttered 9 x 20-inch pan.
Refrigerate for 8 to 14 hours before cutting.

title: potato rolls
directions: Combine potatoes, shortening, sugar, salt and hot milk.
Cool until lukewarm.
Add egg and yeast.
Stir in flour.
Beat well. Knead on slightly floured surface until smooth and elastic.
Place in lightly greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.
Cover and let rise until double (about 1 hour).
Punch down and let rise 10 minutes.
Roll and cut into shape.
Place on greased baking sheet. Cover and let rise until almost double (about 1 hour). Bake in hot oven at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes. Brush tops with butter.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Fry hamburger and bacon in butter.
Layer as follows: cooked spaghetti, hamburger and onions, green pepper, tomatoes without the juice, corn, remainder of the spaghetti and meat, juice of the tomatoes and olives and cheese.
Cover and bake 1 hour or more at 350° and serve with hot biscuits.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Boil vinegar, water and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Set aside and let cool.
Fry bacon and crumble.
Pour off most of bacon grease, saving enough to brown onion.
Let cool.
Mix onion, bacon and mayonnaise with vinegar liquid.
Refrigerate overnight.
Heat on low to warm before serving.
Great on fresh spinach salad!

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine sour cream, soup, broth and green chiles.
Heat and stir until smooth and well blended.
To soften tortillas, heat a small amount of reserved chicken broth in a skillet.
Place tortillas, 1 at a time, in broth for a few seconds.
Remove and drain.
After draining, place tortillas, 1 at a time, directly into soup mixture.
Lift tortillas out of the soup mixture.
Place 3 tablespoons chicken and 2 to 3 tablespoons of each cheese in the center of each tortilla.
Roll up and place, seam side down in a 2-quart baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over tortillas. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Layer in the order written, in a greased 9 x 13 inch pan, pouring the Eagle Brand milk over all of it.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: three cheese and sausage casserole
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes as directed on package except decrease water to 1 3/4 cups; stir in sour cream and Cheddar cheese.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease square 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spread 1/2 of potato mixture in pan.
Arrange sausage on top.
Spread with remaining potato mixture; sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake uncovered until light brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chili
directions: Fry onions in
tablespoons
shortening until tender. Add meat and cook until it separates.
Add water and cook over low heat.
Pour boiling water over chili peppers and let stand until skin can be
peeled
off.
Add
other ingredients except flour. Let cook about 1
hour.
Then
add flour (mixed with a little water) to thicken.	More
water
may be needed.
Cooked pinto beans may be added if desired.

title: blueberry bonanza
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: patate alla salsiccia(potatoes with spicy italian sausage)
directions: Remove skin from sausage and break up the meat.
Heat the oil in a large cast-iron skillet.
Add the meat, onion and potatoes and cook, covered, over low heat for 30 minutes.
Uncover, increase the heat and saute the potatoes until brown, stirring. Season with salt and pepper and serve.
Serves 6.

title: mexican salad
directions: Toss and put Fritos and dressing on just before serving. (Ground meat can be browned, drained and added to this; however, its already a complete meal by itself.)

title: m&m cookies
directions: Combine shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla, then add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add 1/2 cup M&M's.
Use the rest on top of cookies.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Blend all dry ingredients in double boiler.
Slowly stir in milk and well beaten egg yolks.
Cook and stir over boiling water until mixture thickens.
Cool.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue; return to oven to lightly brown.
When cool, you can garnish with chocolate sprinkles or shaved chocolate.

title: bernice's scratch cake
directions: Cream shortening and butter together.
Add sugar gradually. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour with salt and baking powder; add to mixture in thirds alternating with milk.
Add flavorings.
Pour into cake pan and bake at 325° until done.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix first 4 ingredients; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat eggs, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add mayonnaise and flour mixture alternately with water.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain well.
Combine soups and onion in 2-quart casserole or 10-inch square casserole. Add cooked broccoli to the soup mixture and mix well.
Melt butter or margarine and mix well with stuffing mix.
Sprinkle stuffing mix evenly over top of broccoli mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes (30 minutes covered, last 15 minutes, uncovered).
Serves 8.

title: squash ball
directions: Mix squash, egg, flour, baking powder, salt and pepper.
Form into small balls and roll in bread crumbs.
Fry in deep fat until golden.
Serve hot.

title: sausage breakfast bake
directions: Combine pancake mix, milk, eggs and salad oil.
Beat until nearly smooth with rotary beater.
Turn into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Drain apple rings, reserving syrup.
Halve each sausage link.
Arrange rings and sausages so can be cut into squares when baked.
Bake at 350° until done (about 30 minutes).
Cut into 6 squares.
Serve with spiced apple-maple syrup.

title: old fashion peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all 3 ingredients until well mixed.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls; mash flat with fork.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 7 to 9 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet.
Remove; keep tightly covered.

title: hot deviled potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water for about 20 minutes. Drain well and mash.
Combine potatoes and remaining ingredients except paprika, mixing well.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 1-quart casserole; sprinkle with paprika and cover and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: piccalilli relish
directions: Grind all vegetables and cover with salt.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Next morning, rinse thoroughly and drain well three times using a fine mesh strainer.
In a large kettle, put the vinegar and sugar on to boil.
Add the spices and vegetables. Cook 15 minutes.
Put in pint jars which have been sterilized. Seal and store in dark place.
Makes 8 pints.

title: teriyaki chicken wings
directions: Combine soy sauce, water, garlic powder, mustard and brown sugar.
Place chicken wings in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish. Pour over marinade.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Bake in marinade in 350° oven for 1 hour, basting every 15 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place hash brown potatoes in casserole dish.
Brown onion in 1/2 margarine.
Add to top of potatoes.
Top this with sour cream, milk, soup and cheese.
Mix corn flakes with remaining half of margarine for topping.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: ham and red eye gravy
directions: Put shortening in skillet.
Add ham and cover with lid until brown.
Remove ham.
Add water to skillet and let boil.
Add coffee.
Let simmer for 3 to 5 minutes.
Put ham back in.
Serve with hot biscuits.

title: cornmeal muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add well beaten eggs, then flour, and salt sifted together and mix with cornmeal. Add milk gradually. Stir well. Bake in well greased muffin pans in hot oven (450 degrees) about 25 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, mayonnaise, Cheez Whiz and bacon bits in bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon into glass dish.
Microwave on High for 20 minutes, turning dish 4 times.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: fabulous cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 9-inch spring-form pan.
At high speed, beat cream cheese with cottage cheese until creamy. Gradually beat in sugar, then add eggs until well combined.
At low speed, beat in cornstarch, flour, lemon juice and vanilla.
Add butter and sour cream until smooth.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until firm around edges.
Turn off oven and let cake stand 2 hours in oven.
Remove cake and let cool.
Refrigerate for several hours, then add pie filling.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix 1/4 pound of melted margarine and graham cracker crumbs. Press into 9 x 12 baking dish. Refrigerate for 1/2 hour. Beat until fluffy 1/4 pound margarine, eggs, confectioners sugar and vanilla. Spread evenly over crust. Slice bananas and lay on filling. Spread pineapple over bananas; spread Cool Whip over entire dish. Decorate with maraschino cherries. Sprinkle top with chopped nuts. Keep refrigerated until served.

title: ham and mandarin salad
directions: Rub salad bowl with cut cloves of garlic.
Combine ham, celery, onion, walnuts and orange slices in the bowl.
Cover and chill.
Just before serving, mix the pepper, mayonnaise, cream and vinegar.
Pour over the ham mixture.
Toss until well coated. Garnish with lettuce, watercress or chopped mint.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli and put
in
a single layer in bottom of a flat casserole.
Melt
together
1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, milk, cream cheese and garlic
salt
in a double boiler.
Whip with whisk.
Pour one half the cheese sauce over the broccoli. Break the cooked chicken into
fairly
large
pieces and put a thick layer on top of
the broccoli.
Add the remainder of the sauce to the chicken.
Sprinkle the remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and the crushed corn
flakes over the top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: irish bread
directions: Soak raisins in water until plump.
Mix everything together. Heat oven at 350°.
Separate mixture into two pieces and place on pie plates lined with aluminum foil.
Bake about 1 hour and 30 minutes or until well done in center.
You can add some green food coloring to mixture before baking if you would like green Irish bread.
Makes 2 loaves of bread.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: Combine filling ingredients with a fork; stir in pecans. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
If using a frozen deep-dish pie shell, preheat oven to 350° and heat cookie sheet.
Enjoy!
Serves 8.

title: foil packs
directions: Use 4 to 5 pieces of aluminum foil.
In each piece put 1 hamburger patty, potato slices, carrot slices and 1 slice onion. Salt and pepper to taste and a pat of margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
This will make 4 or 5.

title: ma tish's munchies
directions: Melt almond bark.
Put other ingredients in large bowl. Pour melted almond bark
over
mixture
and stir.
Pour coated mixture onto wax paper and spread out to cool.
Break apart as cooling.

title: hot cha cha cheese
directions: Knead together cheeses and nuts until well mixed.
Spread pepper or chili powder on wax paper and roll cheese in powder to form a log.
Wrap in wax paper and chill.

title: pineapple cheesecake
directions: Melt about 3/4 of a stick of butter or margarine in a large rectangular Pyrex dish.
Add 2 tablespoons of sugar and cracker crumbs.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Let stand and cool.
In a bowl, mix lemon jello with boiling water.
Let cool, then beat until very frothy.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar into cream cheese.
Add drained can of pineapple and Cool Whip.
Mix all together and pour onto baking dish.
This is best when chilled overnight.

title: wine
directions: Use stone jar (such as churn) container.

title: rolled dumplings
directions: Mix together flour, salt, pepper and chicken broth.
Add eggs to mixture.
Roll out very thin on floured board.
If too wet, add flour.
Cut in strips 1/2-inch wide.
Cut strips up in 2-inch lengths.
Lay pieces on floured waxed paper.
Stack layers on top of each other.
Cook or freeze them.
Cook them in juice from a nice fat stewin' hen.
Yum!
Yum!

title: peanut brittle
directions: Line a cookie sheet or jelly roll pan with well buttered aluminum foil, buttered side up; set aside.
Combine sugar, syrup and salt in 2-quart bowl.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir in peanuts; microwave 3 to 5 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes, until syrup and peanuts are lightly browned.
Watch very carefully so the peanuts don't burn.
Stir in butter, vanilla and soda until light and foamy.
Spread to 1/4-inch thickness on foil covered cookie sheet.
Cool; break into pieces.
Makes 1 pound.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Mix together well the cream cheese, pecans and mayonnaise.
Add garlic and salt; mix well.	Spread 1 big spoonful across the end of a ham slice.
Roll up in jelly roll fashion.
Let set in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Slice 1/2-inch thick.
Place on crackers.

title: delicious fish batter
directions: Mix flour, 2 eggs and salt together.
Add enough beer to form a thick but still pourable batter.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg white.
Allow to ferment at room temperature for 1 hour.
Dip fillets into batter and deep-fry until crisp and golden brown.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate for one hour.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine dry mix and pie filling.
Mix until blended.
Do not grease pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix and pour half in oblong dish and chill until firm.
Spread 1 pint sour cream and put the rest of mixture on top.
Chill again.

title: rubbed noodles
directions: Mix together.
Will be crumbly.
Put in sifter and shake off excess flour.

title: brownie treats
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Stir in oats.
Mix well. Spread evenly over bottom of pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle chocolate morsels over hot oats to melt.

title: marbled pecan pound cake
directions: Beat butter and 1/2 cup shortening at medium speed with an electric mixer about 2 minutes or until creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to butter mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix at low speed just until blended after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.

Combine chocolate and 1 tablespoon shortening in a small, heavy saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate melts. Remove 2 cups of batter and add chocolate mixture, stirring until blended.
Pour one-third of remaining plain batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan; top with half of chocolate batter. Repeat layers, ending with plain batter.
Gently swirl batter with a knife to create marble effect and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on a wire rack 10 to 15 minutes; remove from pan and let cool completely.

title: hamburger supreme
directions: Brown meat.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Stir in soup, milk and seasonings.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Remove seasoning packet from noodle package as it will not be used. Crush noodles. Combine noodles and next four ingredients. Mix remaining ingredients with wire whisk for dressing. Pour dressing over cabbage mixture; toss gently to coat. Cover and chill. Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Put crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat until light.
Add pumpkin. Mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix at low speed until well blended.

title: peanut drop cookies
directions: Add syrup to thoroughly creamed fat. Add well beaten eggs and mix thoroughly. Sift dry ingredients. Add peanuts and combine with fat mixture. Mix well until blended. Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Makes 60 small cookies. Try this one, TOO!

title: marble cheesecake bars
directions: Heat oven to 350 (dark nonstick pan 325). Grease rectangular pan, 13x9x2 inches. Reserve 1 cup of dry cake mix. Blend remaining dry cake mix, margarine, and 1 egg on low speed until dough forms. Pat in bottom of pan. Bake until golden and until crust falls away from sides of pan., 15 to 20 minutes. Beat cream cheese and sour cream until smooth. Blend reserved cake mix, water, sugar, and 2 eggs into cream cheese mixture on low speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 2 minutes. Blend reserved cream cheese mixture and marbling mixture in small bowl on low speed. Drop dark batter by generous tablespoonfuls randomly in 6 to 8 mounds onto yellow batter. Cut through batter with knife in "s" shaped curves in one continuous motion. Turn pan 1/4 turn and repeat for marbled effect. Bake until set and cake springs back when touched lightly in the center, 31 to 36 minutes. Run knife along edges of cake to prevent cracking; cool completely. Refrigerate until firm. Cut into 2 1/4 x 1 inch bars. Top with fruit pie filling if desired. Refrigerate any remaining bars. Makes 48 bars.

title: marzetti
directions: Brown meat in shortening in heavy skillet; add onion, green pepper, mushrooms and seasonings.
Cook until tender, about 5 minutes.
Combine with tomato soup, tomato paste, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook noodles in boiling water until almost tender.
Drain and rinse.
In a large greased baking dish, spread half of noodles, cover with half of meat and sauce mixture and sprinkle with half of cheese.
Repeat, using remaining ingredients.
Bake in a moderate oven (375°) for about 45 minutes or until heated.
Serves 10.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Blend eggs, sugar and salad oil.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and ginger.
Add pumpkin alternately to egg mixture.
Mix well.
Fill 2 layer pans with mixture or 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or 45 minutes for the 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add milk and cook slowly.
Melt chocolate and add to the hot mixture.
Beat yolks and add small amount of hot mixture, then pour into the rest of the hot mixture. Add butter and vanilla and cook until stiff.
Cool and pour into cooled, baked crust.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter in pan.
Remove from heat.
Add to sugar and vanilla.
After you have mixed the sugar, butter and cheese, add what option you want (1 cup peanut butter or 1/2 cup cocoa).

title: quick salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and pineapple. Sprinkle dry Jell-O over this and mix well. Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Allow roast to come to room temperature.
Leave out at least 1 hour, but you can leave out overnight.
Season as you like.
Use no salt or salt products at this time, as they will draw juices and toughen the meat.
Garlic slivers in the fat and a good grinding of black pepper are nice.

title: cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake in spring-form pan.
Keep cream cheese at room temperature.
(So it will be easy to mix.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Skin, cook and cut chicken into cubes.
Mix soup (undiluted), sour cream and drained mushrooms and add chicken.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Heat water and melt margarine in it. Stir in stuffing and mix well.
Spread stuffing over chicken and cut it in.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Whip in cranberry sauce.
Add cold water.
Mix in Miracle Whip with beater.
Stir in apples. Chill 4 hours.
Serves 12.

title: luzi's enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Heat shortening on medium-high or enough to keep hot.
Mix tomato sauce with chili powder in large pie pan.
Put tortilla in hot grease; make sure it does not get hard.
Then put tortilla in sauce mixture, coating both sides. Place into square baking dish.
Stuff with ground beef, cheese and onion.
Roll tortilla up.
Repeat steps for each tortilla.
Put leftover meat, cheese, onion and tomato mixture over top.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: iroquois expedition food(traditional)
directions: All ingredients were pounded together with a stone wrapped in rawhide.
The pounded ingredients were carried in a parfletch bag or dried gourd.

title: baked doughnuts
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg.
Combine flour, baking powder, nutmeg and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with 1/2 cup milk.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, melt butter with garlic.
In medium bowl, combine cracker crumbs, cheese, parsley, salt, poultry seasoning and pepper.
Mix well.
Dip chicken in garlic butter; coat with crumb mixture.
Place skin side up in pan containing garlic butter.
Bake uncovered at 400° for about 1 hour or until tender, basting occasionally with pan drippings.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine all ingredients, including cheese.
Pour into 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Put paprika on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: english plum pudding
directions: Mix well the dry ingredients with butter (except flour and soda).
Beat eggs well and add whiskey and wine.
Mix well. Last, add flour and soda, sifted.
Mix.
Makes about 6 pounds. Boil 8 to 10 hours.
Place mixture in coffee cans; set in boiling water.
It's an all day affair.
May be topped with brandy and taken to the table flaming.
Serve with Hard Sauce.

title: peach pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each. Stir in extracts. Add all dry ingredients, then fold in sour cream and peaches. Pour into greased 10-inch tube pan and bake 75 to 85 minutes at 350°.

title: duffie's fried muskrat
directions: Wash; cut into	pieces.
Soak in salt water for 1 hour. Rinse and dry.
Dip
pieces
in batter made from milk and eggs and roll in	flour.	Brown
in a greased frying pan for 1 hour or until tender.
Make gravy from drippings and pour over meat before serving.

title: corn and broccoli
directions: In heavy, 2-quart saucepan, melt butter.
Add remaining ingredients; stir to blend.
Cover; cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until crisp-tender (8 to 10 minutes). Yield:
4 (3/4 cup) servings.

title: taco burgers
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; add beef and mix well.
Shape into 6 patties.
In large lightly greased skillet, brown patties on both sides.
Mix soup and 1/2 cup water.
Spoon over meat patties, cover and cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Cover and heat 3 minutes.
Serve with chips.

title: malfoof mahshi(stuffed cabbage leaves)
directions: Cook rice until tender (30 minutes).
Drain and add meat, butter and seasonings.
Form into small rolls.
Cook individual cabbage leaves in a small amount of water until wilted (about 5 minutes).
Wrap around meat rolls and place in a heavy skillet. Add tomato juice; cover and cook for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease pie pan, 10 x 1 1/2-inch.
Brown beef or turkey and onion; drain and season to taste.
Spread mixture into pie pan.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add soups and taco sauce; mix well. Add crushed chips.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch dish at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with salad for a complete meal.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream until smooth cream cheese, lemon juice, and mayonnaise. Whip the cream and add sugar; mix with cream cheese mixture. Add fruit and nuts. Dice chilled cranberry sauce; add to mixture. Freeze and serve.

title: kolache
directions: Scald milk; let cool until lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water to which has been added the sugar.
Let rise while milk cools.
Add dissolved yeast to cool milk and sponge and let rise until light.
Cream together 1 cup sugar and 1 cup butter.
Add eggs and salt.
Then add sponge and mix well.
Add enough flour to handle well.
Let dough rise until light and make into kolaches. Roll out dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with biscuit cutter. Make depression in center and fill.
Let rise and bake in quick oven, 400°, for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken divan
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 25 to 30 minutes.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Peel carrots, slice and cook in water until tender.
Process cooked carrots in blender until smooth.
Add all other ingredients and place in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: north carolina sand cake
directions: Mix well and bake in a large 9 x 12-inch pan at 350° for about 45 minutes. Put miniature marshmallows over top and brown lightly. You may substitute chocolate chips for butterscotch.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well and add flour.
Spread 3/4 of batter in a greased and floured 18 x 12 x 1-inch cookie sheet.
Make it a little higher at the sides of the pan.
Spread the contents of 2 cans of Thank You Brand cherries over all.
Drop the remaining batter here and there over all.
It spreads and makes its own design.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until light brown.
Good plain or with vanilla ice cream.

title: powdered rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cut or roll into small rolls. Cook for 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll into powdered sugar.

title: cheese spread
directions: Melt cheese in milk, stirring constantly.
Mix remaining ingredients together; add to cheese mixture.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Great for sandwiches for a reception.

title: chocolate raspberry cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition until well blended.
Fold in raspberries, reserving a few for garnish.
Place crust on baking sheet; fill with raspberry mixture.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Cool completely and chill.

title: hoagie dip
directions: Combine ham, salami, bologna and cheeses.
Put this in cubes. Then add lettuce, tomatoes and onion that has been chopped. Combine this all with dressing, oregano, garlic powder and pepper. Best if made several hours or night before.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain off grease.
Put in kettle and add remaining ingredients.
Cook until done.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into an 8-inch pie shell. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix and chill.

title: pull apart raspberry bread
directions: Allow each loaf to thaw and cut into 8 slices.
Cut each of those slices into 4 pieces.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Mix jello, sugars and spices.
Sprinkle evenly over bread.
Top with butter.
Let rise to top of pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately turn upside down on cookie sheet and let syrup run through bread.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat 4 minutes.
Bake in a well-greased tube pan at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Melt margarine and cheese together in double boiler.
Cook raw crabmeat and shred finely.
Fold into cheese mixture.
Season to taste.
Serve warm dip with crackers or raw vegetables.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on box.
Drain well and mix with undiluted can of soup.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Top with bread crumbs and almonds.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large bowl; add yogurt and toss gently to coat.
Cover and chill.
Yields 8 servings.

title: banana split cheesecake pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and bananas, mixing at medium speed on an electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in chopped walnuts; pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: family brunswick stew
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove meat from bones and cut into cubes.
Return it to the water in which it was cooked.
Add vegetables; cook until a thick mixture.
Cook slowly and stir often to prevent burning.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Chop all ingredients into a large salad bowl.
Mix in the Italian dressing.
Marinate overnight.
Serve icy cold.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Add milk, egg and onion.
Mix well.
Drop teaspoon in deep fat (300°).
Cook until golden brown. Place on paper towel to drain.
Great taste!

title: pork chops and potato dinner
directions: Place all ingredients except pork chops in 2-quart baking dish.
Stir well.
Fry pork chops until brown on both sides. Remove from skillet and place on top of potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes.

title: never fail pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening for 10 minutes.
Beat in one egg at a time.
Add mixed flour and milk alternately.
Stir in vanilla. Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: caramel delight pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Melt
butter in large skillet.	Add coconut and pecans. Cook until
golden
brown,
stirring
frequently.
Set aside. Combine cream
cheese
and condensed milk, beat until smooth. Fold in Cool Whip.

title: freezer cole slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, celery, pepper and salt.
Cover it with water and soak for 1 hour, then drain.
Mix in another bowl with sugar, vinegar, water, celery seed and mustard seed.
Put in cooker and simmer for 15 minutes.
Cool it and pour it over cabbage mix.
Mix it up good.
Put in freezer cups.
Store in refrigerator overnight, then you freeze it.
Thaw and eat.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice.
Separately chop onion and saute in oleo.
Mix together the rice, broccoli, onion, Cheez Whiz, soup and water.
Place in a large casserole dish and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Mix all together and bake in a 9 x 14 pyrex dish at 350 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes. Cut in squares. Before serving make a sauce to pour over it. Use one can cream of chicken soup and 1 c. water. Thicken this with flour and add some butter. Now pour it over the chicken loaf.

title: cherry winks
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Crush cornflakes and set aside.
Beat margarine and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Mix in nuts, dates and cherries and mix well.
