Take rounded spoonfuls of cookie dough, roll into balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Press 1/2 of a maraschino cherry on top of each dough ball.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.

title: quiche(yields 6 servings)
directions: Mix eggs, milk, pepper, Bisquick and salt in blender; set aside.
In greased quiche pan, place a layer of mushrooms, layer of onion and layer of green pepper and celery mixed.
Then add layer of chicken, ham or bacon, layer of broccoli, layer of Cheddar and layer of Mozzarella cheese.
Pour egg mixture over layers and bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until knife in middle is clean.

title: microwave coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in 2-quart microwave-safe bowl. Add milk and egg yolks.
Mix well.
Microwave at High power 10 to 12 minutes.
Stir after 5 minutes, then every 2 minutes, until thickened.
Stir in butter, extracts and flaked coconut.
Pour into a baked 9-inch pie shell.
Top with meringue and sprinkle on 2 to 4 tablespoons coconut.
Bake at 350° about 5 minutes or until brown on top.

title: chocolate chip bars(about 24 bars)
directions: In small mixing bowl, cream together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg, milk, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add creamed mixture. Blend well.
Stir 1/2 cup chocolate pieces and nuts.
Spread in greased dish.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup chocolate pieces. Cook on High for 5 to 6 minutes, until done.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Take peanut butter and confectioners sugar.
Mix until crumbly and put in graham cracker crusts.
Mix vanilla long cooking pudding.
Put on top of confectioners sugar and peanut butter mixture.
Refrigerate until pudding is cooled and set up.
Then top with Cool Whip.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pork stuffing
directions: Saute sausage with onion and celery.
Mix in bread crumbs. Add small amounts of chicken bouillon until desired consistency is obtained.
Add poultry seasoning to flavor.
Stuff turkey.
Enjoy!

title: easy biscuits
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder in a bowl.
Measure oil and milk in same measuring cup; add to flour mixture.
Make into biscuits.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes.

title: potato topped cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in shortening; drain.
Stir in seasoning, corn, cheese and ketchup.
Spoon into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Blend egg yolks into potatoes.
Spread on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Place under broiler for several minutes for a crisper topping.

title: mushroom pastries
directions: Melt butter and saute onion; add mushrooms and cook slowly, about 3 minutes.
Add thyme, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons flour.
Stir in sour cream.
Cook gently until thickened, cool!

title: chicken breasts tarragon
directions: In 6-quart Dutch oven, heat oil and 2 tablespoons margarine. Add chicken breasts, covering bottom of pan.
Saute, turning on all sides, until brown.
Remove chicken.
Add shallots and carrots to drippings; stir until golden brown.
Return chicken to Dutch oven and heat.
Heat cognac in ladle over gas flame or electric burner; ignite and pour while flaming over chicken.
Add wine, chopped tarragon, chervil, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer gently while covered for 30 minutes. Remove chicken to heated serving platter to keep warm.
Strain drippings in Dutch oven (discard vegetables); return drippings to Dutch oven.
In a small bowl, combine cream, egg yolk and flour; mix well with wire whisk.
Stir into drippings, bringing just to a boil.
Add more wine if sauce seems too thick.
Meanwhile, saute mushrooms in hot margarine 5 minutes, until tender.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Garnish with tarragon and mushrooms.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crab mold
directions: Heat
soup.
Dissolve
gelatin	in
tablespoons cold water. Stir gelatin into hot soup.
Cook a little bit. Remove from
heat and mix with rest of ingredients.
Spray molds with Pam and pour mixture into molds.
Serve on crackers.

title: best ever banana creme pie
directions: In heavy saucepan, dissolve cornstarch and salt in water. Stir in milk and egg yolks.
Over medium heat, cook until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Dip sliced bananas in lemon juice; drain.
Arrange bananas in pie shell; cover with filling.
Chill 4 hours.
Cover with Dream Whip prepared as directed. Refrigerate.

title: cauliflower-broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let set overnight or for several hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: cherry cheese delight
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine cherry pie filling, cottage cheese, almonds and almond extract.
Mix well.
Fold in whipped topping; chill until ready to serve.
Garnish with almonds or mint leaves, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken breasts tarragon
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Stir together butter and seasonings. Loosen skin on one side of each chicken breast to form pockets, keeping remaining outer edges intact.
Place about 1 tablespoons of butter-herb mixture in each pocket.
Close pocket and press, smoothing mixture under skin.
Place chicken, skin side up, in shallow baking pan.
Place chicken, skin side up, in shallow baking pan.
Bake for about 35 minutes or until juices run clear; baste occasionally with pan drippings.
Serve immediately.
Yields 8 servings.

title: meatless chicken salad
directions: Chop chicken (or use food processor).
Add all ingredients and mix.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, lettuce, green onions, almonds, chow mein noodles and water chestnuts in a large bowl.
In small mixing bowl, mix sugar, salt, Accent, rice vinegar, pepper, salad oil and lemon juice.
Don't pour over salad until you are ready to eat.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, cheese, oregano and garlic powder together. Spoon dressing mixture over chicken in 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Place baking dish on oven rack in second from top position. (This allows for even browning.) Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until chicken is cooked done. Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and congeal.
Mix the remaining ingredients and spread on top of pie.

title: dill casserole bread
directions: Add yeast to water.
Combine in mixing bowl cottage cheese, sugar, onion, butter, dill, salt, baking soda, egg and yeast.
Add flour to form a stiff dough, beating well after each addition. Cover, let rise in warm place till light and double in size (approx. 1 hr).
Stir down dough.
Turn into a well greased 8-inch round pan that holds about 1/2 to 1 qt casserole.
Let rise in warm place 30-40 minutes.
Bake at 350 F for 40-50 minutes.
Brush with soft butter and sprinkle with salt.
(I prefer coarse salt for this.)

title: cinnamon skillet apples
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch; add rest of ingredients and cook over medium heat.
Spoon sauce over apples.
Cook 20 minutes or until tender.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Saute ham, onion,
garlic
and
parsley in butter until golden.
Drain beans and mix with sauteed mixture.
Cover with water.
Add salt, pepper
and
cayenne pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil and simmer
over
very low heat until beans are soft and creamy, about 4 hours.
May
be
refrigerated
for
2 to 3 days and reheated slowly.

title: krautwinkles
directions: Cook ground beef until done; drain. Add cabbage and cook until tender.
Use Season-All as desired.

Unroll 1 can of rolls and press 1 section crescent rolls until flat and seams are sealed. Place cheese slices on dough to cover up to 1/2-inch each edge. Spoon 1/2 to 1 cup cabbage mixture onto cheese.
Unroll second section and press as before.
Place on top and press edges to seal.
(May fold dough in half, if smaller winkles are desired.) Place on cookie sheet and bake according to package directions. Repeat with second can crescent rolls.

title: rainbow pasta salad
directions: Boil rotini until tender and drain.
Chop boiled eggs and mix with all ingredients.
Season with salt, garlic salt or seasoned salt.

title: stuffing good chicken
directions: Put chicken in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking pan.
Lay cheese over chicken pieces.
Mix soup and wine with a whisk and pour over chicken and cheese.
Dump stuffing over all and spread out evenly. Pour melted butter over top of stuffing and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(Can be made up the night before and baked the next day for 50 minutes if cold from the refrigerator.)

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients except flour.
Work this mixture with the flour until you have a workable dough.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: sundae bubble crown
directions: Bake the Miniature Cream Puffs.
Prepare Fudge Sauce.
Cool to room temperature.
When ready to assemble crown, soften vanilla ice cream.

title: bakery style cheese cake
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13 baking dish with crescent rolls; seals all seams.
Blend all other ingredients until smooth.
Pour into dough lined baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 - 45 minutes. Will rise during baking then sink some what.

title: cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Use 10-inch spring-form pan (don't grease pan).

title: low-fat baked lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In Dutch oven, cook ground beef, onion, garlic and fennel seed over medium heat until meat is browned. Drain and return to pan.
Stir in pasta sauce, basil, oregano and pepper; continue cooking until heated through.
In 13 x 9-inch baking dish spray with nonstick cooking spray.
Spread 1 cup sauce on bottom of pan.
Top with 1/3 lasagna noodles, sauce, Ricotta cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layering 2 more times. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover; bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: unfried chicken(good for you and yummy)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Coat baking pan with 3 sprays of Pam. Put chicken in ice water (will help it to brown).
Put yogurt in bowl or plastic storage bag.
Toss bread crumbs and spices in sealed plastic storage bag.
Roll 2 pieces of chicken in yogurt and then toss in sealed bread crumb mixture until thoroughly coated. Place on baking sheet or pan.
Repeat until all chicken is coated. Spray chicken lightly with Pam.
Bake for 1 hour on bottom shelf of oven, turning every 20 minutes for even browning.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugars with margarine.
Add eggs, then peanut butter. Add flour 1/2 cup at a time until it forms big ball.
Pinch off about 2 inches, roll into ball and make crisscross as you press down onto cookie dough with fork.
Bake at 350° until golden brown (10 minutes).
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice as directed on package. Cool completely.

title: crab and rice casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in a Pyrex bowl and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
(I make 2 layers.)

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water.
Set to soft set, then stir in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Add all ingredients together and serve.

title: tasty squash casserole
directions: Cook and cube the squash and zucchini.
Cook onion in water and drain.
Add to the cooked squash.
Mix in the sour cream and mushroom soup.
Stir in the carrots, butter and stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peach cobbler quick and easy
directions: Place peaches in a pan.
Sprinkle lightly with sugar.
Cream together 1 cup sugar and margarine.
Add flour and vanilla.
Mix until crumbly and crumble over peaches.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: fassafern tomatoes
directions: Mix tomatoes, salt, pepper and brown sugar very well.
Pour into shallow baking dish.
Cover with crushed Melba toast and then cover entire top with lumps of butter.
Bake in slow oven at 275° or 300° for 4 hours.
Serves 4 plentifully.

title: cold oven cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Microwave the ingredients for 5 minutes on Medium.
Stir and pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut and enjoy.

title: sunday supper hamburger(grandpa tackett's favorite)
directions: Brown onion lightly in butter.
Add hamburger and brown. Combine remaining ingredients, except wheat flakes.
Put in buttered baking dish, 7 1/2 x 11 3/4 x 1 3/4-inch.
Top with crushed wheat flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken tamale pie
directions: Cook onion, celery and garlic in 2 tablespoons oil until just tender.
Stir in chicken, tomato sauce, olives, 1/2 cup chicken broth, 1 teaspoon salt and chili powder.
Bring remaining broth to boil.
Add remaining salt and salad oil.
Pour into casserole dish.

title: butch's red slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: nectarine chicken salad with tarragon
directions: Combine mayonnaise, yogurt, tarragon, lemon juice, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Add chicken, nectarines and celery; toss. Line bowl or platter with the lettuce.
Mound chicken salad on lettuce.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Serve with croissants.

title: easy tomato sauce
directions: Blend tomatoes and add carrot chunks until desired consistency is reached.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 15 minutes.

title: tangy lemon chicken
directions: Cook on low heat for 30 minutes, then let chicken sit in sauce for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cook on grill (indirect heat) for 45 to 60 minutes.
After cooked, spoon some sauce on chicken.

title: bacon-cheese rolls
directions: Pick asparagus as round as your finger.
Partially cook asparagus in microwave until half done.
Drain and run under cold water until cool.
Roll in flour with salt and pepper.
Dip in egg mixture of grated Romano cheese, 2 cloves of garlic and some parsley.
Hold up and let egg run off.
Dip in Italian bread crumbs.
Fry in about 1/4-inch oil on medium heat until lightly brown and crunchy.
Drain on paper towels and sprinkle grated Romano cheese over.
Serve hot.

title: spanish beef stew
directions: Place olive oil in a large deep skillet or dutch oven with the top round, salt, pepper and garlic.
Brown well.
Add tomatoes, onion and green pepper.
Cook for a few minutes longer.
Add oregano and bay leaves and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to a slow simmer.
Cook for about 30 minutes longer.
Add potatoes, carrots, and string beans and cook until meat and vegetables are tender, about 30 minutes.
Mix flour and water together to make a smooth roux.
Add to stew.
Stir and cook until thickened.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Layer alternating layers of carrots, onion and bell peppers in casserole dish.

title: norwegian pancakes
directions: Combine sour cream and cottage cheese.
Add other ingredients, beat with mixer and blend well.
Bake on hot griddle until bubbles break on surface, turn.
Serve with favorite syrup.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Place cake cubes in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Mix milk and package of vanilla pudding mix.
Cook according to directions. Cool; stir in softened vanilla ice cream and beat until well blended.
Pour mixture over cake cubes and chill until firm. Combine boiling water with strawberry gelatin in another bowl. Stir until dissolved.
Add frozen strawberries; blend well and chill until slightly thickened.
Pour over pudding mixture.
Do not stir.
Chill until firm or overnight.
Serve plain or with whipped cream, topped with strawberries.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix dry stuff and set aside. Cream butter, peanut butter and sugar. Add egg and vanilla. Mix well. Add dry stuff. Mix together. Add chocolate chips. Drop onto cookie sheet. Press with fork. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken, debone and cut in bite size pieces.
Place in baking dish coated with Pam.
Mix sour cream and milk, pour over chicken.
Cover with crackers, sprinkle with poppy seed, drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until golden brown and bubbly.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix all of the ingredients well.
It is enough for 2 pies. Cook 2 frozen pie shells as directed.
Pour mixture into the cooked pie shells and refrigerate.
Pies may be frozen.

title: monica's lemon pie
directions: Blend lemonade, milk and vanilla until white.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into crust.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cheesecake
directions: Stir cream cheese until very soft. Gradually blend in 1/2 cup milk until smooth and creamy. Add 1 1/2 cups milk and pudding mix. Beat slowly with mixer for 1 minute. Pour at once into a cooled graham cracker crust. Chill 1 hour or until firm enough to cut.

title: carol herget's mushroom bread
directions: Split bread.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on bread. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: golden mushroom beef tips
directions: In skillet, brown beef in butter with onion and garlic.
Add chicken broth; cover and cook over low heat 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in soup and water.
Cover; cook 30 minutes longer or until tender. Stir now and then.
Serve over noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: confetti scalloped potatoes
directions: In a skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Saute onion until tender.
Stir in potatoes, soup and milk.
Add cheese, green pepper, pimento, pepper and 1/2 cup of the crumbs.
Pour into a shallow casserole.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fajitas
directions: Trim fat from steaks.
Prick with fork in several places.
Mix 1/4 cup oil, vinegar, sugar, oregano, chili powder, garlic powder, salt and pepper in ungreased baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate, turning beef occasionally, for 8 hours.
Heat oven to 325°.
Wrap tortillas in foil and heat until warm; move beef from marinade. Broil beef until brown.
Turn and brush with marinade and broil 7 to 8 minutes longer.
Cook and stir onions and bell peppers in 2 tablespoons oil until tender.

title: old-time gingerbread with warm lemon sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Into large bowl, measure 1/2 cup boiling water and all ingredients except Warm Lemon Sauce.
With mixer at low speed, beat until well blended, constantly scraping bowl with rubber spatula.
Increase speed to high; beat 2 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool gingerbread in pan on wire rack 10 minutes to serve warm or cool completely on rack to serve later.

title: drumstick torte
directions: Mix together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: blintzes
directions: Blend together cottage cheese and eggs.
Stir in cinnamon. Fill each crepe with a couple tablespoons.
Fold into a small square package.
Brown in a little margarine.
Serve with sour cream and pie filling.
We usually use two eggs for a pint of cottage cheese.
Because we like them well done, we usually pop them in the microwave for a bit after browning.

title: potato-carrot bake
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bake full power in microwave in casserole dish for 20 minutes.
Fat free.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add milk, peanut butter and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Roll into balls and then into sugar.
(Use color sugar at Christmas.)
Pam spray cookie sheets. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Immediately top with candy kiss. Press down and bake 1 minute.
Cool and remove from sheet.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add after first mixture has set overnight.
Fold in 1 package prepared Dream Whip.
Chill.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: papaya seed dressing
directions: Place the first 5 ingredients in the blender.
Turn on the blender and gradually add onion and oil.
When blended, add papaya seed and blend to a consistency of coarse ground pepper.

title: liver and sour  gravy
directions: Fry liver in shortening, slowly turning only once.
When done, remove liver and use grease for gravy.
Brown flour in grease. Add onions (chopped) and stir together until onions are half done. Add vinegar, water, brown sugar and salt and pepper.
Cook slowly until gravy is the thickness you like.
Add more water if necessary.
Put liver back in gravy and heat thoroughly.
Serve with noodles or boiled potatoes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients; pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chili-sausage supper
directions: In a large skillet or an electric skillet, cook and stir meat, onion and green pepper until meat is brown and onion is tender. Drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except sour cream. Cover.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until noodles are tender, adding more water, if necessary, to prevent sticking.
Add sour cream the last 5 minutes just to heat through.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: In a punch bowl, layer as follows:
pineapple; yellow cake (1 layer); pudding; cherries; coconut; pecan pieces and Cool Whip. Repeat this process, finishing with whipped cream.
I garnish with mint leaves.
Keep refrigerated.

title: orange cream cheese frosting
directions: In small bowl, beat cream cheese, oleo and peel.
Beat until fluffy and spread over cooled cake.
(If too thick, add milk.)

title: cantaloupe fruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Cool; add ginger ale and fruits.
Pour into ring mold; chill until firm.
Turn out on shredded lettuce.
Serves 8.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Clean and seed the peppers.
Boil 5 minutes; drain.
Brown the ground beef with the chopped onion.
Remove fat.
Add 1/2 cup Ragu spaghetti sauce flavored with meat (from the 32-ounce jar) and 2 cups herb seasoned stuffing cubes.
Stuff peppers.
Place 1/2 remaining sauce, 2/3 cup beef broth and 1/2 cup water in a large saucepan.
Stand 6 peppers in sauce.
Repeat in an oven-to-freezer casserole.
Simmer, covered, 20 minutes.

title: potato chip tuna casserole
directions: Moisten chips and crush.
Line bottom of baking pan with chips. Drain tuna, sprinkle tuna on top of chips.
Cover with cream of mushroom soup.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: rebaked potatoes
directions: Bake (do not foil wrap) 450° approximately 1 hour or until done.
If serving whole potato, cut section off side; if serving 1/2 potato, cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out, leaving just enough to keep skin firm.
Beat all ingredients together to desired consistency and fill skins.
To serve, reheat approximately 1/2 hour before serving, or until hot throughout.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush
Oreos.
Mix pudding and milk according to directions on box.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar.

title: spicy spaghetti
directions: In medium bowl, combine ground beef, ground pork, onion, bread crumbs, parsley, milk, seasoned salt and pepper; mix well.
Shape 12 meatballs.
In Dutch oven, brown meatballs in oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, 30 minutes stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf. Prepare 1 pound package of spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
Serve with meatballs and sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: melon cooler salad(low calorie - weight watcher)
directions: Place Neufchatel Cheese and Lemonade concentrate in food processor until well blended.
Spoon melon balls into parfait glasses or desert bowls.
Top with cream cheese mixture. 8 Servings - 3 Points.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Line pie shell with whole berries, reserving 1 cup for glaze. Simmer 3 or 4 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and sugar.
Add cooked fruit.
Cook again until thick and clear.
Stir continuously.
Cool slightly.
Pour over berries.
Chill thoroughly (at least 1 hour). Cover with whipped cream.

title: milk custard(flan)
directions: Mix eggs, rum and vanilla in blender.
Add milks and blend for about 5 minutes.
Pour mixture into a recipient already prepared with caramel and raisins.
Let cool for approximately one hour.

title: blueberry salad
directions: To Jell-O, add boiling water; dissolve thoroughly and set aside 1/4 cup of mixture.
Add pineapple (juice and all) and blueberries (juice and all).
Mix well.
Set in refrigerator to congeal.
When congealed, mix cream cheese with powdered sugar and vanilla; set aside.
Whip 1 envelope Dream Whip according to directions on package.
Mix with cream cheese mixture.
Add 1/4 cup of Jell-O mixture.
Spread on top of congealed salad. Sprinkle with pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes; cut in 1/8-inch slices and combine mayonnaise, sour cream, horseradish, celery seed and salt.
Set aside.
In another bowl, mix parsley and onion.
In rectangular glass serving dish, arrange a layer of potatoes; salt lightly.
Cover with a layer of mayonnaise-sour cream mixture, then layer of onion mixture.
Continue layering, ending with parsley and onion.
Do not stir.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours before serving. Serves 8 to 10.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle the coconut and pecans over the bottom of the pan. Prepare cake mix according to box directions and pour over coconut and pecans.

title: savory meat loaf
directions: Mix and form into loaf.
Put a few slices of bacon on top or glaze.

title: rice gumbo
directions: In a large skillet saute onions in a small amount of oil.
Add tomato sauce with 1/2 can of water.
Add seasonings and chicken gumbo soup.
Rinse can with water and add to skillet.
Let simmer 20 minutes.
Prepare rice according to package directions.
Blend gumbo mixture into cooked rice.
Serve as a side dish with anything.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown hamburger meat, salt and pepper to taste.
Add onion and egg.
Cook until done.
After meat is done, add 1 package Mozzarella cheese.
Cook noodles as directed.
Wash in cold water after done.
Pour enough spaghetti sauce in bottom of pan to cover.
Stuff noodles with prepared meat.
Lay over sauce.
Then add the rest of sauce.
Cover with package of Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: no-bake banana pudding
directions: Prepare instant pudding following package directions.
Let stand until slightly thickened, 3 minutes.
Mix in Eagle Brand and Cool Whip.
Slice bananas, then layer wafers, bananas and filling in clear glass bowl or 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass dish.
Serve immediately or refrigerate.

title: venison machaca style(deer or elk)
directions: Remove all fat from venison.
Sprinkle meat with tenderizer. Melt margarine in skillet and add roast or meat chunks.
Brown on all sides.
Add water to almost cover meat.
Heat to boil; add oregano, garlic and celery seed.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until meat falls apart when tested with fork (about 2 to 3 hours depending on size of roast).

title: baked sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Arrange pork chops in baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1 package Lipton onion soup.
Pour 1 bottle Russian dressing over all.
Add approximately 1/2 bottle of water.
Top with 3 to 4 tablespoons apricot preserves.
Do not cover.
Bake at 350°
for about 1 hour. Good with rice.

title: brandied chocolate
directions: Combine 1 cup cold water, cornstarch and cinnamon.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Add milk, sugar and chocolate; stir until chocolate melts.
Remove cinnamon stick.
Beat with a rotary blender to blend in chocolate.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of boiling water for approximately 10 minutes, or until tender-crisp.
Drain, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Combine reserved liquid, honey, butter and brown sugar.
Stir well.
Pour over carrots and cook over low heat until thoroughly heated.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix 2 cups flour with 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Press mixture into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Sort beans to remove any "bad" ones.
Place in a large saucepan, cover with water.
Place a loose cover over pan and soak overnight.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt well in boiler; add milk and stir well.
Cook over medium heat, then add beaten eggs.
After it thickens over medium heat, add vanilla flavoring.
Take the 3 egg whites and beat good until fluffy.
Add 4 tablespoons sugar; beat well and add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread over top of pudding. Bake in 400° oven until brown.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and quarter artichokes.
Add other ingredients; mix and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with Town House or other special crackers.

title: fruited pork cutlets
directions: Pound meat between waxed paper sheets to 1/4-inch thick.
Melt margarine in skillet and brown cutlets a few at a time.
Remove as they brown and keep warm.

title: millionaire fudge
directions: Cook sugar and evaporated milk together for 14 minutes or soft boil, stirring constantly.
Take from stove and add margarine, chocolate chips, marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla extract. Beat until thick.
Pour into buttered pan (about 18 x 12-inch). Cool and cut into squares.

title: mexican soup
directions: Mix and heat chicken and rice soup with can of Ro-Tel.
Pour over Ranch Doritos chips and top with shredded Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheese.
Serves at least 6 people.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Partially thaw potatoes; heat oven to 350°.
Mix sour cream, soup, margarine, onion, salt, pepper, garlic salt and cheese. Stir in potatoes and place mixture in lightly buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
With hands, crush corn flakes; stir in 4 tablespoons melted margarine.
Spread over potato mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 12 servings.

title: nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts, beating vigorously by hand for 30 seconds.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch heat resistant glass loaf dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shipwreck stew
directions: Grease dish.
Put all meat and vegetables in.
Mix up sauces and seasonings and stir in good over the meat and vegetables. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fried rice
directions: Cut meat in small pieces. Cook onion lightly in oil (not brown). Add eggs and fry lightly. Add rice, salt, pepper and meat. Stir and cook 3 minutes. Take off heat and add soy sauce. Serve hot.

title: coconut cream pie(microwave)
directions: Mix milk, sugar, salt, flour, coconut and egg yolks in a large Pyrex bowl.
Microwave on High for 9 minutes or until thickened. Add butter and mix until melted.
Then add vanilla; mix well. Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and 2 tablespoons coconut.
Brown in oven.

title: sesame almond chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients, except butter and chicken.
Dip chicken in melted butter, then coat with crumb mixture.
Reserve remaining butter.
Place chicken in ungreased (9 x 13-inch) dish.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Pour remaining butter over chicken.
Bake for 65 to 75 minutes or until the chicken is fork-tender.

title: overnight cauliflower salad
directions: Saute garlic and mushrooms.
Let mixture stand in marinade overnight.
Then drain off.
This recipe will serve 5 people.

title: the next best thing to tom selleck
directions: Bake cake as directed in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Take out of oven and poke holes in the cake with a wooden spoon.
Pour milk in holes, then ice cream topping.
Frost with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with crushed candy bars.
Refrigerate.

title: black walnut diabetic cake
directions: Beat eggs, measure 3 bottle caps of Sucaryl.
Pour into eggs. Add shortening; beat until creamy.
Blend in salt, flour and lemon juice.
Stir in walnuts and coconut.
Turn into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Yields 20 slices.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: In the microwave, soften the cream cheese.
Stir in the green enchilada sauce, the sour cream and the diced ortega chilies.
Stir in 1/2 of the grated cheese.
The ingredients are going to be assembled in layers similar to lasagna-sauce, chicken, tortilla strips.
In an 8 x 8 x 2-inch deep casserole dish, spoon in some of the sauce, enough to lightly cover the bottom of the dish. Sprinkle chicken pieces over the sauce.
Cover the chicken with strips of tortilla and start the process again.

Leave enough sauce for the top layer (if you have any extra, just pour it on). Sprinkle the rest of the cheese over the top of the casserole and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until the cheese begins to brown.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugars and eggs together well.
Add vanilla. Sift flour, salt and soda together; add to egg mixture.
Add chocolate chips.
Spoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: oriental malo soup
directions: Combine pork, chopped shrimp, 1/2 of chopped onion, 1/2 of chopped carrot, soy sauce, egg, sesame oil, pepper and cornstarch. Mix well.
Place 1 teaspoon of filling in the center of each malo wrapper.
Fold in triangle; moisten edges, pressing to seal.
In a casserole, put minced onion and chopped carrot in 1 tablespoon of oil.
Add the chicken broth and cream of asparagus.
Put salt or salted fish sauce to taste.
Drop filled malo in the boiling broth; cook for 10 minutes.

title: jambalaya
directions: Melt margarine over medium heat.
Add onion, garlic and pepper. Cook to transparent (3 or 4 minutes).
Add chicken, tomato sauce and ham.
Bring to boil, then simmer 5 minutes, stirring often.

title: garlic grit casserole
directions: Add grits to boiling water. While hot, add 1/2 stick butter and cheese. Add milk.
Add eggs, beaten in a measuring cup then add enough milk to make a cup. Stir into greased casserole.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes.

title: christmas eve pecans
directions: Beat egg white until foamy.
Add pecan halves and stir gently until coated.
Set aside.
Combine the sugar, cinnamon and salt and sprinkle over pecans, stirring gently, until coated.
Spread pecans in a lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Cool completely and store in airtight container.

title: date nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over raisins, dates, butter and baking soda.
Let stand.
Mix flour, sugar and salt; add to fruit mixture.
Add remaining ingredients; beat well.
Pour into greased bread pan (1 regular or 2 small).
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy cakes
directions: Mix all but peanut butter and chocolate together.
Bake in large greased jelly roll pan for 12 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove and spread with peanut butter while still warm.
Refrigerate until cold.
Melt the Hershey bar and spread over the peanut butter. Refrigerate until set.
Cut into bars.

title: diet peppercorn steak with mushrooms
directions: Press cracked pepper into both sides of steak; saute with margarine in a nonstick skillet.
Add remaining ingredients and cook, covered, for 10 minutes or until done.
Serve over 1 cup cooked noodles.

title: zucchini pie(tastes like sugar cream)
directions: Peel, chunk and cook zucchini until soft; blend in blender until smooth.
Put all ingredients into blender.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pie shells.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon across the top.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature and bake at 300° for 25 additional minutes.

title: momas shrimp salad
directions: Boil noodles until tender allow to cool in the refrigerator. When noodles cool add bell pepper, onion, and shrimp.
Season with Tony Chacheres, salt, black pepper to taste.
Add mayonnaise. For best taste chill in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and pudding mix until smooth and thickened.
Stir in Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip. Layer in large bowl: first the wafers, then bananas, then pudding until all is used. Makes a large serving.

title: potato casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 1/2 package potatoes, half of onion, salt, pepper and parsley flakes.
Dot with margarine. Repeat.
Pour whipping cream all over.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for about 1 hour.
If potatoes get dry, add a little milk.

title: microwave munch mix
directions: Place butter in glass baking dish.
Microwave about 1 1/2 to 2 minutes on Medium-high or until melted.
Stir in seasoning mix and remaining ingredients.
Microwave on High for 2 to 4 minutes or until heated through.

title: olive spread
directions: Mix and chill. Can be made ahead.

title: ranch style cookies
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients and mix until like corn meal. Add unbeaten eggs and vanilla and mix.
Add oatmeal and Rice Krispies and mix well then add coconut.
Stir only until mixed. Roll out dough into small balls with hands and place on ungreased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
With fork, press dough to 1/4 inch.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: company casserole
directions: Layer the first 6 ingredients in casserole.
Combine mayonnaise, soup, mustard and curry powder.
Spread over casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Heat soup and milk, stirring frequently.
Stir in vegetables and turkey.
Heat through.
Pour mixture into ungreased 3-quart casserole.
Keep hot while preparing top.

title: stacked omelet in the microwave
directions: Scramble eggs and add seasoning.
Since eggs cook quicker at the edge of the pan, use a small glass bowl upside down in the center of your large glass bowl.
Butter and add eggs and your favorite fillings.
Cooked in 7 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Knead all ingredients except water together, then add water. Let stand 10 minutes, then roll out.
Makes 3 crusts.

title: nonfat brownie oatmeal cookies
directions: In large bowl, mix all dry ingredients.
Add wet ingredients. Stir and mix together very well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets sprayed with cooking spray.
Space 1 to 2 inches apart. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cook longer for crunch, less for chewy.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Fry bacon crisp.
Remove from skillet; saute onion in bacon drippings.
Remove all but 1 to 2 tablespoons of bacon drippings. Add vinegar and sugar.
Add drained and rinsed green beans. Simmer until most of liquid is gone.
Add bacon, toss and serve.

title: overnight salad
directions: Cook and cool.
Add 1 pint whipped cream.
Pour over fruit mix.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Five minutes before cake is done, mix, in a saucepan, and bring to a boil, oleo, cocoa and milk.
Remove from heat.
Add chopped pecans, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Stir and pour over cake as soon as you remove it from oven.
(Excellent cake.)

title: fruit goop
directions: Chop frozen strawberries; stir in other fruit.
Freeze for a couple of hours.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating good after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients 3 times and add alternately with sour cream to first mixture, beating until smooth.
Add flavoring and fold in cherries.
Pour in greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: pat a pie crust
directions: Pour all ingredients into pie pan.
Mix until damp.
Reserve 1/3 for top crust.
Press evenly into bottom and side.
Add filling.
Crimp. Crumble.
Reserve dough over top and bake.

title: deluxe corn bread
directions: Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Beat egg white; set aside. Mix all other ingredients and fold the egg white into mixture. Cook on hot griddle. Thin if desired. Makes about 8.

title: four-star chocolate chips
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Combine the flour, soda and salt; set aside. Cream butter, sugar and vanilla with mixer. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in chocolate chips, walnuts, raisins and coconut. Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake 9 to 11 minutes or until golden brown. Let them rest 2 minutes on baking sheet before removing. Makes about 60 cookies. Can freeze. Can do ahead.

title: garlic buttered popcorn
directions: Place butter and garlic in small saucepan.
Heat until butter is melted.
Remove garlic and stir in parsley.
Pour butter mixture over popcorn and toss lightly.
Good for a party snack.

title: creole beef
directions: Brown meat in 2 tablespoons oil.
Brown onion and celery in 1 tablespoon oil and add flour.
Add tomatoes and make a sauce.
Add green pepper, seasonings, meat and water.
Cook slowly for 10 to 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.
(All ingredients can be modified to taste and the recipe definitely improves with age.)

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Make into balls and place in baking dish.

title: grilled trout
directions: Wash fish in cold water.
Lay fish on aluminum foil.
Place salsa inside fish.
Lay bacon strips on each side of fish.
Wrap fish in foil.
Place fish on barbecue grill when charcoal stops flaming.
Cook fish 20 minutes on each side (40 minutes total).

title: porcupines
directions: Crumble bread into a bowl and pour a little milk over it (just enough to soften it).
Add beaten egg, ground meat, rice, bell pepper and salt and pepper to taste.
Form mixture into balls and place in a greased casserole dish.
Cover with dry soup mix, tomato puree and 1 can of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until meat is done and rice is popping out.

title: easy creme frosting
directions: Cream together all ingredients, except milk.
Add milk, one tablespoon at a time, until frosting is of spreading consistency. Refrigerate until cake is cool.
Spread on cake. This makes a lot!

title: breakfast granola
directions: Combine dry ingredients; mix well.
Combine with wet ingredients.
Spread on cookie sheets.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour, stirring frequently.
Cool and store in airtight containers. Makes about 33 cups.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix together oleo, eggs, sugar and 1 teaspoon vinegar.
Fold in nuts, coconut and raisins.
Pour in deep pie crust and bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done (test with straw).

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Go out into the 'cuntree' or on the road-side or 'fince' row and 'peek' 'yo-self' some poke.
Be sure ya' don't git snake bit! 'Brang' 'em home 'un warsh 'em.
Then 'tho' 'em in a pot an boil 'em good; drain an' add ya some mo' watta' an' boil again.
Then scramble ya up some egg an' mix with the poke.
Add salt and peppa'...an ya got 'yo-self' some poke salet.

title: divine rice casserole(serves 12)
directions: Brown meat in a small amount of cooking oil; season meat with salt and pepper or seasoned salt.
Parboil celery.
Saute onions and pepper lightly in the same skillet you browned meat in.
Mix all ingredients together; pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 2 1/2 hours or until meat is done.
Makes 1 large or 2 small casseroles.
Delicious!!!!!!

title: hamburger noodle casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients
in
large	Dutch
oven and saute until done.
Then add
tomato
sauce and simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Blend together
scallions,	cream
cheese
and
sour cream.
Cook noodles according
to
the	package.
In
greased casserole, place 1/3 noodles,
then 1/3 scallion mixture, then 1/3 meat mixture. Continue
two more layers.	Top with grated cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes
at
350°. Freezes well before baking.

title: ann's peanut butter candy
directions: Boil milk and sugar for 1 minute.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well and pour into an 8-inch square pan lined with aluminum foil. Cut into squares when cooled.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put light brown sugar, white syrup and margarine in a pan and melt.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove and stir in soda.
Pour over corn. Put on cookie sheets and spread.
Bake in a 200° oven for 1 hour.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Mix well; set aside.
Cut ribs in serving size pieces.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Turn and bake 20 minutes.
Pour sauce over ribs and bake until tender, about 20 minutes.

title: calico potato salad
directions: Cube potatoes; combine with corn, carrot, onion, peppers and olives in a salad bowl. Pour dressing over; toss lightly. Cover and chill.

title: asparagus bake
directions: Saute onion in oleo until brown.
Add flour, salt and pepper. Cook until blended.
Add sour cream but do not let mixture come to a boil.
Place asparagus in a shallow baking dish and cover with sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle cheese and bread crumbs on top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: marvelous macaroons
directions: Mix together the coconut, sugar and salt.
Stir in egg whites and almond extract.
Mix well.
Stir in almonds.
Drop onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 20 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Remove from baking sheet immediately; let cool.

title: spinach cheese squares
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat eggs. Add flour, milk, baking powder, salt, cheese, spinach and margarine; mix ingredients as they are needed. Pour into pan and bake for 35 minutes at 400°. Cool 30 minutes and cut into bite size pieces or squares. If you use a glass dish, bake at 375°. Can be used as an appetizer or as a vegetable with a meat.

title: golf balls
directions: Stir coconut, powdered sugar, oleo, milk and walnuts together.
Roll into balls.
Freeze.

title: 5 flavor pound cake
directions: Mix together the sugar and margarine until fluffy. Add the eggs and beat well. Stir in the flour, powder and milk; mix well. Stir in the flavorings and mix. Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons brown sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon and keep separate.

title: favorite fruit crisp
directions: Prepare and cut up fruit into a baking dish to depth of 2-inches.
Mix sugar with melted butter. Blend in other ingredients and spread over fruit. Bake at 350° until fruit is tender, usually about 1/2 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: microwave stuffed peppers
directions: Arrange peppers in micro-proof baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients, except tomato sauce and cheese.
Blend thoroughly. Put meat mixture in peppers.
Top with tomato sauce.
Cover with plastic wrap and cook in microwave on High for 20 minutes or until beef is no longer red and peppers are tender.
Remove plastic wrap and top each pepper with cheese.
Cheese will melt.
Serve hot.

title: green pepper and onion potatoes
directions: Using a large sheet of heavy-duty foil, place potatoes, onion and green peppers in center.
Sprinkle with garlic, pepper and red pepper.
Top with pats of butter.
Wrap and seal foil securely.

title: salmon glaze
directions: Simmer over medium high heat.
Cook until reduced by half. Brush glaze over fish while broiling.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together, cook until cheese melts.
In oblong pan, layer tortillas, chicken, onion, soup mixture and grated cheese.
Place layers again in this same order if desired. Cook for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Roll out one can crescent rolls in rectangle.
Place on cookie sheet.
In frypan, cook all ingredients except cheese until pepper is soft.
Put 1/2 mixture on roll rectangle.
Top with 1/2 cottage and 1/2 Mozzarella cheeses.
Repeat layers.
Roll other can crescent rolls in rectangle.
Place on top.
Pinch edges together. Bake at 350° until crust is golden brown.
Serves 8 to 10.
Can be frozen after baked.

title: taco salad
directions: Sprinkle taco seasoning over ground beef.
When ready to serve, mix lettuce, tomatoes, beans and cheese with beef mixture. Pour Italian dressing over salad just before serving.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together; add to hot water to taste.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Mix cream cheese and marshmallow creme together until smooth. Add orange extract.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with sliced fruit of choice.
If needed make proper consistency, add a little milk.

title: kid's soapsud pictures
directions: Beat until mixture resembles marshmallow frosting.
Paint with fingers and allow to dry.

title: welch rarebit
directions: Put beer in pan and boil.
Add cheese, butter and seasonings. Add eggs and cook a few minutes, until cheese is melted.
If thick, add more beer.
Serve over toast.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, oats and butter.
Mix on low in mixer.
Press into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: orange cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package instructions. Add orange Jello. Bake in two 9 inch round pans according to package instructions.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes and place in a greased 9 x 13 pan. Mix all ingredients in the pan. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: chewy coconut cookies
directions: Stir together the flour, soda and cream of tartar; set aside.

title: cioppino
directions: Saute in olive oil the onion, parsley, garlic, red and green bell pepper.
Add tomato sauce, wine, bay leaf, thyme, oregano, marjoram, salt and pepper, cayenne pepper, basil, chili powder and tomatoes.
Stir well.
Cook for 40 minutes.
Add prawns and white fish and cook for 15 minutes.
Add crab legs, etc.
Cook 7 to 8 minutes longer.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish and top with remaining cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour or until firm.

title: luscious pineapple squares
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, pineapple, flour, soda and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir in 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Will turn brown; cool.
Mix the cream cheese, butter, confectioners sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Spread on cake.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup of nuts.
Serves 54 squares.
Can be frozen.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Melt margarine and cook onions until tender.
Butter casserole dish (1-quart to 1 1/2-quart) and line with cracker crumbs. Add onions and soup.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and a few more cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip together and serve with apple slices, orange sections, pears, peaches, bananas and strawberries.

title: cherry pie
directions: Bake pecans into pie shells.
Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar, Dream Whip and salt.
Put mixture into pie shells and top with cherry pie filling.

title: toasted coconut pies
directions: First, toast coconut until brown.
Mix sugar and flour.
Add eggs, butter, milk, coconut and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour in unbaked pie shells and bake for 30 or 40 minutes at 350° or until set.
Makes two pies.

title: yeast bread
directions: Mix and put in covered bowl; refrigerate for at least 2 hours. Make into rolls and let rise about 1 hour.
Bake at 375° to 400° until lightly browned.

title: mock baby ruth bars
directions: Pour melted margarine over oatmeal.
Add brown sugar, peanut butter, syrup, and vanilla.
Mix well and spread in a 9x13 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10-15 minutes.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream margarine; add flour, salt, paprika, cheese, cereal and nuts.
Make into small balls and flatten with a fork.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
These can be kept for a long time in an airtight container.

title: frozen pineapple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze.

title: amish yeast bread
directions: Heat milk.
Dissolve yeast and sugar in 1 cup warm water.
In a large mixing bowl, combine oil, honey, salt, margarine and cold water.
Add cooled milk and yeast mixture.
Add 3 cups flour, then gradually add remaining flour.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Form to make loaves, hot rolls and/or cinnamon rolls.
Let rise, then bake at 350°.
Freezes beautifully.

title: grilled fish rub
directions: Rub fish with a little mayonnaise; then sprinkle rub on--rub it in well with back of wooden spoon.
Rub oil on grill and grill approximately 10-15 minutes depending on thickness of fish filets. Especially good on salmon!

title: dirt dessert
directions: First: Mix together butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Set aside.

title: mandel bread
directions: Beat egg slightly.
Add oil and sugar alternately with electric mixer at low speed.
Beat well. Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Add almond extract and nuts. Pour into lightly greased jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and cut into pieces.
Return to oven to lightly brown.

title: raisin pie
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan combine raisins, water, sugar, salt, cinnamon and vanilla.
Boil over medium heat until raisins are soft and plump.
Add cornstarch to 1/3 cup of cold water and smooth out all lumps.
Stir cornstarch into mixture until consistent.
Pour into an uncooked 9-inch pie crust.
Add top crust and bake at 400° until golden brown.
Cool and feast.

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon until crisp. Remove bacon. Saute onion in 2 tablespoons bacon drippings until transparent, not brown. Cook potatoes in the water with salt, sauteed onion and bacon in covered pan until tender. Add pepper and corn. Blend oleo and flour; stir in milk and cook until slightly thickened. Add to corn mixture; sprinkle parsley, shredded cheese or chips over the top. Serve immediately and piping hot. Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Place chicken pieces and ham slices in large Dutch oven.
Pour on boiling water.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add vegetables. Simmer 1 hour longer.
Taste for seasoning.
Remove bones from chicken and ham.
Let meat cool.
Dice.
Return to soup for 5 minutes before serving.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine zucchini, eggs, sugar and Wesson oil.
Mix thoroughly; empty into a large bowl.
Sift flour, cinnamon, salt and baking soda together and add to wet ingredients.
Add raisins and chopped nuts.
Place evenly in 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: my mom's yogurt
directions: Heat milk slowly over very low heat until small bubbles appear in a
complete
circle
around edge of pot.
Cool.	(My Grandmother always said that it is at the right temperature if you could place
your
little finger in and stir at a moderate speed for 15 times around the edge of the pot.)

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water (salted).
Drain and rinse. Combine remaining ingredients except crumbs.
Alternate with layers of macaroni in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 1 hour. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cranberry jello
directions: Dissolve the jello per instructions on box, adding sugar with hot water.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix completely and chill.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.
Excellent at holiday time.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Chop onions and radishes.
Mix in bowl with softened cream cheese.
Chop imitation crabmeat and add lemon juice.
Mix in with cream cheese mixture.
Season with garlic powder.
Refrigerate 1 hour or more.
Use as a spread on crackers.

title: harlequin salad
directions: Have the peas, beets and carrot cooked till tender.
Shave the cabbage and cut the onion into very small dice, mix all the vegetables, or, if preferred, arrange them in layers or heaps separately.
The effect is better if they are mixed and they are also easier to season and to arrange.
Pour a French dressing over the salad an hour before serving, and pass either a mayonnaise or boiled dressing, or a further supply of French dressing, with it at table.

title: pound cake with nuts
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and eggs slowly.
Add flour and vanilla.
Mix on medium speed.
Add nuts.
Fold in slowly.
Pour in tube cake pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in 325° oven.

title: quick oven potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Coat potatoes with mixture.
Put in a shallow baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Stir 2 or 3 times during baking.

title: children's peanut butter pudding
directions: Add the water to a jar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Place top securely on jar and shake until well mixed.
Pour into bowls and enjoy!

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix 3 packages pudding mix and milk until slightly thickened. Then stir in 2/3 carton Cool Whip and sour cream. Layer with pudding, bananas and vanilla wafers.
Top with rest of Cool Whip. Always start with layer of pudding.

title: meat loaf
directions: Pour over loaf and bake 45 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese. Stir with fork until smooth. Mix all ingredients except 1 cup pecans. Shape mixture into a ball. *Roll in remaining cup of pecans.

title: strawberry cheese cake
directions: With mixer, blend cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk together until smooth.
Add lemon juice and vanilla flavoring, also mixing until smooth.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Let chill for about and hour.
Top with strawberry pie filling.

title: squash dressing
directions: Moisten bread crumbs with water.
Add all other ingredients. If too thick, add more water until mixture pours easily into a greased dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until lightly brown and set.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Combine in large saucepan and heat to boiling.
Crumble tortilla chips in casserole dish.
Pour hot mixture over chips and top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Microwave until cheese is melted, turning occasionally, or heat in oven.

title: old fashioned egg custard
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and butter.
Add flour and vanilla flavoring. Add milk and pour into thawed unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: jewel's sourdough rolls
directions: Mix in a quart jar; cover with foil.
Mix together and put in refrigerator for 4 to 5 days.

title: corn and broccoli casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover top with cracker crumbs and melted butter, mixed.
Bake at 350° for ____ minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar together and let stand. Cream sugar and shortening. Add egg. Add dry ingredients alternately with sour milk.
Add vanilla and rhubarb mixture. Bake 1 hour at 350° in a 9 x 12-inch pan. Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice according to directions on packages. Mix soup with milk. Stir into rice and broccoli, then add onion and cheese to mixture.
Put into a large greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar, soda, vanilla, sour cream, baking powder, eggs, allspice, and cinnamon together in a mixing bowl. Mix until well blended.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until a knife inserted around the edge comes out clean, but may not come out clean in the middle.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Combine Spry, salt and vanilla.
Add sugar gradually, add egg and cream well.
Add baking powder to flour and sift 3 times.
Add small amounts of flour to creamed mixture alternately with the pineapple juice, mixing until smooth.
This may all be done on mixer.
Sprinkle brown sugar on the bottom of pan (8 x 8-inch) that has been well greased.
Arrange pineapple and cherries on top of sugar.
Pour batter over this.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Turn upside down on plate and cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: peachy blueberry cobbler
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a medium mixing bowl.
Combine milk and butter.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix until smooth.
Pour into a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Spread peaches evenly over top of batter.
Sprinkle with blueberries.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until batter rises through the fruit and top is golden brown.
Serve cobbler warm and topped with vanilla ice cream, if desired.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: linguini salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill overnight.
Serve next day.

title: ice cream cone cupcakes
directions: Mix cake mix according to box.
Fill each cone with mix.
Bake on cookie sheet according to box directions.
Remove from oven and cool.
Mix powdered sugar and milk; stir until creamy.
Add vanilla.
Frost cupcakes; top with fresh strawberry.

title: icing for german chocolate cake
directions: Cook margarine, eggs and milk together slowly.
Boil until thick.
Stir constantly.
Add
coconut, vanilla and nuts. Spread quickly.

title: potted beef
directions: Cover bottom of frying pan with Crisco oil.
Cook carrots, green pepper and onion in fat for a few minutes.
Add tomato paste with 1 can of water.
Place beef in pan; add salt and pepper. Simmer until beef and vegetables are tender.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onion and pepper with ground beef.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart greased baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: congealed peach salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Cut peach pickle into small pieces.
Add remaining ingredients and congeal.

title: easy chicken a la king
directions: Slowly heat soup and cream. Stirring constantly, add remaining ingredients. Beat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Serve over toast.

title: galveston gumbo
directions: Saute okra in shortening, about 10 minutes, or until okra appears dry, stirring constantly.
Add green onions, garlic and ground black pepper.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Add stock, tomatoes, tomato paste, thyme, gumbo file and red pepper flakes.
Simmer 1 hour or longer.
Add shrimp and cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.
Serves 6.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix dry and store in jar.

title: butter baked rice
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil.
Pour over rice; let stand 30 minutes.
Rinse with cold water; drain well.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add rice; saute over medium heat until butter is absorbed, about 5 minutes.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan; pour chicken broth over it.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 45 minutes.
Add some parsley flakes; fluff with a fork.
Sprinkle with slivered almonds.
Bake, uncovered, for 10 more minutes.
Serves 12.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and put in greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex cake pan.
Lay chicken pieces on top of rice mixture. Sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Do not peek.

title: date loaf
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients for about 5 minutes.
Add the dates. Cook until soft ball stage. Take off fire and add the pecans and vanilla and beat.
Roll in damp cloth.

title: avocado spread or dip
directions: Mix lemon juice, salad oil, onions, salt, avocado and cream cheese in blender until smooth. Pour into dish.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni according to package directions. Drain.

In a large saucepan over medium heat, melt butter. Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Gradually stir in milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens and mixture begins to boil. Add cheese. Stir until cheese is melted.
In 3-quart casserole, stir together macaroni and cheese sauce.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: german pizza(a recipe for leftover christmas ham)
directions: Pour oil into an electric skillet.
(You may use just a large skillet on top of your stove.)
Slice potatoes and onion thinly and arrange them in the bottom of the pan.
Cover them with some of your leftover ham.
Cook on medium heat for 20 minutes, covered. Turn potatoes so they won't stick.
Lift the lid; pour eggs over the top.
Sprinkle with pepper and a little salt, if you want. Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Lift the lid and place cheese on top. Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Serve.
This should serve 4 to 6 people. Sometimes we serve it with catsup on the side.

title: kahlua cream cheese ball
directions: Dissolve chocolate in Kahlua.
Add to cream cheese.
Mix on low speed just until mixed; do not overbeat.
Mixture will turn soupy if overmixed.
Stir in 1 cup nuts by hand and blend.
Chill 4 hours.
Shape into 1 large or 2 small balls; chill overnight. Before serving, roll ball in 1 cup of nuts.
Serve with assorted cookies (butter cookies, chocolate wafers, etc.).

title: mim's orange jello salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until marshmallows dissolve.
Put in refrigerator until thickens.
Then add apples and pineapple.
Put in refrigerator until set.
Then mix last 3 ingredients and spread on top.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: For Chocolate Cake, use vanilla flavoring instead of lemon and 1 can Hershey's chocolate syrup.
Bake for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: barbecued chicken breasts
directions: Take the skin off the chicken breasts and wash.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in baking dish.
Melt the margarine in saucepan. Add the other ingredients and pour over the chicken. Bake about 1 1/2 hours at 375° or until breasts are thoroughly done.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Boil until candy forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until mixture thickens slightly.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 1-inch pan.
Cut into squares.

title: salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed through peas.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and sugar mixture and pour on top of peas. Sprinkle bacon bits and cheese on top if desired.
Put in refrigerator.
Keeps well.

title: applesauce tea bread
directions: Mix the dry ingredients together.
Add the applesauce, then the egg and milk.
Pour into a nonstick loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Remove the loaf from the pan; cool on a rack.

title: chocolate mint cookies
directions: Cook oleo, sugar and water in large pan over low heat until melted.
Add chocolate chips and stir until partially melted. Remove from heat and continue to stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Pour into large mixer bowl and let stand 10 minutes.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, on high.
Reduce to low and add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill 1 hour.
Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Roll into ball and bake 2-inches apart at 350° for approximately 12 minutes.
Place mint candies on top and let set until soft.
Swirl to ice cookie.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar.
Beat eggs and add to sugar mixture. Fold in pineapple.
Crust bread, cube and fold into mixture. Bake at 400°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Wonderful with ham.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces and saute in pan with chili powder or garlic powder.
Drain liquid after chicken is cooked. Place chicken in large round bowl.
Cut tomatoes into cubes and layer on top of chicken, scallions to follow; salsa and sour cream. Sprinkle whole package of cheese on top of sour cream and pack down firmly.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: ribs with apple butter
directions: Cut meat into 2 or 3 rib portions.
Place ribs, meaty side down, in a shallow roasting pan.
Roast in a 450° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove meat from oven and drain.
Turn ribs meaty side up.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Roast ribs, covered, 30 minutes more.
Mix apple butter, vinegar, onion, garlic, 1 to 2 tablespoons water, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper; pour mixture over ribs.
Roast, uncovered, about 30 minutes more. Serves 6.

title: jalapeno logs
directions: Let cheese stand at room temperature until softened.
Roll into 1-inch logs.
Roll logs in chili powder and chill.
Cut in small pieces and serve.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef with pepper and onion.
Drain liquid from beans.
Combine ketchup, barbecue sauce, Worcestershire sauce and dry mustard.
Drain meat and blend with beans and sauces.
Pour into large baking dish (9 x 13-inch) and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: tortillas de papas
directions: Peel and slice potatoes into 1/8-inch round slices.
Heat 1 cup olive oil in a heavy skillet until hot.
Add potato slices and sprinkle with salt.
Cook until lightly browned.
Add finely chopped onions.
Reduce heat and cook for 10 minutes until potatoes and onions are tender.
Drain oil.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Make corn bread.
Debone chicken and cut in small pieces.
Mix corn bread with onion, celery, green onion and boiled eggs.
Mix broth with corn bread mixture until moistened.
Mix soups together.
In a large baking dish, place half of soup mixture in bottom of pan.
Add dressing mix over soup.
Add chicken on top of dressing.
Pour remainder of soup on top of dressing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: turkey in a skillet
directions: In a nonstick skillet, cook turkey and onion over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain. Add tomatoes, macaroni, green pepper, tomato sauce, water and chili powder (if using). Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes, until macaroni is tender. Top each serving with sour cream.

title: old-fashioned jelly roll
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until thick and lemon colored.
Add flour, baking powder and flavoring.
Pour into a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: hamburg-potato pie
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add ground beef, A.1. and salt; brown. Stir in soup and beans or corn.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine chocolate morsels and condensed milk in a microwave bowl.
Microwave on high for 3 minutes.
Stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly in foil lined 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm about 2 hours.

title: the world's best cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg; mix well.
Add oil, oats, Grape-Nuts flakes, coconut and nuts.
Mix well.
Add flour (little at a time), soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Form into small balls (walnut size).

title: hot fudge sauce(yields 2 cups)
directions: In a small saucepan, melt the butter.
Remove from heat; add cocoa.
Whisk until smooth.
Stir in chopped chocolate, sugar and evaporated milk.
Bring sauce to a boil over medium heat, stirring the entire time.
Remove from heat at once and stir in salt.
Cool briefly, then stir in vanilla.
Keeps nicely in refrigerator.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Combine beef, cornflakes, parsley, eggs, soy sauce, pepper, garlic powder and minced onion.
Make small meatballs.

title: classic pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 425 degrees.
Prepare pie crusts as directed on package for two-crust pie, using 9 inch pie pan.
Melt margarine in medium saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion; cook 2 minutes or until tender.
Add flour, salt and pepper; stir until well blended.
Gradually stir in broth and milk, cooking and stirring until bubbly and thickened.
Add chicken and mixed vegetables; mix well.
Remove from heat.
Spoon chicken mixture into crust-lined pan.
Top with second crust; seal edges and flute.
Cut slits in several places in top crust.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch. Cook eggs, sugar, cornstarch and milk until thick.
Layer vanilla wafers, strawberries and pudding in a large bowl. Repeat layers.
Top with whipped cream or meringue.

title: refried black beans
directions: Soak beans overnight, then cook until soft, drain and save liquid.
Saute onions and garlic in oleo, add to beans and season with 1 to 2 tablespoons cumin.
Cook until thick and use leftover liquid if necessary.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order given:
eggs, brown sugar, sugar, syrup, soda, oleo, peanut butter, oatmeal, vanilla, chocolate chips and M&M's. Drop on a cookie sheet with a large spoon and then flatten batter with a fork.
Bake for 13 minutes at 350°.

title: kolachy dough
directions: Mix yeast in a little warm water to dissolve.
Cream butter, margarine and eggs (yolks).
Add sour cream and yeast (use a wooden spoon). Mix.
Add flour a little at a time.
You can then use your hands to mix real well.
Take some dough and roll out on floured table.
Cut with juice glass or whatever size you want.
Put fruit topping on.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes in 425° oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Mix in other ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cubed potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and chop into tiny cubes.
Boil in water 5 to 10 minutes and drain.
Mix potatoes with onion, flour, butter, salt and pepper in a bowl gently.
Grease casserole dish with margarine.
Pour potato mixture in casserole dish and set in refrigerator for a few hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked chicken dijonnaise
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Arrange chicken breasts on prepared cookie sheet.
Brush each with mustard.
Sprinkle with onion and grated Swiss.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes, until chicken is cooked through and cheese is melted. Serves 4.

title: hamburger taco bake
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and green pepper in skillet.
Add seasonings to taste.
Add taco mix with water as directed on package.
Spray or grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat biscuits out to fit bottom of it.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread hamburger mixture over it; top with cheese.
Bake 15 minutes or until hot at 350°.
Serve with chopped lettuce, chopped tomatoes, sour cream and salsa for each to put on their own serving.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut round steak into cubes and brown in butter.
Sprinkle flour over meat.
Add onion soup mix, 1 cup water and 1 cup milk. Simmer 45 to 60 minutes.
When ready to serve, add sour cream and heat again.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops quickly.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Mix soups together and pour over pork chops.
Sprinkle caraway seed on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruited cheese ball
directions: Blend together well.
Shape into ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Chill well.
Serve with vanilla wafers.
Makes 1 large or 2 small cheese balls.
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: skillet spaghetti
directions: Combine first seven ingredients with 3 cups water and 1 teaspoon salt. Boil, cover and simmer 1/2 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Add noodles; cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until noodles are done, about 1/2 hour.
Serves 8.

title: asparagus casserole(meatless)
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Arrange in layers asparagus (cut into 1-inch pieces), mushroom soup, sliced eggs, cheese and almonds (add asparagus liquid if needed).
Top with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: beefy onion roll-ups
directions: Cut all onions to about 4 inches in length; clean and peel. Cut the cream cheese into 8 equal parts.
Take 1 onion and mold 1 part of the cream cheese around the white end of it about halfway down, then take 1 slice of the beef and wrap around the cheese.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix butter, sugar, flour and baking powder.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans or 18 to 24 muffin tins (or line with paper liners). Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla and oil. Add dry ingredients.
Stir in zucchini and nuts. Pour into prepared pans. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour for loaf pans; 15 to 25 minutes for muffins.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain in cold water.
Add Italian dressing, seasoning, bell pepper, mushrooms and green onion.
Blend Pasta Salad Vinaigretta with oil and vinegar.
Add diced cucumbers; season to taste.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, add diced tomatoes.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix together the dry ingredients (flour, cocoa, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon) and set aside.
Mix together, creaming the butter, sugar, eggs, vanilla, orange peel and zucchini.
Stir in alternately the milk and dry ingredients into the zucchini mixture. Add 1 cup chopped nuts.
Pour into 10-inch buttered Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: After cooking corn bread, cool and crumble.
Add all ingredients, except broth.
Mix well.
Add broth, enough to make very juicy (as it will thicken when cooking).
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until top is brown.

title: embassy cheese ball
directions: Grate and mix all cheeses; set aside, until room temperature is reached.
Add other ingredients.
Spread 3/4 cup nuts over waxed paper.
Shape mixture into ball and roll in nuts.
Let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.
Take ball out 2 hours prior to serving with assorted crackers.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl and serve.

title: puppy chow
directions: Place cereal in a large bowl; set aside.
In a saucepan over low heat, melt chips, butter and peanut butter together, stirring often and until smooth.
Turn off heat and add vanilla.
Pour over cereal and toss until evenly coated.
Take a grocery bag and pour in the powdered sugar, then the cereal mixture.
Shake until all pieces are well coated.
Spread on wax paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: quesadias
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Best if left to make over night.
Roll out and cut into shape.
Cook in aluminum pans with butter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Stir mix on top of the stove.
Cool for
1 hour.
Pour mix into the pie crust.
Serves 4 people or more, depending on how large a piece you would like.

title: sauerkraut relish
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in refrigerator; let stand 24 to 48 hours before serving.
Keeps indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: fruit dip
directions: Add marshmallow cream to cream cheese, blend well.
Add cool whip and serve with chunks of fresh fruit.

title: low-fat crumb cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch dish. Dump pineapple in dish, followed by can of cherry pie filling.
On top of that, dump dry cake mix.
Then, thinly slice margarine and spread over top of cake mix.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
It's best to eat it warm.

title: apple pie
directions: Form crust to shape of pie plate.
Pare and slice apples.
Mix together sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt; toss with apples and put in pie plate.
Dot the top with the butter.
Place top crust on (cut slits in crust).
Moisten edge of apple filled crust and flute edges.
Microwave 10 minutes on High.
Then continue baking in a preheated 450° oven for 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: hot and light potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Melt margarine in a heavy nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, 2 to 3 minutes.
Combine mayonnaise and next 4 ingredients.
Stir into onion mixture.
Add potatoes; cook, stirring constantly 2 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yields 6 servings (156 calories, 6% from fat; per 3/4 cup serving).

title: ambrosia cookies
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients.
Cream together shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Mix together oats, coconut, raisins, dates and nuts.
Stir into creamed mixture.
