Shape into small balls, walnut-size, and place well enough apart to spread while baking on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 12 to 14 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: p.t.a. tea
directions: Place all ingredients in gallon jar.
Add 2 cups hot water to dissolve.
Stir until dissolved.
Fill jar to make 1 gallon tea. Serve over ice.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain and add sauce.
Let simmer on low. Cut up sausage into bite size pieces and brown.
Cook lasagna noodles by directions on box, when done, rinse with cool water and strain.
In 13 x 9-inch baking dish layer ingredients.
Start with thin layer of sauce, noodles, Ricotta cheese, sauce, sausage and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layer again, ending with sauce.
Put layer of Mozzarella cheese; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes, then cut into squares.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine lettuce, tomatoes, beans, cheese, and Frito's.
Pour dressing over mixture and mix well.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in one cup of boiling water, add pineapple with juice and strawberries. Pour one half of this in dish and let set solid in refrigerator. Mix sour cream with mayonnaise and spread over Jello layer. Sprinkle nuts over this and top with remaining Jello and let set again.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Beat well.
May add Blue cheese if desired.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Cook the giblets first.
Crumble cornbread and mix with Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix.
Lightly saute onion and celery in butter.
Add cornbread mixture and other ingredients; mix.
Add more broth if needed to moisten.
Bake in shallow pan at 400° for 15 to 25 minutes, or stuff turkey.

title: make ahead dinner salad(8 servings)
directions: Drain oranges, reserving 2 tablespoons of syrup.
Set aside. Blend together mayonnaise, mustard, lemon
juice, coriander and reserved syrup.
Set aside.

title: pecan grahams
directions: Place graham crackers broken into singles in bottom of flat pan.
Combine pecans, sugar and margarine in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Spoon over graham crackers and place in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and place on wax paper until cool.

title: tuna new orleans
directions: Saute tomato, green pepper, mushroom soup and onion in butter for 5 minutes.
Add celery soup; cook 5 minutes.
Add tuna.
Cook 2 minutes.
Pour over rice.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix together and pour into 13 x 9-inch well-greased pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until browned.

title: cheddar coated olives
directions: Mash together first 5 ingredients.
Wrap around each olives. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, then add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Add sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat 1 minute with electric mixer.
Add carrots, pineapple, nuts and coconut.
Mix and pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: seven layer cookie bars
directions: Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add remaining ingredients, one at a time, in layers.
Bake in a 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Cut into small bars.

title: vegetable stir-fry over rice
directions: Mix soy sauce and cornstarch, then add broth, mustard and ginger.
Set aside.
Heat oil in skillet; stir-fry onions and peppers for 3 minutes.
Stir in pea pods and cook an additional 2 minutes.
Stir in sauce mixture and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Gently stir in bean sprouts until warm.
Serve over rice.
Good served with baked chicken.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water; add flour, 8 tablespoons sugar and salt.
Combine milk and water; add slowly, stirring constantly, to chocolate mixture.
Cook over hot water until thick and smooth or cook in a kettle such as a pressure cooker which has a thick bottom.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly; cool.
Add flavoring.
Pour into baked pastry shell. Cover with meringue made of the stiffly beaten egg whites and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: vicki's breakfast
directions: Brown sausage; drain. Grease 9 x 12-inch pan. Put bread cubes on bottom. Add meat. Pour other ingredients on top.
Top with onions. Refrigerate overnight (very important).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sour cream and eggs in large bowl.
Bring water, butter and chocolate to a boil in saucepan.
Stir hot chocolate mixture into cake mixture until blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carol carrots
directions: Cook carrots; drain and cool.
Cut onions and green peppers in round slices and mix with cooled carrots.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over vegetables.
Cover and marinate for 12 hours or more.
Will keep 2 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: impossible cherry pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°; grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Beat first 5 ingredients 1 minute, or until smooth.
Pour into pan and spoon cherry pie filling over batter.
Bake 25 minutes.
Mix butter with Bisquick; add sugar and cinnamon.
Crumble on pie and bake 10 minutes.

title: hot crab, artichoke and jalapeno dip
directions: In a heavy skillet, cook bell pepper in the oil over moderate heat until soft.
Let cool.
Combine everything with pepper except crab meat until well blended.
Gently stir in crab.
Place mixture in buttered baking dish and sprinkle with almonds.
(Can prepare 1 day ahead to this point.
Keep covered and chilled.)
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes until top is golden and mixture is bubbly. Serve with pita triangles.

title: chocolate cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in milk, 1/4 cup sugar, salt, egg, shortening, cocoa and 1 1/2 cups of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough of the remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; turn greased side up.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
(Dough is ready if indentation remains when touched.)
Punch down dough and roll into a rectangle, 15 x 9 inches.
Spread with margarine.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over rectangle.
Roll up, beginning at wide side.
Cut into 1 inch slices and place slightly apart in greased rectangular baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2 inches.
Let rise until double, about 45 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake 25-30 minutes.
While warm, frost rolls with creamy frosting. 15 rolls; 160 calories easy.

title: can't fail 5 minute fudge
directions: Mix milk, sugar and salt in pan.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 5 minutes; stir constantly.
Time when mixture starts to bubble around edge of pan.
Remove from heat; add marshmallows, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Stir vigorously for 1 minute, until marshmallows and chocolate chips have melted.
Garnish with nuts. Pour out on greased cookie sheet.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour together.
Sift out any lumps.
Add milk and vanilla.
Cook over medium to low heat, stirring often until mixture becomes thick like gravy.
Remove from heat and add margarine.
Serve hot over biscuits for breakfast.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Put ingredients in a crock-pot in order listed.
Stir.
Cook on low for 10 to 12 hours.
Or cook on high for 5 to 6 hours.

title: onion patties(tastes just like onion rings)
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; then add milk.
Batter should be fairly thick.
Add onions and mix thoroughly.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into 1/2 inch of oil in skillet.
Flatten slightly when you turn them.
Brown on both sides until crisp.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Mix together corn, mayonnaise, milk, broccoli, 1/2 of onions and meat.
Stir in egg noodles and 1/2 package cheese.
Put rest of cheese and onions on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until hot.
Microwave time 5 minutes or until hot.

title: betty's pink lemonade dessert
directions: Mix lemonade, Cool Whip, sweetened condensed milk and food coloring.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Put strawberries and sugar in boiler and let come to a boil. Add Jell-O and let cool.
Put Carnation milk in refrigerator freezer in ice tray and let set until it begins to ice around edges.
Beat like whipped cream and add cooled strawberry mixture. Mix well and pour in crust made from vanilla wafers.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Set aside.
Mix salt, 1/2 cup sugar, shortening and boiling water in large bowl.
In smaller bowl, mix eggs and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Beat well until the sugar is dissolved.
Add to mixture in large bowl.
Add 4 cups flour to mixture and stir well, then add the yeast and water and mix well. Add last 4 cups flour and stir real well.
Cover and let rise in refrigerator.
Punch down.
Form in balls the size of walnuts. Place in greased pan, not touching.
Cover and let rise until doubled.

title: spinach-topped tomatoes
directions: In sauce pan, cook spinach according to package directions with bouillon; drain well.
Cool slightly; press out excess liquid. Lightly salt tomato halves and place with cut side down on a paper towel for 15 minutes to absorb excess moisture.
In small bowl, combine spinach, bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, onion, butter, egg, garlic, pepper and cayenne pepper.	Mix well.
Place tomato halves, cut side up in shallow baking dish.
Divide the spinach mixture over tomatoes.
Sprinkle with shredded Parmesan cheese if desired. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: rump roast
directions: Season roast with ingredients. Place all in cooking bag and bake on 350° for 2 hours until done.

title: green congealed salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a 9 x 12-inch dish. Refrigerate.

title: microwave chocolate pudding or pie filling
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in medium size glass bowl. Gradually stir in milk.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes, stirring once during cooking.
Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes until thickened.
Stir in margarine and vanilla.
Pour into cups or 8-inch baked pie shell.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: First, prepare the strawberries, cut and put on sugar.
Stir and let set.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Cream first 6 ingredients.
Add alternately flour and soda mixed in sour milk.

title: pork francese
directions: With knife held in slanting position, almost parallel to the cutting surface, cut tenderloin crosswise into 1/4-inch slices. With meat mallet, pound each slice to about 1/8-inch thickness.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni with salt and drain.
While macaroni cooks, prepare tomatoes, cucumber, pepper, onion, eggs and radishes.
Mix together and add salt and pepper to taste with mayonnaise.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.
Lightly oil spray 12 muffin cups with nonstick cooking spray.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix flour and soda; add all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan or loaf pans.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: peanut butter sandwiches
directions: Spread peanut butter on one slice of bread and spread jelly on the other slice.
Then put them together, then cut in half.
Then eat it.

title: apricot-coconut balls
directions: Combine apricots and coconut; stir in condensed milk, mixing well.
Shape mixture into 32 small balls; roll in sugar.
Let stand until firm.

title: chicken soup
directions: Place chicken, vegetables and dill in a large kettle.
Add water to cover (about 2 1/2 quarts).
Cover and bring to a boil over high heat; skim foam.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover; simmer for 2 hours.
Remove chicken and vegetables; set aside to cool.
Pour broth through strainer.
Slice carrots and dice chicken; return to broth.
Discard all other vegetables and bones.
Add noodles to soup and heat through.
Yields 10 servings.

title: easy potato soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, cook bacon.
Set aside and crumble. Drain grease.
Melt margarine and cook onion and celery until soft.
Add chicken broth, potatoes, carrots, parsley and bacon. Cook until potatoes are done, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Blend together milk and cornstarch; stir into broth.
Heat thoroughly; do not boil.
Add Worcestershire and pepper.
Top serving dishes with dash of pepper and more bacon bits, if desired.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Use a food processor to grind cranberries, oranges and the apple.
Mix with other ingredients. It's a wonderful salad for the holidays.

title: heaven in a pan(my husband's favorite)
directions: Mix flour, margarine and walnuts together.
Press mixture into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip. Spread over cooled crust.
Mix together pudding and milk until thick.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Chill 1 hour.

title: oriental delight
directions: Cut meat into cubes.
Fry meat and onions (onions should be clear). When done, add cabbage and stir, fry about 2 minutes.
Add noodles, water and seasonings.
Cook until noodles are tender.

title: basic sweet and sour sauce
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, combine vinegar and brown sugar. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, stirring until sugar is thoroughly dissolved.
Stir in catsup, soy sauce, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Pour into glass jars, seal tightly and refrigerate for up to 2 months.

title: sweet potato custard
directions: Boil, mash and strain sweet potatoes, then measure. Add butter and milk. Separate eggs.
Beat yolks with sugar. Add to potatoes. Add flavoring. Beat whites stiff and fold into mixture. Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake 30 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: black and white cookies
directions: Cream butter, then add sugar gradually.
Add eggs to this and beat well.
Add vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
In another bowl, mix flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add this alternately with the sour cream to the butter mixture.
Begin and end this with dry ingredients.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto a well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 10 to 12 minutes. Cool cookies and then flip over to ice the flat bottom half chocolate and half vanilla.
Makes about 20 cookies.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and cut the potatoes.
Put fat in skillet.
Keep turning until almost done.
Add the brown sugar and milk.
Reduce heat to low and simmer until done. Serve hot.

title: fruit cocktail dump cake
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and pineapple. Save juices in measuring cup. Evenly spread fruits, coconut and nuts on bottom of 9 x 13 cake pan. Cover with dry cake mix. Melt butter and evenly distribute over cake mix. Add water to fruit juices to make 3/4 cup. Sprinkle juice over cake mix. Bake 40 minutes at 350°. Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: caramels
directions: In a 3-quart heavy saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Cook over medium-high heat until mixture reaches firm ball stage (244°), stirring occasionally.

title: vegetable pilaf
directions: In skillet, in hot butter, cook mushrooms with basil for three minutes.
Add broth and water.
Heat to boiling. Stir in rice; return to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover; simmer for 15 minutes. Stir in zucchini, carrot and parsley.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Let stand covered for 5 minutes. Garnish with tomato wedges.

title: chocolate sin pie
directions: Mix together and spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: stirred custard
directions: Combine
eggs,
sugar
and salt;
gradually stir in hot milk. Cook
in double boiler over hot, but not boiling, water until mixture
coats spoon, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and cool rapidly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix sour cream or yogurt and beef broth.
Blend in red wine vinegar.
Whisk in mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Add to corn. Garnish with tomato, crumbled bacon and green onion.

title: kentucky butter cake
directions: Grease bottom only of a 10 inch tube pan.
Cream butter, gradually add sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one by one, beating well after each addition.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Bake in a 325° oven for 60 to 65 minutes, until top springs bake when touched lightly in the center.
Prepare butter sauce.
Prick top of cake with fork.
Pour warm butter sauce over warm cake.
Cool cake completely before removing from pan.

title: luau baked beans
directions: Lightly saute thinly sliced onion until limp, not brown.
Add catsup, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, ginger, salt, pepper and half of the juice from the can of pineapple.
Simmer about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add baked beans, thinly sliced lemon, pineapple cubes and ham. Add sugar. Allow to simmer about 1/2 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: garlicky lemon chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Dot each piece of chicken with butter.
Scatter garlic over pan.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Take fresh lemon and squeeze all over chicken.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.
Take cover off and let brown.

title: grandma keller's sour cream cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Beat eggs and add to creamed mixture.
Add sour cream to soda.
Sift baking powder, salt and flour.
Add to mixture.
Makes 80 to 90.
Bake at 375°.

title: favorite cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed. Bake in two 8-inch rounds. Thaw whipped topping. After cake cools, place 1 layer on cake plate; top with 1/2 cherry pie filling. Put second layer on top. Place remaining cherries in center of top layer. Frost with whipped topping on outside edges of top and on sides.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except coconut, and cook until thick. Then mix in coconut.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells.
Top with meringue and sprinkle with coconut, then brown.

title: rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let rise at room temperature until double in bulk.
Punch down and let rise again.
Squeeze off small amounts of mixture.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Brush top with butter while hot.

title: some kinda casserole
directions: Brown ground meat; layer in casserole dish with Ranch Style beans, cheese, mushroom soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Put remaining cheese on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all filling ingredients together and spread in greased baking dish.

title: corn and crabmeat soup
directions: Combine the thawed corn with 1/2 cup of the chicken stock in a blender or food processor and mix for about 15 seconds until coarsely chopped.
In a saucepan, combine the corn mixture, 2 cups stock and sugar.
Bring to boil over moderate heat.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in 2 cups water and 1 teaspoon salt; bring to a boil.
Lower heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes. Turn off heat. Let stand for 10 minutes.
Cook broccoli as directed on package. Saute onion and celery in butter.
Mix all together. Add soups and cheese.
Place broccoli-rice in casserole.
Heat in
a 300° oven until bubbling, about 30 minutes.
May be frozen.

title: coconut chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chips and coconut.
Drop by teaspoon or tablespoon on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes if by tablespoon; 8 to 10 if by teaspoon.

title: easy beer bread
directions: Stir together flour, sugar and beer in medium mixing bowl. Spray a 9 x 3-inch loaf pan with Pam cooking spray. Pour batter into loaf pan and bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 40 minutes. Melt stick of butter. Take bread out of oven and pour melted butter over bread. Bake bread for another 10 minutes.

title: butterscotch-pecan puffs
directions: Arrange 6 (6 ounce) custard cups in circle on 12-inch plate. Place 2 teaspoons margarine in each cup.
Microwave, uncovered, on High until margarine is melted, about 1 minute.
Place 2 teaspoons brown sugar and 3 pecan halves in each cup; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Microwave, uncovered, on High until hot and bubbly, 1 to 2 minutes.

title: chili sauce
directions: Grind tomatoes, peppers and onions.
Mix together and add salt. Let stand overnight.
Drain well in colander.
Put in kettle and add vinegar, sugar, mustard and flour.
Boil hard 20 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars.
If desired, add 2 teaspoons red pepper or more if you like it hot.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Melt butter in a skillet, add breasts and cook until lightly brown (but done).
Remove chicken.
Stir in flour and cook for 1 minute.
Add broth and milk.
Stir and cook until thickens and bubbles.
Stir in mustard.
Return chicken.
Cover and heat 10 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: irish cream liqueur
directions: Combine in blender until smooth.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in one pint boiling water and add 1 pint (scant) cold water.
Refrigerate until it starts to jell.
Mix cheese, cream and cherries.
Add this to the jello; refrigerate until set.

title: blender popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
Measure ingredients into blender in order.
Mix in blender at medium speed about 30 seconds.
Pour into muffin cups and bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 minutes longer.
Remove from cups at once.

title: tomato soup salad dressing
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: graham gems
directions: Baking Temperature: 375°.
Baking Time: 15 minutes.

title: cinnamon sour cream biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees. In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar cinnamon, baking powder, soda and salt. Cut in margarine. Make a well in center. Add sour cream, 2 Tbsp. milk and raisins, stirring just till combined (add a bit more milk, if needed). On floured surface, gently knead 8 to 10 strokes. Pat dough to 1/2 inch thickness. Cut with biscuit cutter, dipping in flour between cuts. Place on baking sheet. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool slightly on wire racks. Stir together confectioners' sugar and 2 tsp. milk. Drizzle over biscuits. Sprinkle with additional cinnamon and sugar, if desired.

title: fresh blueberry crunch
directions: Place fruit in a 2-quart baking dish; spread fruit evenly. Combine brown sugar, flour, oatmeal, butter and yogurt; sprinkle mixture over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Contains 5 fat grams.

title: mom's jam cake
directions: This cake is meant to fall in the center.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Reserve 1/4 cup strawberry juice for icing.
Mix jello and cake mix. Add oil and strawberries. Beat 1 minute. Add eggs, one at a time, beating each time until smooth.
Put in greased angel cake pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix everything together.
Put in greased 9-inch pie plate. Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas thoroughly; melt oleo.
Add sugar, egg, flour, soda, salt, vanilla, buttermilk, bananas and nuts; mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in 2 small greased and floured loaf pans or in Bundt pan; let cool before removing from pan.

title: puckett meal
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onions, veggies and juice.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: dinner party potatoes
directions: Defrost potatoes.
Place in buttered 3-quart casserole dish. Combine other ingredients.
Pour over potatoes.
Combine 1/4 cup softened butter with 2 cups cracker crumbs.
Spread over potatoes.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 16.

title: baked salmon croquettes
directions: Drain salmon; reserve liquid.
Add enough milk to make 1 cup. Melt butter in heavy skillet; add onion.
Cook until tender.
Add flour; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk mixture.
Cook until bubbly and thick.
Stir in salt and pepper. Remove skin and bones from salmon.
Flake salmon.
Add lemon juice, 1/2 cup corn flakes and white sauce.
Stir well; chill. Shape into croquettes.
Roll in 1/2 cup crushed corn flakes. Lightly grease sheet; place on sheet.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well, then put in a medium size casserole dish.
Then crush 1/2 cup of cornflakes or potato chips on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken almondine
directions: In medium saucepan bring water to a boil; stir in noodles and chicken flavor sauce.
Continue boiling over medium heat, stirring occasionally, 7 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; heat through. Makes about 4 servings.

title: golden macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Rinse and drain.
Shake together milk, flour and salts.
Add to saucepan with butter and stir until thick.
Add cheese; stir at low heat until melted.
Place macaroni and cheese mixture in casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: deep dish pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Unroll pizza dough and press out with hands on lightly greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake crust at 425° for 6 to 8 minutes or until crust just begins to brown.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Simmer.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: easy egg biscuits
directions: In a bowl, put the flour and make a well.
Add the baking powder, oil, milk, sugar, eggs and flavoring.
With a wooden spoon, mix well.
Batter will be greasy.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Cut shortening with flour and next 5 ingredients with blender or tips of fingers, until it looks like grainy oatmeal.
Add the orange juice, grated orange rind and Egg Beater.
Add to dry ingredients until dry.
Fold in the cranberries and chopped walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: london broil or steak on grill
directions: Use unseasoned meat tenderizer.
Pierce meat with fork.
Add meat to marinade, stirring to coat.
Let stand 2 hours or overnight.
Broil and baste.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Pour half of juice out of each can of peaches.
Pour remainder of juice and peaches in 9 x 13 glass pan.
Pour dry yellow cake mix on top (do not mix in with peaches).
Pour melted butter on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes until brown.

title: microwave chicken breast diane
directions: Place chicken between waxed paper and pound slightly. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In microsafe dish, melt butter and mix with oil.
Place chicken in dish and coat both sides. Microwave at High for 3 minutes. Let rest 1 minute.
Turn breasts over.
Microwave at High for 3 minutes.
Set aside.

title: broccoli corn casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Combine broccoli, corn, egg, onion, salt, pepper, 2 tablespoons melted margarine and 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.
Pour into greased casserole.
Combine 3/4 cup cracker crumbs and 2 tablespoons melted margarine.
Sprinkle over vegetable mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: italian grilled cheese
directions: Top each of 4 bread slices with 1 cheese slice and 2 salami slices.
Sprinkle each with dash of oregano.
Top with bread slice.
Butter both sides of sandwich generously.
Place on hot griddle.
Brown on both sides.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: harvest time sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes 35 minutes until tender when pierced with a fork.
Put syrup in small saucepan with sliced, peeled apples and cook over low heat until tender.

title: one pan banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Stir in oil, eggs, pineapple and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine beans, onion and green peppers in a bowl.
Add brown sugar, mustard, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, salt and cayenne pepper; mix well.
Spoon into a 2-quart baking dish.
Top with bacon.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.
Yields 8 servings.

title: italian chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts into bite-sized pieces.
Beat eggs and soak chicken pieces in eggs for 8 hours.
Bread chicken with Italian crumbs.
Brown in margarine.

title: bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, pour boiling water over bran; mix well and set aside to cool.
In another bowl, mix all other ingredients and stir well.
Add the cooled bran and mix well.
(Add the raisins at this point, if desired, and mix well.) Fill buttered (Pam?) muffin tins 2/3 full and bake for 35 minutes.

title: pierogi
directions: Make a dough by beating 1 egg until very light.
Sift flour and add alternately with the water.
Cream the cottage cheese with a fork.
Beat the remaining egg and add to the cheese.
Mix well. Add the raisins, 3 tablespoons of sugar and salt.
Roll out the dough on a floured board until 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into 4-inch squares and place 1 tablespoon of the cheese mixture in the center of each square.
Fold the dough to shape a triangle and press edges firmly together with a fork.
Drop into boiling salted water and boil for 15 minutes.
Drain well and then fry in deep hot fat until a golden brown.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Serve hot.

title: pecan meringue pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly beat in baking powder, vanilla and sugar.
By hand, fold in crackers and nuts.
Turn mixture into a 9-inch greased pie pan. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Have cheese at room temperature; mix well.
Scald jello with the boiling water.
Add slowly to cream cheese.
Add other ingredients and last of all, add 7-Up.
Stir occasionally so it is well mixed as it cools.
Pour into mold.

title: creamy sure fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, margarine, marshmallow creme, and salt in pot.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture has boiled for exactly 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips and vanilla.
Stir until chocolate is melted.
Stir in pecans or walnuts.
Turn into a buttered pan.
Let stand until firm, then cut into squares.

title: fried green beans
directions: You will need 1 large skillet and lid.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix and bake in square pan, 2 quart casserole or tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with glaze.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Blend 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 10-inch glass pie pan.
Pie crust forms as it bakes.
This recipe works only when mixed in blender.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: original plymouth succotash
directions: In a large kettle or Dutch oven, boil meat and chicken together the day before the dish is to be served.
Soak the beans overnight, then cook until soft enough to mash.
Reheat the meat and fowl.
Skim off fat from broth and add sliced turnip and potatoes.
Cook slowly.
When nearly done, add the mashed bean pulp and corn.
Stir often.
Serve immediately.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: For crust, combine flour, margarine and nuts.
Press in bottom and on sides of a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 6 to 7 minutes at 375° or until slightly browned.
Cool.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Combine sugar and syrup.

Cook in microwave 4 minutes on High. Stir in peanuts and cook 4 minutes on High. Stir in butter and vanilla. Cook on High 1 more minute. Stir in baking soda until light and foamy. Pour mixture onto a lightly greased cookie sheet. Let cool 1 hour and break into pieces.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix together ground beef, egg, oatmeal and salt and pepper. Form into meatballs; brown in skillet. Drain off fat. Combine water, lemon juice, ketchup, brown sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan. Heat to a boil and simmer until thickened. Add to browned meatballs and simmer for 15 minutes. Serve with rice.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook apples until they mash real easy.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook for 20 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from heat and put in pint jars; seal.
Makes 6 pints.

title: cheese roll
directions: Roll Velveeta cheese between waxed paper.
Mix cream cheese and chilies together.
Spread on Velveeta cheese.
Sprinkle with chopped olives.
Roll up and sprinkle with paprika. Refrigerate.

title: sausage egg casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour into a greased 9 x 13 inch pan. Refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Remove from refrigerator, sprinkle remaining 1 cup cheese on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes. Serve with fresh fruit and croissants or juice and biscuits. Serves 8 and is great for company.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except for almonds.
Place in baking dish and cover with sliced almonds.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Serve with large crackers.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute celery, onions and green pepper in the olive oil.
Brown flour in the vegetable mixture.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce. Add salt, pepper, sugar and seasonings.
Cook on slow simmer, stirring occasionally, for about one hour.
Add shrimp and cook just until shrimp turns pink.
Serve Shrimp Creole over rice, add French bread and a salad for a great meal.

title: quick fish-potato supper
directions: Break up potatoes.
Set aside.
In a bowl, combine eggs, milk, onion, seasoned salt, dill and pepper.
Stir in potatoes and cheese. Turn into a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish. Arrange fish sticks on top. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until center is nearly set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: betty's biscuits
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° until golden brown.

title: vegetable dip
directions: In blender, blend mayonnaise, chili sauce and garlic.
Mix olives, pickle, green pepper, chives and eggs, cut in quarters. Blend thoroughly.
Chill.
Serve with fresh veggies.

title: new england indian pudding
directions: Combine milk and apples in top of double boiler.
Bring to a boil over direct heat.
Remove from heat and stir in cornmeal. Cook over boiling water for 15 minutes.
Add molasses and cook another 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Set buttered casserole (not over 1/2 full) in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 350°.

title: toffee refrigerator cake
directions: Cut sponge layers in half crosswise to make 4 layers.
Prepare pudding mix as directed on package, using the 2 cups milk.
Press one of the cake layers into a medium sized mixing bowl.
Add 1/3 of the cooked pudding, another cake layer and so on, ending with the 4th cake layer.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Unmold on serving plate and swirl whipped cream on top and sides.
Makes 8 servings.

title: summer stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops off each pepper.
Cook in boiling water 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove and rinse with cold water.
Remove stems from pepper tops and chop enough to make 1/3 cup.
Brown meat in skillet over medium heat.
Add garlic, onion, carrot, zucchini and 1/3 cup chopped peppers.
Saute until all vegetables are tender.
Add tomatoes, rice, sugar and basil.
Cook until rice is tender, about 20 minutes.
Stuff this mixture into peppers.
Serve.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs until light and lemon-colored (about 10 minutes). Slowly add sugar and lemon juice.
Fold in pumpkin.
Sift flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, baking powder and ginger together and fold into egg mixture.
Prepare 11 x 16-inch jelly roll pan by greasing bottom, covering bottom with waxed paper and buttering the waxed paper.
Pour in mixture.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on damp dishcloth that has been sprinkled with 1/4 cup confectioners sugar.
Roll up and cool.

title: jeff's clam chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crispy.
Drain.
Saute carrots, celery, onion, pepper and garlic in 2 tablespoons bacon drippings until soft.
Add potatoes (1/2-inch cubes) and add clam juice.
Boil, then simmer until tender.
Add seasoning, clams and bacon.
Heat and serve.

title: chinese egg rolls
directions: In bowl, combine the first 11 ingredients and chill.
Prepare batter for egg rolls in mixing bowl.
Sift together flour, cornstarch and salt.
Combine the two beaten eggs and water; gradually blend into dry ingredients.
Beat smooth with rotary beater.
Reserve about 1/2 cup batter for sealing edges of egg rolls.
Pour about 2 tablespoons of remaining batter into lightly greased 6-inch heavy skillet, lifting and tipping skillet to cover bottom.
Cook over medium heat until top looks dry and edges begin to curl.
Do not turn.
Place on paper toweling; repeat, stacking pancakes as they are done.

title: taco pie
directions: Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch dish.
Cook ground beef and onions until brown; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Spread in pan. Sprinkle with chilies.
Beat eggs, Bisquick and milk for 1 minute until smooth.
Pour over meat and bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Top with cheese and bake 10 more minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes. Top with lettuce, tomatoes and sour cream.

title: ham loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 6 ingredients.
Simmer for 10 minutes and add celery, pepper and bread crumbs.
Form loaf.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: pineapple icing
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan and cook until thick enough to spread on cake.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Cook bacon in Dutch oven until crisp, then remove.
Shake steak with flour and brown in bacon drippings.
Add bacon, salt, marjoram, thyme, pepper, onion, garlic, bouillon and wine.
Heat to boiling, then cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add mushrooms and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve with crusty rolls for dunking.

title: strawberry kolaches
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Put shortening, sugar, and salt in large bowl and pour in boiling water.
Stir until ingredients are dissolved.
When they are lukewarm, add the dissolved yeast, beat in the egg and stir in the flour.
Cover with a clean cloth and let rise until doubled in bulk.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Place chicken in a greased, 9 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish.
In a small bowl, mix together all remaining ingredients; pour over chicken.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute celery, onions and parsley in small amount of oleo. Boil ingredients until tender.
Mix milk and flour; blend well. Add to sauteed mixture.
Add potatoes and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Cut up Velveeta and add to mixture.
Can add ham.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine first eight ingredients.
Form into bite size balls. Brown meatballs lightly in oil.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Drain fat, pour chili sauce over meatballs.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until sauce has thickened.
